title: sugar-free pineapple pie
directions: Mix pineapple and sour cream. Add dry instant pudding and mix well; pour into crust. Can be topped with whipped topping. Preparation time about 20 minutes.

title: mom's thin pancakes
directions: Beat eggs and 1/4 cup milk.
Add salt, butter, sugar and flour; blend well.
Add remaining milk and blend.
Over medium heat, place a 10 1/4-inch round griddle.
Brush with butter.
Lift off heat and using 1/3 cup, pour batter on pan.
Swirl the pan quickly to cover, then return to heat.
When pancake is golden brown on bottom, flip it over quickly and cook on reverse side for half a minute.
Turn pancake out on a dinner plate and continue cooking additional pancakes, adding butter to pan as needed.
Spread jelly over pancakes and roll up.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Triple recipe makes about 21 to 22 pancakes.

title: spinach au gratin
directions: Dice bacon and fry until partly done; remove from pan.
Cook spinach according to directions on package; drain thoroughly.
To beaten egg, add 1 tablespoon bacon fat, milk, salt, spinach, bread crumbs and 1/2 of the cheese.
Pour mixture into 1-quart baking pan.
Cover with bacon and remaining cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: mr. bird cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together by hand.
Fold in bananas. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Frost with:

title: cornbread almond stuffing
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Sprinkle poultry seasoning, savor salt, salt and pepper over bread cubes.
To celery and onion mixture, add eggs and almonds; toss.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water; pour over bread mixture, tossing lightly until blended. Stuff bird; put remaining stuffing in casserole.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 40 minutes.
Remove cover; let brown.
Stuffs a 10 to 12-pound turkey, plus extra casserole.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, soda and sugar.
Add zucchini, oil, eggs, vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Bake in 2 loaf pans, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Put sliced apples in 10-inch pie dish.
Mix next 5 ingredients together; pour over apples.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle over top and bake 40 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: noodles
directions: Beat egg yolks and whole egg; beat in cold water and salt. Stir in flour.
Roll thin as possible on a lightly floured board. Cut into strips.
(You may need more flour.)

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small frying pan, fry bacon until clear.
Add the margarine and all other ingredients except the shrimp.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Place the shrimp in an open baking dish and pour sauce over the top.
Stir once to coat all of the shrimp.
Bake in an uncovered dish for 20 minutes, stirring twice during the baking process.
Serve hot and at once.
You may want some French bread to dip in the juice.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a saucepan, cook pudding and milk over a medium heat until thickened and bubbly. Remove from heat and cool slightly.

title: honey baked ham (or turkey)
directions: Using sharp knife, remove layer of skin from ham, leaving a thin layer of fat to keep meat moist and juicy while baking.
Score surface of the ham in a diamond pattern without cutting into meat. Place a whole clove in the center of diamonds.
Baste ham with mustard and place in roasting pan.
Combine sugar, honey and cinnamon; heat over low to medium heat for 2 minutes until mixture is pourable, but not thin.
Spread over ham; pour juice in bottom of pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste every half hour using juice in pan.

title: graham cracker pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites with baking powder until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat well.
Fold in crumbs and pecans.
Pour into well-greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and top with cream.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: fried cornbread
directions: Preheat iron skillet.
Cover bottom of skillet with oil and coat sides and bottom with corn meal after grease is hot.
Pour in bread batter.
Leave on heat until sides of batter cringe.
Put in 450° oven for 15 minutes or until brown edged.
Fry.
Or drop tablespoons into hot oil (Fry Daddy) until crisp and brown.

title: cream biscuits
directions: Mix well, add flour to make a dough.
Spread thinly on a sheet and mark into squares.
Put a dab of butter and powdered sugar on each square and chill for 20 minutes.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: After melting butter, put it in refrigerator for about 30 minutes until a little hard.
Put in bowl and stir in sugar.
Then stir in egg white.
Then stir in flour and baking powder.
Roll the dough into small balls and line up on cookie sheet.
Gently press each on with your finger.
Bake in 350° oven until light brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl until blended.
Roll into bite-size balls.
Bake in shallow pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
May be frozen ahead of time for quick party snacks.
Heat before serving.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; cool.
Add pineapple, with juice, and cherries to cooled jello.
Whip the cream cheese; add to whipped cream.
Blend until smooth.
Combine cream cheese mixture with jello mixture.
Place into mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: red velvet cake(heritage recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix food coloring and cocoa and set aside.
Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs together and beat until fluffy.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Put enchilada sauce, soup and chilies in a large pan with meat.
Bring to a boil.
Crush Doritos and pour in pan with other mixture.
Cook for about 10 minutes on medium heat. Pour into bowl.
Put cheese on top.
Bake in the oven for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: imperial crab
directions: Clean crab shells, if available.
If not, use a baking dish.

title: white trash candy
directions: Melt
butter, peanut butter and butterscotch morsels in a pan. Cool
slightly.
Pour
dry
ingredients into a plastic bag.
Add powdered
sugar, then peanut butter mixture.
Shake well.
Pour into large pan.

title: cathy's cheese ball
directions: Combine the first four ingredients in mixer.
Shape into ball and roll in parsley flakes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: *Use 20 ounces ripple/sliced.
Put in a little water; cook for 3 minutes and drain.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
Mix cornbread to almost pouring consistency.
Add small amount of oil to iron skillet and heat on burner to almost smoking.
Pour out excess.
Pour in batter; it will sizzle.
Place in oven and cook until golden or browner if you like.
Turn into plate; butter and enjoy!

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut over bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour mixture over pecans and coconut.
Cook for 40 to 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet; drain.
Stir in soups and taco sauce. Simmer for a few minutes.
Combine cheese, onion and garlic to taste.
Quarter tortillas.
Line baking dish with 1/2 of the tortillas; top with 2 layers of beef and cheese mixture, with remaining tortillas in between layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry sauce(good for ham)
directions: In a medium-sized saucepan, mix all the ingredients together and cook, covered, over low heat until thickened, at least 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
If you wish, mash the berries with a spoon.
This can be stored in the refrigerator for several weeks.
Yield: about 3 cups.

title: johnnycake(journey's cake)
directions: Sift dry ingredients into medium size bowl.
Add other ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Pour into shallow greased pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Add all ingredients except cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Add cheese to top and bake for 30 minutes.

title: cheesecake dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water and lemon juice.
Let set until thick.
Mix sugar and cream cheese together.
Whip milk; add Jell-O and vanilla to sugar and cream cheese mixture.
Mix crumbs with margarine.
Line 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch dish with the crumb mixture.
Pour in cheese mixture; sprinkle some crumbs on top.
Chill.

title: mozzarella meat pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add green pepper and cook until semi-tender.
Add tomato paste and 1/2 cup cheese; mix well. Separate crescent rolls and press into 9-inch glass pie plate. Form crust and flute edge.
Fill with meat mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
(Use spaghetti sauce to top; warm it first.)

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Do not prepare gelatin with water.
Mix it dry.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: dorthy's soup
directions: Brown ground meat and onion.
Add rest of ingredients to this and simmer 30 minutes.

title: easy fudge
directions: Boil condensed milk and sugar for 9 minutes.
Add marshmallow cream, margarine and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Stir in walnuts. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine
oats
and buttermilk;	let soak for 30 minutes or more.
Mix	flour,	salt,
baking
soda
and baking powder together;
add
oil,
brown
sugar	and
beaten egg to oatmeal mixture and blend thoroughly.
Stir in dry ingredients and mix only until	moistened.
Spoon into 12 cup muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until browned.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel onions; put in blender with eggs and liquify.
Peel and grate potatoes.
(If blender is really strong, can put potatoes in it, too.)
Mix onions, eggs, potatoes and flour well in large bowl.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Mix in remaining ingredients and drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Beat sour cream and eggs and soda with mixer until smooth. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when done.

title: choco-caramel delights
directions: In a small bowl, beat butter, sugar, egg yolk, milk and vanilla until blended.
Stir together flour, cocoa and salt. Blend into butter mixture.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or until firm. Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Beat egg white slightly.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Dip each ball in egg white; roll in pecans to coat.
Place 1-inch apart on cookie sheet. Press thumb gently in center of ball.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy fried rice
directions: Heat oil to 350° in wok or electric skillet.
Add shrimp and stir-fry 1 minute; set aside.
Add egg and stir-fry until firm but still moist; set aside.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Boil zucchini 2 to 3 minutes and drain well.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle generously with grated Jack cheese.
Mix sour cream and dry onion soup mix.
Pour over zucchini.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes or until done.

title: crab and cream cheese hors d'oeuvres
directions: Blend together first six ingredients; put in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle almonds over top and bake at 350° until lightly browned on top.
Serve hot on crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: cool whip lite fantastics 5 minute mousse
directions: Beat pudding with wire whisk into milk for 1 minute.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spoon into 6 dessert dishes.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Garnish as desired.

title: lillie's green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Saute celery, onion and pepper in butter.
Combine the soup and sour cream, mixing well.
Add sauteed mixture, corn and green beans.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole and sprinkle crumbs on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Saute beef, onion and green pepper.
Cook noodles separately. Add tomato sauce, cheese and noodles to beef mixture in casserole dish and sprinkle with either bread crumbs or Parmesan cheese. Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: margaret kirton's vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables.
Mix beans and corn in bottom of long dish. Mix sour cream, onion, cheese and soup together.
Spread on top of vegetables.
Put crushed crackers and almonds on top.
Melt butter and pour over crackers.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy fudge
directions: Bring to a soft ball stage the first 3 ingredients.
Remove from heat.
Add the chocolate chips.
Mix until chips melt.
Add the remaining ingredients.
When mixed real good, pour into greased dish.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: graham cracker snack
directions: Put crackers on baking sheet.
Cook margarine and sugar 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.

title: deviled crab
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: "church windows"(chocolate candy log)
directions: Mix
melted
chocolate,
butter and nuts in large bowl. Pour in	marshmallows
and mix well.
Pour lengthwise on long sheet of foil.
Wrap foil together to form a log.
Seal ends. Refrigerate overnight.	Cut into thin slices.

title: garden supper casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix bread cubes, cheese and butter.
Spread half this mixture in greased 1-quart baking dish.
Add peas.

title: ham and cheese hors d'oeuvres
directions: Slice rolls in half.
Put bottom half back in tin pan.
In a pot, melt butter and saute onions; add poppy seed and mustard.
Put Swiss cheese and ham in a blender.
Mix together, then spread on bottom half of rolls.
Cover with top half of rolls.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: open house mints
directions: Combine butter, shortening, 2 tablespoons warm water and 2 cups sugar; mix thoroughly. Add remaining 3 cups sugar and 1 tablespoon warm water. (If needed, add little more sugar to make mixture stiff enough to roll out.) Add 3 teaspoons warm water mixed with green food color and oil of peppermint; knead thoroughly to mix. Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness on waxed paper dusted with powdered sugar. Cut with tiny cutters or inside of doughnut cutter. Let mints stand bottom side up at least 2 hours (preferable overnight) and store in airtight containers.

title: glazed nuts
directions: Mix sour cream, salt, oleo and sugar.
Boil until soft-ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Drop on waxed paper and separate.
Do not double recipe!!!!

title: quick turkey noodle casserole
directions: In a cup, dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water. Cook noodles according to package directions, drain. In a casserole, combine turkey, noodles and beans. Mix well and sprinkle with cheese. In another bowl combine bouillon mixture, mushroom soup, salt and Worcestershire. Pour over cheese, cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 6.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine
cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme
mixing
at medium speed, with electric mixer until well blended.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the sweet potato, honey, cinnamon and salt together in a large mixing bowl.
In a separate bowl, beat the eggs, then gradually beat in the sugar and vanilla.
Pour the eggs into the potato mixture and mix well.
Add the pecans, if desired and pour into the pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour or until a knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage, onions, green peppers and carrots together in water until tender-crisp.
Drain.
Layer vegetables, cracker crumbs, basil and soup.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Cook chicken; keep 3 cups of broth.
In large bowl, mix 3 cups of broth, 2 eggs and package of stuffing.
In a separate bowl, mix milk, onion, mayonnaise, 2 eggs and diced chicken.
Preheat oven to 250° to 300°.
Spread stuffing mixture in 9 x 12-inch dressing pan.
Pour chicken mixture over top.
Spread cream of mushroom soup over chicken mixture.
Cook 15 minutes.
Then stir mixture all together.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes more, or until golden brown.

title: cherry cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add chopped and well drained cherries.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Chill thoroughly. Serve with graham crackers.

title: homemade salisbury steak
directions: Pat hamburger into patties.
Cook until brown.
Drain patties.
Place soups and water in sauce pan.
Place patties in soup mixture.
Let simmer covered for 30 minutes.
Serve with rice or potatoes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Make a dressing using the mayo, vinegar and sugar; mix and set aside.
Cut the flowerets from broccoli head and discard stems. Toss with the raisins, peanuts and cut up onion.
Add dressing and toss lightly.

title: banana pie
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Add boiling water and butter. Cook until thick, then add egg yolks of 3 beaten eggs.
Stir in well and add bananas.
Pour into the baked pie shell, cover with the beaten egg whites with sugar and vanilla added.
Bake long enough to brown meringue.

title: brandied cherries and cream(low-fat)
directions: Drain cherries, reserving 1/3 cup syrup and 3/4 cup cherries. Set aside remaining cherries.
Combine reserved syrup and cornstarch in a small saucepan; stir well.
Bring to a boil and cook one minute, stirring.
Stir in reserved 3/4 cup cherries and brandy.
Cook 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
To serve, spoon over ice milk and sprinkle with chocolate.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form balls.
Bake under broiler until done.

title: quick banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, butter and bananas.
Add spices and biscuit mix.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: gingered carrots
directions: Cut carrots diagonally into 1/4-inch slices.
Cook carrots in boiling water to cover 7 minutes or until tender; drain.
Keep warm in a serving dish.
Combine next 4 ingredients in saucepan; gradually add orange juice, stirring well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly; stir in butter.
Pour over carrots; toss well.
Makes 8 servings.

title: stephanie's cheese bread
directions: Cut bread into cubes by slicing in 2 directions to form crisscross.
Place bread cubes in ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle cheese over bread.
Combine remaining ingredients in small saucepan.
Heat until butter melts, stirring occasionally.
Pour mixture over bread.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cover with foil first 30 minutes.

title: wassitta casserole(german)
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion together.
Drain.
Add tomato soup, Cheddar cheese soup, cream of chicken soup and corn.
Let simmer.
Cook egg noodles.
In a casserole dish, layer egg noodles and meat mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: cottage deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise; remove yolks.
Mash yolks. Combine yolks, cottage cheese, mustard, milk and chives.
Mix until well blended; season to taste.
Re-fill egg whites. Sprinkle with chives (if desired). Makes 8 servings.

title: cornbread(hand me down recipe)
directions: Mix well and bake in deep sheet pan at 350° until it passes the toothpick test.
Serve with butter or go on to make cornbread dressing.
You can make the cornbread up days in advance of making your dressing in order to save time.

title: swiss cheese potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Reserve 1/3 cup cheese. Combine remaining cheese, parsley, tarragon and garlic. Toss potatoes with salt and pepper. Pour 2 tablespoons butter into shallow 10-inch round baking dish. Starting and ending with potatoes, alternately layer potatoes and cheese-herb mixture in dish. Drizzle with remaining butter. Cover with foil. Bake on upper rack for 1 hour. Remove foil. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 35 minutes or until golden.

title: baked fruit
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender and remove from bones.
Make a layer of bite size pieces in bottom of a 9 x 11 1/2-inch glass baking dish.
Mix can of soup with 1/2 to 1 cup of broth from chicken. Pour over chicken.
Mix flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Do not stir.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in boiling salted water to cover until just tender.
Drain and set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add to squash, eggs, milk, cheese, sugar and crackers.
Add onion and green pepper to squash mixture.
Spoon into greased casserole and cover with additional cracker crumbs. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cake that doesn't last
directions: Mix until well blended and pour into large greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: 4th of july potato salad
directions: Cut up boiled potatoes bite size.
Add mayonnaise, mustard, chopped dill pickles, olives, juice from one can and celery.
Mix well.
Chill.
More mayonnaise may be desired.

title: date bars
directions: Stir sugar, flour, vanilla, egg yolks (well beaten) and baking powder together until crumbly.
Add nutmeats and chopped dates. Fold in beaten egg whites. Bake on a cookie sheet in moderate oven. Cut in strips when cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: turkey lasagna
directions: Brown turkey in saucepan; drain.
Add cottage cheese and sauce.
Reserve 1 cup sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put one layer of noodles in bottom of 9 x 13 baking pan.
Spoon layer of meat mixture over noodles.	Put some cheese on top.
Continue as directed.
Should end with noodles as top layer.
Put reserved sauce over top and cover with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight. Cover with foil and bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve hot.

title: chipped beef in a bread bowl
directions: In a large bowl, combine the sour cream, cream cheese, cheddar cheese and chipped beef.
Mix until smooth.
Cut off top of bread bowl and remove inside.
Pour dip mixture into bowl and replace top.
Wrap in aluminum foil and bake at 275 degrees for 2 hours.
Use the inside bread or crackers for dipping.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Beat eggs; reserve a small portion.
Mix sugar, flour and rhubarb.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; pour reserved egg over top. Bake at 425°.
When it begins to turn brown, turn down to 350° and bake until center sets.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine soup and milk.
Add drained beans and 1/2 can fried onions. Put in casserole and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cover with rest of onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: success cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar and add the water.
Never mind its looks.
Then add the flour and baking powder, after sifting together.
Stir this thoroughly and then add the stiffly beaten whites of the eggs.
After that, beat it for 5 minutes.
Finally, add the flavoring extract, whichever one you prefer, and bake immediately.

title: night before french toast
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cut bread into 1 inch thick slices and arrange in one layer of pan.
On large bowl beat eggs with remaining ingredients, except butter (margarine).
When thoroughly mixed, pour over bread.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 4 to 36 hours.
Bake uncovered.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until bread is puffy and lightly browned.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain.
Add 1 package taco seasoning; let cool.
Mix vegetables, meat and cheese together.
Mix Thousand Island dressing, 1/2 package taco seasoning and hot sauce to taste. Mix into salad.
Serve with taco chips.

title: meat loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Place shortening in with flour; cut
with pastry blender.	Add ice
water;
mix.
Roll out with rolling pin; shape into pie pan.
Makes an 8-inch pie crust.

title: orange (or lemon) balls
directions: Mix together and form into small balls. Roll in coconut and/or powdered sugar. Store in refrigerator.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix hamburger and taco mix together and spread in bottom of long dish.
Heat beans and spread over meat.
Layer sour cream, chili dip and cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with chips.

title: apple pie
directions: Place apples, 3/4 cup sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon in crust. Make paste with sugar, flour and butter.
Spread over apples in crust.
Place in a brown bag.
Fasten end and bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: peace 'n plenty wheat rolls
directions: Heat water, milk and shortening until very warm; shortening doesn't need to melt.
Combine 3 cups white flour, 1 cup wheat flour, sugar, yeast, baking powder and 5 eggs.
Pour liquid mixture over this, beating at medium speed, about 3 minutes.
Add remaining flours gradually.
Knead until smooth and elastic. Dough is ready for shaping.

title: asparagus canapes
directions: Cut crusts off bread and roll with rolling pin.
Combine cheeses, Miracle Whip and egg.
Spread each slice of bread with 1 teaspoon cheese mixture.
Top with asparagus spear and roll up. Cut each slice in 3 pieces.
Dip each piece in melted margarine. Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Place in storage container when frozen.
Later, bake as needed, at 350° for 20 minutes or until slightly golden.
Makes approximately 60.
Serve hot.
(These keep about 3 months in freezer.)

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar, then 1/2 carton Cool Whip.
Pour into prepared deep dish pie shell and top with remaining Cool Whip and mini morsels (if desired). Refrigerate.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook about 3 hours.

title: blueberry hot bread
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar. Add milk and melted butter. Add flour, salt and baking powder. Mix until just combined; do not try to get it smooth. Toss blueberries in a little flour to keep them from sinking to the bottom of the bread. Fold blueberries into mixture. Pour into 2 small, very well greased bread tins. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer beginning with mushroom soup and finish with soup on top layer.
Cook covered with foil 25 minutes at 350°.
Uncover, top with onion rings and cook 5 more minutes.

title: southern baked beans
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and brown with chopped meat and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: mom's brown bread
directions: In a saucepan bring the water to a boil.
Add raisins, butter and soda; remove from heat.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, vanilla and salt and stir into raisin mixture.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add margarine and milk.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Add fruit.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with milk or cream.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chicken apricot
directions: Mix all together.
Pour over chicken in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Baste several times with the marinade.
Serve with rice!
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet, then saute rice until golden.
Add soup mix, water and soy sauce.
Cover and simmer 30 to 35 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Add onions.
In another pan, scramble eggs.
Add eggs to rice and serve.

title: aunt ethel's fruit dip
directions: Cream together all ingredients and chill.

title: pumpkin-apple streusel muffins
directions: In large bowl combine flour, sugar, spice and soda; set aside. In medium bowl combine eggs, pumpkin and oil.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened.
Stir in apples.
Spoon into greased or paper-lined muffin cups, filling 3/4 full.
Sprinkle with Streusel Topping.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: crisp cream puffs
directions: In medium saucepan, bring water to boil.
Add mix all at once over low heat.
Vigorously stir until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a ball, 1 minute.
Beat eggs, one at a time, until smooth.
Cool slightly.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 3-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 325° and bake 20 minutes. Cool on rack from drafts.

title: red devil's beet cake
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients in blender until smooth. Place the rest of the ingredients in bowl and add blender mixture; hand mix together. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lime jello dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Stir well. Chill until slightly thick.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: make-ahead meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs. Add the next five ingredients. Add beef; mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls, about 12 dozen. Place in single layers in ungreased 15 x 10 inch baking pans. Bake at 400° for 10 - 15 minutes or until no longer pink, turning often; drain. Cool. Place about 30 meatballs each into freezer containers. May be frozen for up to 3 months. Recipe makes 5 batches (about 30 meatballs per batch).

title: scalloped cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage and cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Melt 2 tablespoons oleo with 2 tablespoons flour.
Add milk, cheese, salt and pepper.
Put cabbage in a greased casserole and pour sauce over.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo and stir into croutons; place on top of cabbage.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fresh tomato and white bean chili
directions: Core tomatoes; chop and set aside.
In a large saucepan, over medium-high heat, heat oil and add onion and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add chilies, cumin, oregano and red pepper; cook 30 seconds to 1 minute or until seasonings are fragrant.
Stir in beans, chicken broth, chicken, sugar and 3 cups of chopped tomatoes.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low and cover; simmer about 15 minutes.
Stir in one cup of reserved tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes longer or until tender.
In individual bowls, place 3/4 cup rice.
Spoon in chili and sprinkle with remaining one cup of tomatoes.

title: puffy potatokins
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine prepared mashed potatoes and egg; stir until well blended.
Add flour, garlic salt, onion salt and grated Parmesan cheese.
Blend well.
The mixture will be soft and sticky.
Using two teaspoons, form into 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls. Roll each ball into crushed cereal.
Put onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Best when served hot.
Makes 12 servings.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix the sugar, cinnamon, nuts and coconut; set aside.
Beat until fluffy 1 cup butter, 2 cups sugar, vanilla, salt and eggs. Combine flour and soda; add alternately to the butter mixture with the sour cream.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
Saute onions in margarine until tender.
Add soup, milk and cheese melts.
Stir in rice and broccoli.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Sprinkle crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift flour and 1/2 cup sugar together 4 times.
Measure eggs into large bowl; then beat to a coarse form.
Measure and sprinkle over surface of whites the salt, cream of tartar and flavoring. Beat until whites are still moist and slightly foamy.
To test, shake bowl gently; meringue should slide slightly in bowl.
Add remaining 1 cup sugar in 2 tablespoon portions, sprinkling it over the surface; and beat in.
Fold in flour mixture in 4 portions, gently but thoroughly.
Pile lightly in ungreased tube rinsed with cold water.
Insert knife and circle batter twice to cut any air pockets.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 minutes.

Touch surface lightly with fingertip; when cake shrinks from sides of pan, it is done. Invert pan and cool thoroughly, about 1 hour before removing cake. Serve uniced or frost with Boiled White Frosting.

title: 5 can casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to directions; drain and dry.
Mix all other ingredients and fill each shell.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: calico bean soup
directions: Wash dried beans thoroughly.
Place in a large kettle, cover with water and add 2 tablespoons of salt.
Soak overnight.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Brown beef, drain excess fat.
Saute onions, carrots and celery in butter.
Add soy sauce and seasonings.
Add beef, rice, soup and water.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Place in large casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Fix rice per instructions; after rice is ready, place in a large bowl.
Add Cheez Whiz and mushroom soup.
Fix broccoli as per instructions after draining.
Mix with rice and cheese mixture; place in oven for 10 to 15 minutes, until mixture is heated throughout.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and buttermilk until smooth and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, and beat after each.
Stir in mashed bananas and nuts.
Add flour a little at a time and beat well after each time.
Pour into loaf pan that has been well-greased and floured.
Let stand 10 minutes and cover with foil.
Bake in a moderate oven for 20 minutes, then uncover and bake until toothpick comes out clean, about 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie crust and chill. Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook turkey and tofu until mostly browned, drain.
Use large soup size pot.
Heat pan, add olive oil and vegetables.
Cook, stirring frequently until veggies are somewhat limp.
Add spices, turkey-tofu mixture and tomatoes.
Bring to a mild boil and simmer gently for 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Add tomato paste. Remove from
heat, allow to cool.
Makes 6 quarts.
Freezes well. Use in lasagna, pizza or your favorite pasta dishes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
When dissolved, add to other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Let rise 30 minutes or refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: health bread
directions: Boil raisins in water for five minutes, then cool.
Combine this mixture with the other ingredients that have been thoroughly mixed together.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: string bean salad
directions: Marinate the beans and onion overnight in the oil and vinegar. In the morning, drain and add the Sour Cream Sauce.

title: chicken easy
directions: Place cooked and deboned chicken in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix all soup and mix together; pour over chicken. Pour 1 cup of broth over entire mixture.
Add your melted margarine over entire mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken.
In a bowl, combine bread crumbs, herbs and Parmesan cheese.
Add seasonings and mix well to blend. Melt butter.
Dip chicken first in melted butter, then into crumb coating.
Arrange chicken in lightly oiled baking dish.
Bake at 350° until chicken is lightly brown and done.

title: green chili cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done in center.

title: candied peanuts
directions: Mix in saucepan and bring to a boil until water evaporates. Pour on cookie sheet, separating into big chunks.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Mix butter, cheese and flour.
Mold 1 teaspoon mixture around each olive.
Place on cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
May be cut in half.

title: deluxe waffles
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
This makes 4 batches in my waffle iron.

title: harvest cake squares
directions: Empty pie filling in bowl and cut any large pieces.
Stir in nuts and raisins and set aside.
In a large bowl, add cake mix, apple pie spice and nutmeg.

title: lemon pasta
directions: Combine oil, parsley, lemon peel and pepper in saucepan.
Heat gently. Combine stock, lemon juice and cornstarch and add to oil mixture, cooking until slightly thickened. Add pasta which has been cooked to al dente.
Transfer all the pasta and sauce to a warm serving bowl. Add grated cheese.
Toss until well mixed. Serve at once with additional grated cheese, if desired. Serves 4 as appetizer.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in serving dish.
Top with remaining items in different layers.
Black olives and sour cream on top are optional.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Melt butter in pie plate that you are going to use.
Place ingredients in blender and blend on medium speed until all is blended, about 15 seconds.
Pour mixture into pie plate and cover with 1 cup of flaked coconut.
Bake at 350° until set or knife in center is clean.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Cook frozen vegetables as directed on the package; drain and cool.
Drain and rinse kidney beans.
Chop celery, green pepper and onion.
Mix altogether.
Stir in a medium saucepan sugar, flour, water and vinegar.
Cook on medium heat until thick, about 6 to 7 minutes.
Cool.
Pour over vegetable mixture and place in a long casserole.
Refrigerate.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add eggs, onion and buttermilk.
(Should be thick enough to spoon into hot oil.)
Fry hush puppies in oil fish was fried in.
Use an ice tea spoon to dip batter, drop into hot oil.
The batter can be refrigerated up to one week; flavor is better.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add cocoa mixed with flour and salt.
Add eggs, then nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour marshmallows over cake while hot.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly all ingredients; beat until smooth.
Divide batter into 3 loaf pans, greased well.
Bake for 1 hour, or until done.
Cool 5 minutes, then turn out onto plate.

title: baked egg custard
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add to milk and mix well. Pour into crust and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taquitos
directions: Mix avocados, onion, salt and lemon juice.
Set aside.
Warm tortillas over fire in skillet or on grill.
Place roast beef in center of tortillas and roll lengthwise; secure with toothpick. Fry in skillet with oil.
When done, remove and place on plate with paper towel.
Serve with avocado mixture or salsa as desired.

title: pineapple crunchies
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve liquid.
Sift flour and baking soda. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add flour mixture, vanilla and 1 tablespoon pineapple liquid.
Stir in corn flakes.
Press into balls 1 1/4 inches in diameter.
Place on cookie sheet and make an indentation in each.
Fill with crushed pineapple and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in 350° oven about 20 minutes.
Store uncovered.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Beat eggs and add to creamed ingredients.
Add lemon juice.
Beat well.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° until brown, approximately 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream butter, adding sugar gradually. Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Alternate with pumpkin and water until flour disappears.
Stir in raisins.
Fill greased and floured muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: seven layered salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in a 3-quart bowl.
Mix vinegar and next 5 ingredients in a small bowl, stirring with a wire whisk. Pour vinegar mixture over vegetable layers.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover and chill.

title: barbecue stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Brown ground beef, stirring to crumble.
Pour off excess fat.
Stir in can of tomato sauce.
Add brown sugar and mustard.
Simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Spoon over baked potatoes.

title: bo jangles cajun rice
directions: Brown sausage, pour in undiluted chicken broth.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice, onion and celery.
Cover.
Let it simmer for about 20 minutes or until most of the liquid has been absorbed and rice is tender.

title: creamy sliced tomatoes
directions: In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, cream and half of basil; mix well.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, arrange lettuce, tomatoes and onion on individual salad plates.
Drizzle dressing over.
Sprinkle with remaining basil.
Yields 12 servings.

title: cheese strata
directions: Butter one side of bread.
Place 6 slices of bread, buttered side up, in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan (Pyrex is good). Sprinkle with cheeses.
Cover with remaining bread slices, buttered side down.

title: cabbage pudding
directions: Melt butter and mix all thoroughly, adding baking powder last. Turn into Pyrex dish and bake until brown.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.

title: beef and broccoli casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Stir in flour, salt and garlic salt. Add milk and cream cheese.
Cook until thick and smooth.
Add a little of the hot mixture to the beaten eggs.
Put back into skillet and cook a few minutes.
Stir in broccoli.
Pour into large shallow baking dish, lightly greased with butter.
Arrange cheese slices on top of hamburg mixture.
Place rolls flat on top and brush lightly with milk.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
If browning too quickly, place foil loosely on top.

title: potluck appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients well and spread on slices of bread. Toast under broiler.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese on top of bread.
Place ham on top of cheese. Pour melted butter over all.
Beat eggs with mustard, salt and milk.
Pour over casserole.
Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours before cooking.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until crust forms and is firm.
Serves 10.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti; stir in butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form a crust in 10-inch buttered pie plate.
In skillet, cook meat, onion and green pepper until meat browns and vegetables are tender.
Drain off excess fat; add tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Heat.
Next spread cottage cheese over spaghetti crust, then spread meat mixture over cottage cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and spread in bottom of greased 9 x 18-inch pan.
In a separate bowl, mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and 3 eggs.
Spread over first mixture. Bake until brown at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: breadsticks for a crowd
directions: In a large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast. Blend well.
In a small saucepan, heat water and oil until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add warm liquid to the flour mixture and blend at low speed.
By hand, stir in additional 2 1/2 to 3 cups flour, until dough pulls cleanly down and away from sides of bowl. Flour surface and knead 1/2 to 1 cup flour until dough is smooth and elastic.
Place dough in greased bowl.
Let double in size. Punch down.
Divide in half.
Shape into breadsticks.
Brush with egg whites.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 14 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Stir in flour, chili powder, salt and sugar.
Add broken up tomatoes and simmer about 10 minutes.
Add kidney beans.
Bring to boil and then simmer 10 minutes.
Add more chili powder if you want it hotter!

title: cheese cake
directions: Line bottom of tube pan.
Mix sugar, cheese, flour, vanilla and lemon juice.
Drop in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in cream from bottle.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Turn oven down to 200° and bake 1 hour.
Remove from pan when cool.
Do not grease pan.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in 8 x 12-inch glass Pyrex dish 30 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together shortening, sugars, vanilla and egg.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture; blend well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop from a teaspoon 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on a cookie sheet about 1 minute; then remove to a rack to finish cooking.
Makes approximately 3 to 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: italian zucchini quiche(a.k.a.:  immigrant pie, italian pie)
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in butter for 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano.
Combine eggs and cheese and stir into zucchini mixture.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles and press over sides of ungreased 10-inch pie pan to form crust.
Spread with mustard and pour vegetable mixture into crust.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes or until center is set.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: homemade chili
directions: Soak beans in water.
Boil 30 minutes.
Chop up chuck into 1/2-inch chunks.
Cook until brown.

title: cheese strata
directions: Place six slices of bread in bottom of casserole.
Sprinkle half of sausage and half of cheese on bread.
Pour half of milk and eggs over all.
Place six remaining slices of bread in casserole and balance of sausage and cheese.
Pour balance of milk and eggs over all.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Cook uncovered in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, add all dry ingredients, then add the beaten eggs and oil.
Mix together thoroughly.
Fold in chopped apples and nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown (approximately 45 minutes).

title: golden raisin cookies
directions: In a saucepan, combine raisins and water.
Cook over medium heat until water is absorbed.
Cool.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Set aside.
Cream butter; add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and orange extracts.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in walnuts and raisins.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in a pie plate.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into cinnamon-sugar and coat well. Place sugar coated balls on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart. Bake in a 350° oven for 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion together.
Add vegetables and tomato soup.
Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Very good served with corn bread.

title: bean soup supreme
directions: Soak overnight navy beans.
Drain and add water, red pepper pod, bay leaves and a ham bone.
Bring to boil and reduce heat, cooking slowly for 2 1/2 hours.
Discard ham bone, pepper pod and bay leaves and add remaining ingredients.
Return to boil and reduce heat, cooking slowly for 1/2 hour.

title: green beans hong kong
directions: How To Cook:
Snap off ends.
Leave whole, cut French-style into lengthwise strips or cut crosswise into 1-inch lengths.
If desired, add a clove of garlic or a bit of onion while cooking. Cook, covered, in 1/2 to 1-inch boiling salted water: whole beans, 15 to 20 minutes; cut, 15 to 20 minutes; French-cut, 10 minutes.

title: famous ranger pancakes
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, vanilla, eggs and oil.
Stir until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add extra milk to obtain good working condition.
Grease grill with Pam to keep pancakes from sticking.
Heat grill until a drop of water indicates grill is hot.
Cook until bubbles appear (approximately 19 per cake).
Turn and cook on other side.
Store in Dutch oven with plate in bottom until ready to serve.

title: beef ball
directions: Dice dried beef and mix with cream cheese. Add a dash of garlic or onion salt to taste. Blend all ingredients together and roll in a ball. May be sprinkled with dried parsley or paprika for decoration. Chill until firm. Slice and serve with crackers.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Remove chicken from broth. Let cool. Debone and cut into bite-size pieces. Add noodles to broth and cook until tender. Remove about 1/2 cup of broth and set aside. Saute the onion in butter and set aside. Drain noodles and put into baking dish. Add chicken, soups, tomatoes, onions, Cheddar cheese and half of Velveeta cheese. Mix well; add a little broth for moistness, if needed. Top with other half of Velveeta and bake at 350° until cheese melts, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients until dough sticks together.
Roll into balls the size of walnut.
Bake
for 25 minutes; drain on paper towels.
Serve warm on toothpicks. Makes about 75 pieces.
Great for the holidays or small parties.

title: pumpkin gobs and icing
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
When cool, ice with Gob Icing.

title: scalloped sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Boil potatoes in water for 25 minutes.
Drain and let cool. Peel and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Melt butter in small pan. Add brown sugar, cider and mace. Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.

title: divinity puffs
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water to a thin syrup stage. Slowly pour 1/3 over egg whites, beating constantly.
Cook remaining syrup to thread stage.
Add 1/2 to egg white mixture, beating constantly.
Cook remaining syrup to form ball stage.
Add to egg white mixture.
Add vanilla; beat until mixture holds shape when dropped from a spoon.
Serve from teaspoon onto wax paper. Can sprinkle nuts on top.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1 white cake mix (dry) with 1 stick melted oleo until crumbly. Sprinkle over pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil your broccoli; drain.
Melt both cream cheese and Velveeta cheese; mix with broccoli after they are melted.
Put broccoli and cheese in a deep baking pan.
Mix crackers and butter; pour on top of broccoli.
Cook at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Layer in a 13 x 9-inch glass dish sprayed with Pam.
Heat on High in microwave the soup and onions until just bubbly.
Stir in some sour cream.
Set aside.
Heat the tortillas as in microwave on High for about 90 seconds.
Spread a bit of soup mixture on bottom of dish.
Add a layer of tortillas, soup mixture and cheese.
Keep layering until dish is full, ending with cheese on top.
Heat in 350° oven until cheeses melt (or in microwave on High for about 15 minutes).
Serve with a salad and baked (not fried) corn tortillas and your favorite salsa.
We've used this recipe since the early 1970's, a family favorite.
We recently "de-fatted" it a bit!

title: american indian corn cob jelly
directions: Boil the red corn cobs in 3 pints of water for 30 minutes; remove from heat and strain.
If needed, add enough water to make 3 cups liquid.
Add the fruit pectin; bring to a boil.
Add the sugar; boil for 2 to 3 minutes, until jelly stage.
Tastes like apple jelly and is red in color.

title: nettle tonic
directions: Wash the nettles well in several waters, wearing protective gloves.
Put them into a saucepan and cover with boiling salted water.
Cook very gently on top of the stove for a half hour. Strain and drink a tumblerful, hot or cold, first thing in the morning.
Guaranteed to put roses in your cheeks and a glint in your eye.
Not pleasant, but you must suffer to be beautiful.
When cooked, they taste like spinach, only more delicate.
They are included in the diet of race horses and greyhounds.

title: peanut butter and chocolate kisses
directions: Mix sugars, peanut butter, eggs, margarine, vanilla and salt until light and fluffy.
Then add flour and baking soda; beat until blended.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls dipped into sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately top each cookie with a candy kiss, carefully pressing down firmly.
Remove cookies from baking sheets; cool on racks.
Bake at 375°.

title: rose bowl potpourri
directions: Combine all, cover and cure for 6 weeks in dry, dark, warm place.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mash or dice potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix thoroughly.
Divide into 12 portions; shape into balls.
Chill.
Drop into one of the following liquids which is gently boiling:
stew, turnip green pot licker, beef broth, chicken broth, pork broth, water or whatever you have.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter and add flour. Add milk a little at a time. Add grated Cheddar cheese and black pepper

and cook until thickened. Put layer of asparagus tips in bottom of casserole dish. Cover with layer of sauce. Add layer of asparagus tips and cover with sauce alternating until final topping with sauce. Top with cracker crumbs. Bake in 350° oven until cracker crumbs are brown. Do not overcook.

title: hot taco rice
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain and add salsa, tomato sauce and bouillon.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes. Prepare rice per package directions, separately.
Serve beef mix over rice.
Garnish.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Mix sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire, salts and seasonings.
Coat chicken with mixture and then roll chicken in stuffing mix.
Place chicken into greased, shallow pan.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix milk and sugar.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat to low and boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Quickly mix thoroughly.
Pour in a buttered pan.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add cream, blending.
Add egg yolks, stirring all ingredients well.
Add water.
Cook on low heat until mixture thickens.
Add butter.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells. Cover with meringue made with egg whites;
Brown.
Cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together corn syrup, sugar, eggs, vanilla and peanut butter. Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 45 minutes.

title: kuchen bars
directions: Mix ingredients into thick batter and spread into 10 X 16 pan or two 9 X 9 pans. Arrange fruit over batter (banana slices, blueberries or cooked apple slices).

title: bill's favorite black bottom pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Slowly add scalded milk to beaten egg yolks.
Stir in sugar mixture.
Cook and stir in top of double boiler until custard coats spoon.
Add vanilla.
To one cup of custard, add chocolate bits.
Stir until melted.
Pour on cooled pie shell.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add to remaining hot custard.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill until slightly thick. Beat egg whites, adding sugar gradually until mixture stands in stiff peaks.
Fold custard-gelatin mixture.
Pour over chocolate layer and chill until set.
Garnish with whipped cream or shaved chocolate.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, egg, molasses and water. Add gradually flour and spices.
Drop teaspoon size dough onto greased tins.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: overnight breakfast rolls
directions: Place frozen rolls in well-greased Bundt pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over rolls.
Cover with foil and a towel.
Let sit at room temperature overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly before turning out.

title: huevos revueltos ranchos
directions: In large skillet cook chopped onion in the 1 tablespoon of oil till tender.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, chili peppers, chili powder and garlic powder.
Simmer, uncovered for 5 to 10 minutes or till slightly thickened.
Meanwhile, place tortillas on a baking sheet; brush lightly with the 1 tsp. of oil.
Bake in a 350° oven about 10 minutes or until crisp.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel, cut and cook potatoes until done.
Boil eggs; peel and cut into small pieces.
Drain potatoes and mix all ingredients together while potatoes are hot.
I use a lot of pepper to season.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Put all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Start in a cold oven.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Fifteen minutes before done, arrange cheese slices on top.
Return to oven for remaining time.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chili and cheese dip
directions: Blend cream cheese until spreadable. Spread in 13 x 9 x 3 dish. Place sliced Monterey cheese on top of cream cheese. Spread drained cans of chili on top of Monterey cheese. Sprinkle cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 350 for about 20 minutes or until hot through and through. Serve with chips.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream shortening to soft, add sugar and cream until light and fluffy, add syrup and salt; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well each time.
Stir in pecan halves.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Break up cranberry sauce with a fork. Add to jello. Pour into mold and chill until almost set (very thick). Fold in apples and celery and return to refrigerator until firm. Unmold and slice.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Debone chicken and cook with onion.
Wrap cooked chicken in crescent rolls.
Place in buttered dish.
Pour cream of chicken soup and chicken broth over chicken and rolls.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Combine all ingredients into casserole dish. Top with 1/2 package of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Halfway through baking time, stir, thoroughly mixing in cheese.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter shallow 2-quart casserole.
In a large bowl, blend together soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Add mushrooms, cooked vegetables and chicken.
Mix well.
Turn into casserole dish.
Combine crumbs, thyme and butter.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until browned and bubbly. Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add remainder and bake at 350° for 1 hour in loaf or tube pan.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use a round Pyrex dish.

title: souffle(pinnik smetanoyu ta zbitimi vershkami)
directions: Beat sour cream until frothy.
Add egg yolks, flour, vanilla and sugar; beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Fold into sour cream mixture and put into a greased souffle dish. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Do not open oven during baking time.
When done, serve immediately.
Beat 1 cup egg whites with 2 tablespoons confectioners sugar until peaks form.
Serve with souffle.

title: annie mae's yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Make stiff with flour.
Punch down when doubled in size.
Allow to double again and then punch down and make into rolls.
Allow rolls to rise again.
Bake in a 350° to 375° oven until brown.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown ground beef, drain and add Ro-Tel. Simmer uncovered until liquid is gone.
Add drained beans to meat mixture.
When ready to serve, toss with remaining ingredients.

title: pina colada mocktail
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Whirl until well blended. Garnish with pineapple wedge if desired.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate kahlua cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Moist; no frosting needed, but you can make a glaze with 1/4 cup Kahlua and 1 1/4 cups powdered sugar.

title: mocha freeze pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk and chocolate syrup. Blend well.
Dissolve coffee in hot water and add to chocolate mixture.
Whip the whipping cream and fold into chocolate mixture. Pour into prepared crust.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.
Top each slice with a dollop of Cool Whip and garnish with chocolate shavings or curls.

title: zucchini lasagna(makes 8 large servings.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain noodles.
Simmer zucchini slices in tomato sauce for 10 minutes.
Brown meat and add to tomato zucchini mixture.
Place on a layer of noodles.
Add a layer of Ricotta cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with a layer of tomato mixture.
Dribble the olive oil over the top and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish the refried beans, sour cream and salsa. Layer cheese on top. Add jalapenos and banana peppers if desired. Refrigerate overnight and serve with tortilla chips for dipping.

title: stuffed hard rolls
directions: Saute beef and onions.
Turn off heat; add remaining ingredients.
Cut off tops of 8 hard rolls.
Take the inside out; add to meat mixture.
Stuff rolls.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spiced apple juice
directions: Combine all ingredients in the crock-pot to warm.
Delicious and makes the house smell great!!

title: rumaki
directions: After chicken livers are cut into halves, make a thin cut into middle of each piece.
Insert a slice of water chestnut into each cut.
Wrap each piece of chicken liver/water chestnut in a half strip of bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Place in a flat dish or storage container in one layer.

title: cashew casserole
directions: Mix sour cream and soup and fold into rice and dressing mixture.
Put nuts on top 15 minutes before done in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and bake about 35 to 60 minutes at 350° to 400°.
Done when toothpick comes out cleanly.

title: cheese bubble loaf
directions: Cover dough; let rise in warm, draft-free place until doubled. Divide in 32 pieces.
Shape each into a ball around a cube of cheese; pinch to seal.
Dip balls in butter.
Layer seam side down in greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Cover; let rise until doubled. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until top is firm and golden brown.
Remove from pan; serve warm.
No slicing, just pull apart!

title: strawberry delight
directions: Cook together milk, eggs and sugar over low heat until thick. Add vanilla and cool.
Spread half the crushed wafers in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Pour cooled milk mixture over wafers.
Layer pecans, 1 cup Cool Whip, strawberries and remaining Cool Whip.
Top with remaining wafer crumbs.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook peppers in boiling, salted water; drain.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion; drain fat.
Stir in remainder of ingredients, using only 1 cup tomato sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Lightly stuff each pepper with 1/2 cup meat mixture. Stand peppers upright in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over peppers.
Cover; bake 45 minutes. Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Will be thick and sort of dry.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add egg.
Add bananas and beat well.
Sift together baking soda, salt and flour and add to wet ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Add nuts to mixture.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn pone
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Sift together flour, corn meal and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add sour milk or buttermilk and soda.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour or until browned.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, flour and add a small amount of milk. Add egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Prebake pie crust until brown.
Pour pie filling in crust.

title: stewed okra and tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased skillet.
Cook on a low fire.
Stir slowly until tender.
Season to taste.
Cook on top of the stove 30 to 40 minutes (time varies).

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Shred head of cabbage.
Add salt and let stand for 1 hour. Add shredded carrot and green pepper.
Mix vinegar, sugar, water, mustard and celery seed.
Boil 1 minute.
Cool.
Add to cabbage mixture and freeze.
May be refrozen.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter. Press in 13 x 9 x 1-inch pan. Have eggs and butter at room temperature. Beat eggs, butter and sugar for no less than 15 minutes. Spread over crust. Slice bananas and layer over mixture. Spoon pineapple over bananas (be sure each banana is covered so it won't turn brown). Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with nuts and cherries. Refrigerate.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Cut chicken in bite size pieces and place in beaten egg. Crush crackers.
Place in plastic bag and shake chicken which has been rolled in egg. In frying pan, cook chicken on both sides (add butter to fry).
Place in baking dish.
Pour juices and mushrooms over chicken. Cut cheese in small cubes and sprinkle over mushrooms and chicken. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sliced cucumber pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers and onions together and sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 2 hours; drain.
Mix vinegar, sugar and celery seed together.
Stir until dissolved (don't heat).
Pour over sliced pickles.
Put in covered containers in refrigerator.
Ready for use in 24 hours.

title: overnight scalloped chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients (except for 1/4 cup margarine and bread crumbs) in a large bowl. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Take the remaining margarine and bread crumbs and sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: cheesecake cookies cups
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Paper line 12 muffin cup. Place one cookie dough in muffin cups. Bake 12 min. Beat cream cheese, milk, egg and vanilla in a bowl until smooth. Pour about 3 tablespoons cream cheese mixture over each cookie. Bake 15 mins. May top with pie filling and chill for 1 hr.

title: sweetish snow drops
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix well with vanilla and salt.
Roll into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: len shelby's cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients. Drop by teaspoon on a greased and floured cookie sheet.
These cookies were Len's and his friends favorite to take on hunting trips, as they keep very well.

title: beets with cream
directions: Blend salt, pepper, lemon juice, mustard and sour cream. Drain off about half of beet juice that's left to mixture and stir well.
Chill before serving.

title: watergate salad
directions: Fold dry pudding into Cool Whip. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Stir. Pour into pretty bowl.
Refrigerate until set.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown meat in oil; drain and add onion.
Cook until tender. Stir in all ingredients, except cheese. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Spoon into baking dish.
Make lattice top with cheese. Broil until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix well; chill and roll into balls about 1-inch across.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Roll cookies in powdered sugar.

title: stuffed chicken breast(with sundried tomatoes, feta, olives and pine nuts)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large ovenproof skillet cook onions in 1 tablespoon oil over moderate heat, stirring until softened.
Add garlic and cook, stirring 1 minute.
Transfer mixture to a bowl and let cool.
Stir in olives, nuts, tomatoes (pat dry, cut into small strips), cheeses, marjoram and salt and pepper, stirring until combined.
Cut chicken breasts at thick end and make a pocket and stuff with 1/4 filling.
In the skillet, heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil over moderate high heat until hot but not smoking and brown chicken, skin side down.
Leave chicken skin side down, transfer skillet to oven and bake until just cooked through, about 12 minutes.

title: brownies(double batch)
directions: Combine sugar and shortening; add eggs and mix, then add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Sift in dry ingredients and mix; add nuts.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased pan and put in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths.
Put in bowl with 1 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Shake to coat (I do one can at a time). Place in greased Bundt pan.
Melt one stick butter and stir in one cup brown sugar.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: green beans delish
directions: Cook beans according to package directions.
Mix with soup and cover with French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: sausage upside-down corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook sausage, onion and green pepper in skillet until sausage is brown and crumbly.
Stir in flour.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put water and butter in pan.
When this begins to boil, add the
sugar	and
cream
of	tartar	which
have been mixed together.
Bring to boil and as soon as this mixture starts to turn brown on
the	edges,	pour over 3 quarts of popped corn. Stir well.	Put on waxed paper to cool and break into pieces.

title: fruited cabbage slaw
directions: Combine the cabbage, apples, oranges and grapes.
Then in separate bowl, combine yogurt, mayonnaise and celery salt.
Pour over cabbage mixture in bowl; toss well.
Apply seal; refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Sprinkle with pecans if desired. Makes 20 servings.

title: milk white rice
directions: Bring rice, water, condensed milk, orange juice and cinnamon sticks to boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 14 to 17 minutes. Remove from heat and let it cool. Before serving, remove cinnamon sticks and dust the rice with cinnamon and fresh orange slices or wedges.
Yield 8 servings.

title: smoky brisket roast
directions: Sprinkle brisket with meat tenderizer, salt and pepper.
Add 4 tablespoons liquid smoke. Wrap tightly in heavy foil.
Leave overnight.
Mix all remaining seasonings. Spread over meat. Re-wrap tightly and bake
1 hour at 300°.
Loosen foil and bake at 200° for 6 hours.
Let set overnight. Slice as thin as you can across the grain. Save 1 cup of meat broth and mix 1 cup Kraft barbecue sauce.
Pour over sliced meat.
Reheat and cook 2 hours at 200°.

title: limeade
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring some water (about an inch) and a stick of cinnamon to a boil.
Remove from heat and add a tea bag. Allow to brew.
Remove tea bag.
Add small can frozen orange juice, juice of a lemon, some cloves, sugar to taste (1/4 to 1 cup) and extra water as needed.
Heat and serve (can be served immediately, but taste is richer if spices are allowed to soak awhile).
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: brownie cake
directions: Prepare pudding mix according to package directions.
Cool, stirring occasionally.
Stir in dry cake mix and blend well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces and nuts over the top.
Bake cake according to the temperature and baking time given on the cake package for a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake.
Cool completely before cutting into squares. Serves 10 to 12.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Mix flour, pecans and butter and press in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, bacon and raisins in a bowl.
Mix vinegar, salad dressing and sugar in another bowl.
Pour over broccoli mixture. Let set overnight.
Stir before serving.

title: meat and cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Add all ingredients, except cabbage.
Spray 3 quart baking dish with Pam.
Layer cabbage and meat, ending with meat on top.
Cover loosely.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread(makes 2 or 3 loaves)
directions: Beat together first 5 ingredients.
Sift together last 6 ingredients.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for one hour in greased loaf pans.

title: multi-fruit jam
directions: *Your choice (strawberries, blueberries, red raspberries, black raspberries, etc.).

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken and remove bones and skin.
Cut chicken in small pieces.
Mix soup, sour cream, chilies and cheese and then add approximately 1 cup chicken broth.
Mix 1/2 of mixture with chicken.
Spread small amount of mixture without chicken in two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Put chicken mixture in tortillas one at a time and roll and place in pan.
Spread remaining sauce over top; sprinkle with a small amount of cheese and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cut up apples as for pie into 10 x 6-inch or round baking dish.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Into last four dry ingredients, drop 1 egg and cut in with 2 knives (very important).
When crumbly, sprinkle on top of apples, and drizzle melted margarine over the crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.
Good with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix and bake for 3/4 hour at 350°.

title: corn relish macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and margarine.
Add sugar; cream well.
Add eggs. Add vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in greased tube pan with wax paper on bottom of pan.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.

title: play dough
directions: Mix ingredients together and cook in a saucepan over low heat. Stir until it reaches play dough consistency.
Cool.

title: quick chili on buns
directions: Cover and cook about 10 minutes. Serve on 8 split & toasted buns.

title: country ham
directions: Scrub ham with warm suds.
Rinse well with cold water.
Place in roaster.
Fill to top with cold water.
Soak overnight.
Drain water in morning.
Put in fresh cold water until pan is half full. Skin side should be on top.
Heat oven to 325° to 350°.
Start ham on top of stove.
When water comes to a rolling boil, put in oven. When half of cooking time is over, dip out water around ham and add same amount of fresh boiling water.
Thirty minutes before cooking time is up, take out of oven, remove skin.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Put back in oven and let brown last 30 minutes.
(Cook 20 minutes for each pound.)

title: amanda's favorite banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl cream butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in bananas, milk and vanilla. Add remaining ingredients and stir by hand just until well blended.
Pour into one 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, greased.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Or makes 24 muffins, baked for 20 minutes.
Recipe doubles easily and freezes well.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together in medium bowl.
Let set in refrigerator for one hour.
Take out and shape into ball.
Cover with nuts, if desired.

title: 14 day pickles(stone jar)
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and pickling spice.
Pour over your cucumbers.
Mix this amount of solution until you have enough to cover your cucumbers.
Heat syrup early morning for 5 days.
On fifth day can.
Do not heat cucumbers, just the solution.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend until creamy.
You can add 1/2 to a teaspoon of water or milk if you desire a frothier texture.
This tastes great with strawberries, peaches and pineapple.

title: berry yam mallow bake
directions: Combine brown sugar, cinnamon, flour and oats.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Toss 1 cup crumb mixture with yams and cranberries.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Broil until lightly browned.

title: tuna salad
directions: Pare bell pepper.
Mix thoroughly tuna, cottage cheese, onion, mushrooms and bell pepper.
Place in casserole.
Bake until brown at 345° for about 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour bean salad
directions: Mix all beans, corn and chickpeas in a large bowl. In another bowl, mix sugar, salt, water and vinegar. Put beans in a large jar or other container. Pour vinegar mixture over the beans.
Let set overnight. Will keep in refrigerator a week or more.

title: rocky road pudding parfaits
directions: Prepare pudding mix according to package directions, using milk.
Pour into bowl.
Stir in cookie pieces, marshmallows, chocolate morsels and nuts.
In each of 6 parfait glasses, layer a heaping 1/4 cup pudding with 1 tablespoon whipped topping; repeat layers.
Top with chocolate-covered graham crackers, chocolate morsels and nuts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bean salad(high in protein)
directions: *If using canned beans, rinse well to get rid of juice and starch.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter; add seasonings.
Mix into cereals and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Stir frequently while heating.

title: cheezies
directions: Coat Rice Chex with melted butter.
Sprinkle with cheese and toast in oven at 300° for 15 minutes.
Stir.

title: honey baked onions(microwave)
directions: Onions, peel and half crosswise.
Place onions cut side up in a single layer
on
large
microwave
baking dish.
Pour honey over top.
Place small
pieces of butter or margarine on each piece of onion.
Loosely cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Baste onions with pan juices.
Continue on High another 4
minutes
or
until
onions
are
tender. Remove waxed paper.
Sprinkle
with chopped parsley.
Serves 6 to 10 people.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Use the drained pineapple juice and orange juice to cover the fruit.
Add Equal and lemon juice.
Do not stir.

title: peach crumble
directions: Arrange sliced peaches in a buttered 8 x 8-inch dish. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Blend flour, brown sugar and salt together.
Cut in butter.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over peaches. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes and serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Put oil in blender.
Add and blend enough zucchini until it measure 3 cups on blender pitcher.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend. Combine dry ingredients and add to blender mixture in a bowl.
Mix in nuts.
Makes 3 small or 2 large loaves.
Grease loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes; use toothpick test.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut up apples and bananas.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add oranges (drained), pineapple, fruit cocktail and pudding and pie mix.
(If you would like to thicken, add a little orange juice. You can also put in chopped cherries, pears or peaches.) Refrigerate; it is better the second day.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cream 1/2 cup butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in chilies, corn and cheese.

title: dove a la papiot
directions: Clean birds and season with salt and pepper.
Fill cavities with onion, parsley, onion tops and bell peppers.
Cut sausage in small pieces and add this to the bird's cavities.
Wrap birds with bacon strips and bake at 375° for 60 to 65 minutes, applying sherry sparingly over birds every 15 minutes.
