title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add eggs and cheese to sausage and mix.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Punch out 1 can of biscuits to cover bottom of dish.
Spread sausage mixture over biscuits.
Spread second can of rolls out to cover sausage mixture. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Wash, seed and split open chilies.
Place on bottom of an 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Layer with Jack cheese and Cheddar cheese. Mix milk and eggs together and pour over cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Allow to cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: coffee can pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together sugar and pumpkin in large bowl. Add oil, then water mixed with eggs. Combine dry ingredients; mix well. Add pumpkin mixture. Lastly, add dates and nuts. Grease and flour 4 coffee cans. Divide batter evenly in cans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let stand a couple of minutes, then remove from cans and cool on racks.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt.
Stir in milk and nuts. Store batter in refrigerator 1 to 2 days before baking.
Roll into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: chicken baked pork chops
directions: Sprinkle both sides of pork chops with salt and pepper.
Brown slowly on both sides in oil.
Remove from skillet and place in shallow baking dish. Mix together soup, water, evaporated milk and mushrooms.
Pour liquid mixture over the pork chops.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until chops are tender.
Makes 3 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all three ingredients together.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for about 18 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: banana pudding
directions: Whip
egg yolks, sugar, flour, evaporated milk and milk together.
Cook
over
medium
heat, stirring constantly until thickened, about
minutes.
Add
vanilla.
In
a
10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch
baking
dish, layer wafers, sliced bananas and egg mixture into
two
equal
layers.
Beat egg whites with 3 teaspoons sugar
and
teaspoon
cream of tartar until stiff. Spread on
top of pudding and bake in 350° oven until meringue is lightly browned.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut wings at joints; discard tops. Combine remaining ingredients in a small saucepan.
Mix to blend and simmer 5 minutes.
Dip chicken in and bake about 1 1/2 to 2 hours, basting with remaining sauce, turning chicken.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cut slice from top of bread loaf.
Remove center, leaving 1-inch shell.
Cut removed bread into bite-size pieces.
Saute celery and onions in margarine until tender.
Add cheese, stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients, heat thoroughly, stirring constantly.
Spoon into bread loaf.
Serve with vegetable dippers and bread.

title: beef and potato moussaka
directions: Grease baking dish.
Slice potatoes 1/8-inch thick.
Cover bottom of casserole with potatoes.
In a skillet, heat olive oil. Add onion, garlic and meat until it loses red color.
Add tomato sauce, cinnamon, mint, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour meat mixture over potatoes.
Slice rest of potatoes for topping.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour and milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring often.
Stir in beaten eggs and then Parmesan cheese.
Pour over casserole.
Bake until potatoes are done.
(Bake 1 hour at 375°.)

title: divinity
directions: Stir until sugar is dissolved then cook without stirring to 252 degrees or hard ball stage.
Remove from heat and pour, beating constantly into egg whites.
Continue beating until mixture holds its' shape and loses its' gloss.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop quickly onto waxed paper or spread on greased pan. Yield 1 1/4 pounds.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: Combine caramels, water and butter in 1-quart casserole.
Heat in Radarange oven on Cookmatic level 8 for 4 to 5 minutes or until melted.
Stir halfway through heating.

title: hamburger rice hot dinner
directions: In skillet, brown meat; drain.
Add all ingredients
and stir. Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Cover and bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: party punch
directions: Puree frozen strawberries in blender.
Add all ingredients and mix.
Do not add water.

title: hot rolls("quick and easy.  oh, so good.")
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups of warm water.
Cream sugar and melted butter.
Add yeast to creamed mixture.
Add flour and egg.
Stir until well mixed.
(Will look like cake batter.)
Place in refrigerator, in an airtight container, overnight before using.

title: fruit smoothy
directions: Blend all ingredients except cinnamon, vanilla, honey and ice. When well blended, add remaining ingredients.
Enjoy.

title: rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening and egg.
Add cinnamon and salt to flour. Sift. Add soda to milk.
Alternate liquid and dry.
Add fruit and mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: frozen lemonade pie
directions: Fold milk and lemonade into whipped topping.
Spoon into crusts.
Freeze until firm.

title: dressing
directions: Blend celery,
onions,	eggs
and
milk in blender.
In large bowl,
combine all ingredients.
Mix well, using chicken broth to make
juicy.
Pam
spray
a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: low-fat french silk pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk; set aside to become firm.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Make a batter with the flour, sugar, milk and baking powder.
Spoon batter over the butter. Pour fruit filling over batter and spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hurry pie
directions: In mixing bowl combine Eagle Brand milk, pineapple and lemon juice.
Blend together and fold in Cool Whip last.
Chill for at least 30 minutes.

title: tostada casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain off grease.
Add 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Line bottom of flat casserole dish with 2 cups corn chips, crushed.
Crush remaining chips; set aside.
Spoon meat mixture over chips.
Combine remaining tomato sauce with beans; spread over meat.
Add seasonings.
Bake, covered, for 25 minutes.
Remove and add crushed chips and shredded cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Bake at 375°.

title: chili dog pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine Bisquick, mustard and water in small mixing bowl; stir until dough forms.
Press dough into bottom and sides of pan.
Chop hot dogs into bite size pieces and place on dough.
Spoon chili over hot dogs.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8. Top with your favorite condiments, like mustard, catsup, sauerkraut and onions.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in bottom of pan.
Mix the rest of the ingredients; pour over the first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cut or shred seafood.
Mix with celery, mayonnaise, eggs, onion, juice and mustard.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs or Ritz crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange crunch chicken
directions: In a shallow bowl mix honey, Worcestershire sauce, seasoned salt, ginger, paprika, oil and orange juice.
Add chicken pieces and marinate 2 hours at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first three (3) ingredients in a bowl - refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Shape mixture into balls and roll in chopped nuts, coating throughly.
Serve with crackers.
Yields 2-1/2 cups.

title: apple fritters
directions: Beat egg and milk.
Beat in flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add apples.
In hot oil, drop a teaspoonful of mixture, until brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together. Add all other ingredients. This is a stiff dough. Bake in Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients with a fork; then add the rest. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sue's cinnamon pie
directions: Scald milk and add all other ingredients.
Cook slowly until mixture bubbles and thickens.
Add vanilla.

title: danish cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla and mix. Gradually add flour.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° to 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: In a large bowl, stir flour, soda and salt.
Add remaining ingredients (except candy Kisses) and mix at medium speed until well combined.
Chill dough 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°. Roll small amount of dough into 1-inch ball.
Dip into sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet, sugar side up.
Bake 10 minutes. Remove and place Kiss in center.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: onion soup gratinee
directions: Thinly slice onions.
Lightly brown onion in half butter and half oil.
Slowly add white wine, immersing onions using medium heat.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Add veal stock (or your favorite brown stock).
Add fresh ground pepper, salt, ground thyme and nutmeg to taste.
Cook liquid until reduced by 1/3.
Pour soup into ovenproof bowls; place generous slice of browned French bread on top of each bowl.
Top with a generous handful of Parmesan cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese bubbles and partially browns.
Serve immediately.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Add butter, bouillon, onion, salt and pepper.
Add well beaten egg and mix.
Add sour cream.
Pour into greased 1-quart baking dish.
Make topping of crumbs, cheese and paprika.
Sprinkle over top of squash.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage or green beans with paprika gravy
directions: Boil cabbage, cut in quarters or green beans.
Add onion and clove of garlic.
Cover with water and salt to taste.
When cooked, make a gravy by browning flour in shortening.
Add paprika and juice from cabbage or beans.
Cook until thick.
Pour gravy over cabbage or beans and serve.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients well and bake at 350° until cake tests done.
Bake in Bundt pan or tube pan about 50 minutes.
Cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion. Add salt. Drain.
Mix Pepperidge Farm dressing with stick of butter.
Put half in bottom of casserole. Mix squash, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour over Pepperidge Farm dressing. Top with rest of dressing.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Mix tomato juice and water.
Add to rest of mixture and bake 5 hours at 250°.

title: decorator's icing
directions: Cream shortening.
Add small amount of sifted sugar and gradually add water (do this alternately until all is used).
Add extract and beat.
Cover until ready to use.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, margarine and milk to a boil for 7 minutes.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Mix thoroughly and pour into a dish that has been greased.
For convenience, use a hand mixer to mix.

title: mozzarella meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly mix together meat, bread crumbs, eggs and seasonings.
Place on waxed paper.
Shape into 10 x 14-inch rectangle.
Layer cheese over meat.

title: homemade salami
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Shape like salami in two sheets of aluminum foil.
Wrap and refrigerate for 24 hours. Place on baking sheet.
Bake for 60 minutes at 350°.
When done, prick with fork to drain excess grease.
Rewrap in new foil. Refrigerate.

title: golden brownies
directions: Mix well and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: fudge candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk, Karo and cocoa.
Boil 7 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Remove from heat and beat until firm.
Pour into greased platter.
Cut when barely warm; remove from platter. Store, covered.

title: cherry wine cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat well.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when removed from pan.

title: russian honey cake
directions: Bring honey to a boil and then cool it.
Cream butter with sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in honey.
Sift flour with dry ingredients twice; add alternately with sour cream.
Stir in nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Spoon into buttered tube pan. Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: chicken in a skillet
directions: Melt butter and shortening in a frying pan.
Roll chicken in flour and brown.
Remove extra fat from pan.
Mix chicken soup, celery, Pet milk and poultry seasoning; blend well.
Pour over chicken.
Cut carrots in half lengthwise.
Partially cook carrots and onions in salt water.
Place vegetables around chicken and heat to a boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer until chicken and vegetables are tender (35 to 45 minutes).

title: muffin meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cups of muffin pan.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon mixture into greased muffin cups. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool slightly before removing from muffin cups.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a deep dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together; pour over margarine.
Pour fruit over batter.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: basic cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in flour, salt and vanilla.
Spoon into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done. Yield:
16 servings.

title: crisp sugar cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Then work in shortening with hands as in pie dough.
Add eggs, soda and water, vanilla and milk, mixing well.
Roll out and top with sugar.
These roll out easily without rolling in extra flour.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into individual serving pieces.
Brown in butter in a frying pan.
Place ribs and onion in slow cooker.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour sauce over ribs.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours (high for 4 to 6 hours).
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: In double boiler, melt 6 candy bars in the milk.
Let cool. Add eggs, sugar and evaporated milk to the candy bar mixture until well blended.
Cut remaining 2 bars into small pieces and add to mixture.
Pour into 1 gallon container to 1 1/2-inches off full line with homogenized milk.
Put into freezer.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Bake hen at 350° for approximately 2 hours.
Mix broth and flour.
Roll thin and cut into strips.
Boil remaining broth in large pot.
Drop strips in, a few at a time.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: lo mein
directions: Boil vermicelli according to package directions.
Drain well and toss with sesame oil. Set aside and keep warm.

title: hoosier sugar cream pie
directions: Prepare baked pie shell.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar, cream, food coloring and salt in saucepan.
Cook to the boiling point.
Mix remaining sugar and cornstarch in another pan.
Add boiling mixture gradually to pan mixture.
Add vanilla and butter.
Return to heat; cook until thick.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg and a few extra pieces of butter.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes, until firm and lightly brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: weight watchers meat loaf
directions: Put in an ungreased bread tin.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 2 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Stir in soda, then stir in peanuts.
Place corn on a very large shallow pan.
Pour sugar mixture over corn.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: In a medium bowl cream sugar, butter and shortening.
In a small bowl beat eggs.
In a large bowl mix flour, salt, baking powder and eggs, sugar mixture, milk and flavorings.
Blend well and pour into well greased pan.
Bake one to one in a half hours at 350°.

title: coconut crumb cherry pie
directions: Bake pie shell at 450° for 5 minutes.
Bring pie filling just to a boil in saucepan.
Pour into warm pie shell.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: METHOD:
Wash chicken well and dry off.
Cut up.
Sprinkle seasonings on pieces.
Coat with flour.

title: butterscotch oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 350°
for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: company potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns for 30 minutes.
Mix them with the sour cream, soup, cheese, onion flakes and 1/4 cup butter.
Spread this into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt remaining butter and mix with the crushed corn flakes.
Spread over the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: betty h's chocolate cake
directions: Cook chocolate pudding.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Combine with dry German chocolate cake mix.
Mix by hand.
Pour into lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
It will be thick.
Leave it a little lumpy in the pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top with nuts.
Cool completely, then put powdered sugar in strainer to decorate.

title: punch
directions: Stir together pineapple, orange juice, Kool-Aid and water. Freeze.
Thaw 2 hours before serving.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until well combined. Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Freezes well, too.
Can take from freezer to microwave for quick breakfasts or snacks.

title: biscuits for 12
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in shortening.
Stir in milk and yeast.
Mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
(Can leave overnight in refrigerator.)
Roll out and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Can freeze leftovers for later use.

title: grandma's baked beans
directions: In a skillet, brown your ground round and onion until brown. Drain and put aside.
Then brown your bacon.
Drain all fat. Combine meat, onion and all other ingredients and put into a crock-pot or large pot.
Stir occasionally.

title: "serbian" green beans
directions: Heat beans thoroughly and drain well.
Melt butter and saute onion.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Mix with beans and heat thoroughly. Add sour cream if desired.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in two pans; crumble one in bottom of punch bowl and add 1/2 vanilla pudding, 1/2 pineapple, 1/2 strawberries, 1/2 Cool Whip and pecans.
Repeat, ending with pecans.

title: microwave peanut patties
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a 2-quart glass bowl and microwave for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts.
Microwave 12 minutes. Remove and add remainder of ingredients.
Cool and stir until creamy.
Drop by tablespoons on a sheet of wax paper.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Core and dice apples.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine with nuts, celery and raisins.
Stir in mayonnaise only until blended.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Add all beans to crock-pot. Pour in meat, brown sugar and catsup.
Simmer for 3 to 4 hours.

title: orange cookies
directions: Mix dry oats with cake mix.
Beat eggs and oil together well and add to oats and cake mix.
Mix well and refrigerate for about 15 minutes.
Roll into balls about the size of a walnut, crisscross with fork, sprinkle lightly with sugar and bake for 8 minutes at 350°.

title: black beans
directions: Prepare beans as directed on package.
Add all the seasonings during cooking.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Defrost broccoli and drain.
Process in bender or Cuisinart. Saute onions in skillet with butter flavor Pam.
Add tomatoes and peppers.
Stir in rest of ingredients.

title: brownies for the crowd
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix all the ingredients except the walnuts.
Stir in the nuts.
Pour into a greased and lightly floured 11 x 15 inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.
Serves 24.

title: chocolate molasses caramels
directions: Melt butter; add cream, sugar and molasses.
Bring to a boiling point.
Add chocolate; continue boiling and stir occasionally until a firm ball is formed when putting a drop of the liquid in cold water.
Add vanilla; turn into buttered pan, having mixture 1 or 2 inches deep.
When nearly cold, cut into cubes and wrap individually in wax paper and let stand in refrigerator to harden.

title: deer stew
directions: Cook meat, basil and Italian seasoning until tender.
Add remaining ingredients but salt.
Cook until tender.
Add your salt now to taste.
Very good.

title: perfect spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add rice and onion; cook on low heat until onion is opaque.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer about 1 hour.

title: creamed ham and cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage until tender.
Melt fat; blend in flour.
Stir in milk slowly and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add cabbage and ham to white sauce and heat through.
Mix crumbs and melted butter; heat until brown.
Sprinkle on top of ham mixture just before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easter basket cake
directions: Frost cake entirely.
Cut cookies in half and stand cookie halves around edge of cake by pressing into frosting.
Frost cookie halves.

title: candied pretzel wreaths
directions: Melt almond bark in top of double boiler and dip 5 pretzels. Remove and place on cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Arrange coated pretzels-twisted edge out in a circle with sides joined to form bottom layer of wreath.
Coat 5 more pretzels and repeat to make second layer of wreath on top of first.
Let harden.
(To make 10 pretzel wreaths, repeat entire process.)
Transfer wreaths to wire racks.
Spread remaining almond bark over wreaths for thicker coating.
Let harden.
Melt chocolate and drizzle over wreaths.
When hardened, garnish with cinnamon candies and cherries.

title: homestyle frittata
directions: In medium saucepan, combine potatoes and enough water to cover.
Over medium-high heat, bring to a boil.
Boil about 15 minutes or until tender; drain.
Cool slightly; cut into large cubes and set aside.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream cheese, peanut butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add Cool Whip and blend just enough to mix well.
Place in a 9-inch graham crust.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Real good!

title: good tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill completely.
Serve with soft shelled or deviled crab and fish.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well.
Tastes best with strawberries, apples, bananas and pears.
Can use other fruits.

title: cheese soup
directions: Heat water with bouillon cubes.
Add potatoes and onions. Cook about 20 minutes.
Add vegetables and cook another 15 minutes.
Add soup and cheese.
Keep stirring on a lower heat until heated through and cheese is completely melted.
This can be done in a crock-pot with occasional stirring.

title: mississippi caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: debbie's lasagna
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Preheat oven to 400°.
In one bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, shredded Mozzarella cheese and eggs. In second bowl, combine cooked ground beef and tomato sauce mixture.
Place 1 layer of noodles followed by 1 layer of cheese mixture.
Continue alternating sauce, noodles and then cheese. Make top layer sauce mixture.
Noodles must be thoroughly covered by sauce.
On last sauce layer, place one layer of sliced Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 1 hour and let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: molded waldorf salad
directions: In 4 quart saucepan, stir sugar and gelatin.
Stir in 2 cups white grape
juice.
Cook
over
medium
heat,
stirring frequently, until
gelatin	is
completely	dissolved.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Stir in remaining grape juice.
Refrigerate until mixture
mounds
when dropped from a spoon, about 45 minutes.
Meanwhile, chop
celery;	cut
each
grape
in half. When gelatin
mixture
almost
comes
to mounding consistency, quickly shred apples.
(Apples will turn brown if shredded too early.) Fold celery,
grapes and apples into thickened gelatin mixture;
pour into
10-inch
Bundt pan or 10 cup mold.
Cover and refrigerate until set, about 3 hours.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix together cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Spread in bottom of large baking dish.
Cover this with 1/3 box cake mix, sifted.
Cut margarine real thin and place over mixture.
Spread pecans over top.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour, or until bubbly.

title: teresa's hamburger dish
directions: Cook hamburger in electric skillet until browned; add onion salt, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Mix well.
Cover meat with cheese.
Add noodles, tomatoes and water.
Spread tomato sauce over mixture. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer at 325° for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Use 2 teaspoons in each cup of boiling water. More or less of mix if tasty is desired.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: six-weeks muffins
directions: Pour the boiling water over 2 cups of bran and let stand while assembling other ingredients.
Mix in shortening.
Mix remainder of bran with sugar, eggs and buttermilk.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Combine all ingredients and bake as needed at 400° for 20 minutes.
Mixture will keep 6 weeks or more in the refrigerator.

title: toots' fish chowder
directions: Cover the celery, carrots and onions with water; add salt and pepper.
Boil for 7 minutes.
Add diced potatoes; cook 7 minutes. Add fish; cook 3 or 4 minutes (do not overcook).
Add butter and milk; heat.
This is great for camping.

title: eight layered salad
directions: Make layers with lettuce, pepper, onion, eggs, cheese, bacon bits and peas.
Continue to make layers until amount wanted.

title: porcupine meat dish
directions: Mix hamburg, rice and onion together. Form balls. Add salt and pepper.
Place in a large pan.
Pour tomato soup mixed with water over the balls. Cook slowly for 2 hours.
When done, rice will be sticking out of the balls looking like a porcupine.

title: easy chocolate shakes
directions: In a blender, combine milk, pudding mix and mint or rum extract, if desired. Cover and blend until smooth. Add ice cubes; cover and blend until combined. Let stand 3 minutes to thicken slightly. Makes 5 (8 ounce) servings.

title: fruit pie
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well. Add vanilla and milk.
Mix, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 325° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Set oven to 375°, moderately hot.
In a bowl, combine shortening, salt, sugar and instant dry milk; add boiling water and stir until shortening melts.
Cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water according to package directions.
Stir into cooled first mixture.
Stir in eggs, beaten to a froth.
Stir in about 1 cup flour and blend thoroughly.
Add remaining flour and beat vigorously until batter is smooth.
Cover with a damp cloth and let rise until double in bulk (about 1 hour).
Cut down dough and mix again until very smooth.
Shape in muffin tins.
Let rise about 50 minutes.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen medium-size rolls.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie crust (precooked or crumb crust).
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Mix all ingredients except noodles and cheese.
Layer noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer chicken mixture on top of the noodles. Add another layer of noodles and another layer of chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot punch
directions: Heat, simmer and strain.

title: taco soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer on low heat for 2 hours. Top each individual bowl with grated Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese (combined) and crushed or whole corn chips.

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and spices in large bowl.
Beat eggs in another bowl.
Mix in the shortening, water, buttermilk and pumpkin with eggs.
Add flour mixture and blend well.
Heat a pan and coat with shortening.
Drop a spoonful of batter on pan.
Turn after small bubbles appear.
Remove when golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Cook and peel potatoes; allow to cool. Slice and place in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray. In a small saucepan, combine remaining ingredients; bring to a boil, stirring frequently. Pour over the potatoes. Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes, basting occasionally. Yield: 10 servings.

title: banana split cake(prepare the night before serving)
directions: Combine graham crackers, margarine and sugar.
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream together cream cheese, confectioners sugar and margarine.
Spread over graham layer. Slice bananas and place over cream cheese.
Place crushed pineapple on top of bananas, then top with Cool Whip.
If desired, top with cherries or nuts and shredded coconut.
Set overnight.

title: english toffee
directions: Have ready a large buttered cookie sheet.
Combine all ingredients, except chocolate and pecans in a large buttered saucepan.
Cook over medium-high heat until mixture changes to a deep caramel color.
Pour immediately onto prepared sheet and spread as thinly as possible.
Place chocolate on top and spread over top of candy as chocolate melts. Sprinkle pecans over top and press into chocolate with spatula while chocolate is still warm. Cool.
Break into pieces of desired size.
Never fail candy!

title: chocolate icing
directions: Cream shortening and 1 cup of sugar.
Melt chocolate over hot water and add along with vanilla and salt.
Add remaining sugar alternately with milk, until of spreading consistency.
Beat well after each addition until smooth.

title: deer stew
directions: Cut deer into slices and put into kettle; brown on both sides, then take off heat.
Put potatoes and carrots into kettle with water and cook for an hour and a half or until potatoes are cooked and water is boiling.

title: r. s. meat loaf
directions: Beat meat.
Put into bowl.
Mix all of the ingredients, except bacon and tomato sauce, with meat.
Put in loaf pan.
Cover with 2 strips of bacon.
Pour over all the tomato sauce.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Feeds 6 people.

title: lorraine's cucumber sandwiches
directions: Go down sides of cucumbers with fork.
Slice and place in quart jar.
Add sugar, salt and vinegar.
Fill with water and refrigerate for at least 24 hours.

title: swedish cabbage
directions: Cut up cabbage and apples and cook 15 to 20 minutes in water until tender.
Melt butter; add vinegar, sugar and seasonings. Heat 5 minutes.
Pour water off cabbage and then pour the sauce on cabbage.
Heat and serve.

title: raisin walnut honey bars
directions: Mix butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add honey, eggs and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients and mix in thoroughly.
Add raisins and nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: With electric mixer, thoroughly mix all ingredients except oil. Very slowly add oil a few drops at a time until dressing begins to thicken.
When thickens, may add a Tbsp. at a time.
Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.
If dressing separates, stir well.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onions. Add garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Mix in refried beans and cheese soup. Add velveeta cheese and cook over low heat until melted. Serve with tortilla or Dorito chips.

title: orange dip
directions: Mix and serve with sliced fruit dippers.

title: grandma fuller cookies
directions: Cream together white sugar, brown sugar and margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon out onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, so they will be chewy.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: quick and easy low-fat pasta salad
directions: Prepare rainbow rotini pasta according to package directions; drain and rinse.
Cook frozen peas according to package directions.
Steam broccoli.
Add peas, broccoli and kidney beans to rainbow rotini pasta.
Mix Bernstein's Cheese Fantastico salad dressing to taste to pasta salad.
Chill 15 minutes and serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook frozen green beans in salted water; drain.
(If using canned beans, omit salt.)

title: date nut bread
directions: Sprinkle soda over dates.
Pour boiling water over; let cool. Cream shortening; add sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Then add flour and date mixture alternately.
Last add nuts and vanilla. Grease five No. 2 cans.
Fill about half full.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit salad(oriental variation)
directions: In a bowl, combine all canned fruits, chill. Just before serving add condensed milk and slightly whipped cream (whip till soft peaks form). Stir gently into fruits.

title: holiday fruitcake
directions: Butter pan and line with waxed paper and butter again.
Sift flour and soda.
Combine eggs, mincemeat, condensed milk, fruit and nuts.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cut out core of tomatoes and cut in chunks.
Put in dishpan. Combine ingredients.
Cook for 15 minutes, or until cooked up good. Remove from stove.
Run through blender.
Run through colander and remove seeds and chunks; set aside.
Put juice back on stove.
Add mixture, stirring constantly (sticks easily).
Get hot and put in jars.
Pressure 10 minutes at 5 pounds pressure.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: farmers breakfast
directions: Melt butter in frying pan over medium heat.
Saute the vegetables and ham and seasonings for 3 minutes.
Cover and cook over low heat about 20 minutes.
Pour beaten eggs over the vegetables.
Do not stir.
Cover and cook until eggs are set, about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with the cheese and heat only until cheese melts.
Cut into pie shaped wedges and serve.
Serves 4.

title: spiced apple bread
directions: *Note:
You can exchange the apples for peeled carrots, bananas or unpeeled zucchini.

title: suet pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a greased mold with cover or 1 pound coffee can, two-thirds full and covered with foil.
Tie foil on with string.
Steam 3 hours.

title: orange delight cake
directions: Beat cake mix, Mandarin oranges, butter, eggs and oil and pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: blond brownies
directions: In large saucepan melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in first three ingredients and add chocolate pieces.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: morning mix-up
directions: Place hash browns, ham and onion in skillet.
Brown in oil for 10 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Beat eggs and add to skillet.
Stir occasionally until eggs are set.
Remove from heat and gently stir in cheese.
Spoon onto a serving platter, sprinkle with chives.
A great "make ahead" breakfast.

title: cheesecake brownies
directions: Mix together cake mix, egg and margarine.
Mash into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Make your topping by beating 3 eggs, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour bean salad
directions: Drain beans; wash kidney beans.
Put in large bowl celery, peppers, pimentos and onion.
Mix well.
Add all other kinds of beans.
Mix together.
Combine oil, vinegar and sugar in pan. Bring to a boil.
Set aside and cool.
When cool, pour over bean mix.
Refrigerate overnight.
(You can pour over while still warm if in a hurry.)

title: country apple cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and pour into baking dish (I spray with Pam).
Pat to cover bottom of dish.
Pour in apple pie filling.
Spread over cake mixture.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Pour over mixture.
Mix sour cream, 1 egg and vanilla.
Drizzle over cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Have all cheese at room temperature (not too warm).
Mix with mixer, all but onion.
Add onion and form a ball (can roll in chopped pecans or just put in a dish and refrigerate overnight). Serve on crackers.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Boil dressing ingredients until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Drain vegetables and mix with dressing in large bowl.
Add onions and green pepper.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Stir occasionally. Lasts a week.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over all.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Prepare white cake mix as to directions.
Pour batter into 15 x 9-inch jelly roll pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° about 20 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven.
Poke holes in cake with fork.
Mix cream of coconut and condensed milk, pour over warm cake.
Spread on pineapple.
Let cool completely. Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle on coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken luncheon dish
directions: Mix together and place in greased dish (9 x 13-inch or 11 x 14-inch).
Serves 12 plus.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix nucoa and flour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and press down.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes, cool.

title: barbecue chicken in foil
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
This is enough sauce to use on approximately 4 to 5 pounds of chicken pieces.
Soak pieces in the sauce at least 1 hour.
Brown chicken over hot barbecue coals or in range broiler for about 15 minutes.
Wrap pieces in aluminum foil, adding 2 tablespoons of sauce for each piece.
Let cook over coals or in oven at 450° for approximately 45 minutes until tender.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, milk, and vanilla mixing well.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda together.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture blending well. May add chocolate chips, nuts,etc.
as desired.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5-6 dozen.

title: chicken tetrazzini(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cook chicken on top of stove in 1-quart of water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
In small saucepan, melt butter.
Saute vegetables and garlic 5 to 7 minutes.
Cook spaghetti as package directs and drain.
When chicken is done, remove from water and boil stock until it equals 2 cups.
Add soup, vegetables and cheese to broth.
Cut chicken into small pieces and mix in 9 x 13-inch pan with spaghetti and broth mixture.
Cover with the cream and top with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until browned slightly on top.

title: libby woodley's orange ice
directions: Cook the sugar and water until the sugar is dissolved.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into shallow pans or trays and cover with wax paper or aluminum foil and put into the freezer. When partially thawed, this makes a refreshing dessert or snack on a hot day.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine for 1 minute.
Take off fire and add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Stir and dip out by teaspoonfuls, put on wax paper.
Let sit until firm, approximately 10 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Heavily grease and flour a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan or two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.

title: mexicorn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Place cheese on top (completely cover).
Cook in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until cheese is melted and somewhat bubbly.

title: crumbly apple pie
directions: Mix white sugar, cinnamon, salt and apple slices in mixing bowl; arrange in pie shell.
Blend brown sugar and flour; cut in butter or margarine with pastry blender until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° on bottom rack for 35 minutes.
Serve plain or with cream, whipped cream or cheese.
Yields 6 servings.

title: macaroni pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat the eggs well.
Add the cottage cheese, grated cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Now, gently toss the elbow macaroni into the mixture.
Generously grease an 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Add the macaroni mixture.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: quick chili loaf(300 calories per serving)
directions: About 45 minutes before serving:
Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium baking pan, mix all ingredients.
Shape into 4 loaves. Bake for 30 minutes, or until meat is done as you like it.
Makes 4 servings.

title: divinity candy
directions: Bring sugar, Karo and water to a boil.
Boil until hard ball forms when dropped in a cup of cold water.
Pour over beaten egg whites.
Beat with mixer until thick.
Add nuts and drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.
Top with cherries.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt in bowl.
Put milk in skillet over medium heat.
Add dry ingredients and cook until it thickens. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter.
Serve over hot, buttered biscuits.

title: judy's spicy spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti al dente.
Mix sauce, salt, garlic and red pepper.
"Nuke" on High for about 1 1/2 minutes.
Combine all ingredients; mix together.

title: goulash
directions: Cook beef and onions in hot fat until onions are soft and yellow.
Lightly stir in flour, salt and paprika.
Cook 5 minutes and add bouillon, tomato sauce, peeled tomatoes, garlic and bouquet.
Heat to boiling; cover.
Bake at 350° for 90 minutes. Serve over hot noodles or macaroni.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer in order.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 35 minutes.

title: choc-butterscotch bars
directions: Combine crumbs and butter. Stir well and press into a 9-inch baking pan.
Layer chocolate morsels, butterscotch morsels, coconut and pecans over crumb mixture. Pour milk evenly over top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water over medium heat until raisins are plump (about 15 minutes).
Drain raisins, reserving the liquid. Add enough water to reserved liquid to measure 1/2 cup.
Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir in reserved liquid.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
(If using self-rising flour, omit soda, salt and baking powder.)

title: italian scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Mash with fork so the tomatoes break apart.
Put a layer of potatoes in buttered large decorative casserole.
Cover with a few spoonfuls of tomato mixture.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used and casserole is full. Sprinkle lightly with bread crumbs and Parmesan. Bake, covered, in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover and cook until potatoes are tender.
Makes 12 servings.

title: quick chicken divan
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Arrange in 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Blend soup, mushrooms and chicken.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 450° or until bubbly hot.

title: portuguese potato casserole
directions: Cube cooked potatoes; do not peel.
Cube cheese and mix well with potatoes in large casserole dish.
Add onions, pimento and parsley.
Top with bread cubes.
Pour melted butter over this. Season with paprika and onion salt.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: hershey syrup cake
directions: Beat eggs and vanilla.

title: homemade tomato sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil until soft.
Add garlic and saute briefly. Add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, on low heat for 35 to 45 minutes, until done.

title: sugar puffs
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, milk and eggs.
Drop in hot oil by 1/2 teaspoonfuls.
Drain on paper towels.
May coat with confectioners sugar.

title: cottage cheese rice roast
directions: Mix.
Bake in greased dish for 50 minutes at 400°.

title: mapley chocolate brownies
directions: Beat eggs in small mixing bowl; gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Blend in melted butter; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Add cocoa to batter.
Bake in 8-inch square pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Makes 16 squares.

title: never-fail pork chop casserole
directions: Put rice in bottom of 2-quart greased casserole.
In frypan, brown the chops and then put them on the rice.
Don't wash pan yet.

Lay tomato, onion and green pepper slices on the pork chops. Open the bouillon can or put the bouillon cube into the frypan with 10 ounces water and simmer to make bouillon with drippings. Put a pinch of thyme, marjoram, salt and pepper on the chops.
At this point you can refrigerate the casserole and bouillon until ready to bake.
At baking time, pour bouillon on chops, cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Place refrigerated drippings in a 10 to 12 inch iron skillet to melt in oven and heat pan. Brown ground beef in separate skillet,drain fat and crumble beef. Chop onion and grate cheese. Seed and mince peppers. Make batter by combining corn meal, salt, soda, milk, corn and minced peppers. Mix well. Add bacon drippings. Make sure iron skillet is coated well on bottom and sides. Sprinkle more corn meal lightly on bottom of skillet. Pour in 1/2 of batter. Sprinkle beef, onion and grated cheese in layers to cover batter. Pour remaining batter over to cover. Bake for 1 hour at 375°. Cut into wedges and serve. Freezes well. Flavors blend well in refrigerator and freezer and reheats deliciously.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together and sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with rye bread or crackers.

title: grandma dawson's vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown the hamburger (ground beef).
Add the water; cover and bring to a full rolling boil.
Add vegetables and bring to a boil again.
Add rice or barley and salt and pepper.
Cook 1 1/2 hours. Serves 10 to 12.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Beat egg well.
Blend in sugar, molasses and melted shortening. Sift flour, soda, salt and spices together and add to first mixture.
Chill for an hour or more.
Roll dough about 1/4 inch thick on a lightly floured board.
Cut out.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain well.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish: Doritos, ground meat and cheese mixture (layer to the top of casserole dish).
In bowl, combine soup and chilies, pour over layers using a spoon to let soup mixture go into layers. Top with leftover cheese.
Bake at 400° until bubbling hot.

title: rochester relish
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions and celery coarsely; add salt and allow to stand overnight.
Drain.
Heat vinegar to boiling.
Add sugar, mustard and spices (do not put spices in bag).
Add chopped vegetables to boiling vinegar.
Stir until well blended.
Simmer briskly for 1/2 hour.
Pour into quarts or pints and seal.
This does not say how many this makes.

title: fastest ever biscuits
directions: Measure dry ingredients into medium sized bowl.
Measure milk and oil in measuring cup.
Pour into dry ingredients and stir with a fork until well mixed.
Knead in the bowl 4 or 5 times (do not overknead!).
Pat into a rectangle on ungreased baking sheet.
Cut into 9 or 12 squares.
Do not separate if you want softer biscuits.
Separate for crustier biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine pudding mix, sour cream, and enough juice concentrate to make a good dipping consistency.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Makes just over 2 cups.

title: old time christmas salad (slaw)
directions: Grate cabbage on coarse side of grater.
Drain peas and beans thoroughly.
Mix cabbage, peas and beans together and add 7 tablespoons of horseradish (or more to taste) and mayonnaise. Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Will keep for several days.
Garnish with olives or sliced pimentos.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo and Crisco.
Add sugar and egg yolks.
Add buttermilk and flour alternately.
Add nuts and coconut.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: no bake date balls
directions: Bring
to
a boil over medium heat dates, margarine and sugar. Boil for 2 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat; add
2 well beaten eggs.
Return to heat for 2 minutes longer. Remove from heat; add nuts, vanilla, salt, then Rice Krispies. Cool until
cool
enough
to handle.
Roll into 1-inch balls, then roll in coconut.
Refrigerate in warm weather.

title: ta's chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onion and add flour.
Add milk to make a white sauce.
Add broth and spices.
Add chicken and parsley. Simmer until thickened.
Pour over pastry or toast cups to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli by package directions.
Beat eggs.
Stir in mayonnaise, soup and onion.
Drain broccoli and stir into egg mixture.
Mix well and pour into casserole dish.
Top with crushed crackers, then shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel pecan cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
In heavy saucepan, melt caramels with milk over low heat, stirring frequently, until smooth.
Pour over crust.
Top with pecans.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Blend in chocolate; pour over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Loosen cake from rim of pan; cool before removing rim of pan. Chill.
Garnish with whipped cream and additional finely chopped pecans.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: my boursin
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with crackers.

title: hudson's strawberry and sour cream salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Fold in strawberries, bananas and pineapple.
Pour half of mixture into jello mold or square pan.
Chill until it starts to jell.
Spread sour cream over the chilled jello.
Pour remaining jello over the sour cream layer.
Chill until firm.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Beat with an electric mixer until smooth.
Pour into two large greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for one hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
This recipe also makes great muffins!

title: (the barn) broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onions in butter 3 minutes. Add water and bouillon cubes. Bring to a boil and cook until noodles are done. Add cooked broccoli. Reduce heat. Add milk and cheese chunks.
Stir until melted and season with pepper.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: western macaroni
directions: Prepare dinner as directed. Brown meat, pepper and onion. Cook until tender.
Stir in corn, tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Add dinner.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: texas millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in water in top of double boiler.
Add nuts and stir.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: chicken liver and mushrooms
directions: Place bacon and
onions in a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Microwave on High
until
bacon is crisp and onions are tender, about 3 or
minutes.
Stir
in
remaining
ingredients, then microwave on High
until chicken livers are firm and tender and sauce is thickened,
about
to 22 minutes, stirring once or twice.
This can be served over rice or noodles.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Blend all together and make into balls.
Boil cabbage in boiling water, then drain.
Wrap balls into cabbage and place into deep pan with lid.
Pour can of tomato juice over them.
Add sauerkraut.
Bake until juice thickens.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours.

title: linda's lasagna
directions: Brown beef in drippings; drain.
Add onions and garlic; cook until tender.
Add tomatoes, paste, salt, pepper, basil, oregano and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf. Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender; drain.
Arrange in a greased baking dish.
Pour half of meat sauce over noodles. Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crustless crab quiche
directions: In medium skillet, saute mushrooms in butter until tender. Remove mushrooms with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels. In a blender or food processor, blend eggs, sour cream, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, flour, onion powder, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Fold in mushrooms, Jack cheese and crabmeat.

title: venison salami
directions: Mix all ingredients; cover and refrigerate for 2 days.
Divide meat into 2 equal parts and roll in nylon net or make muslin bags and stuff.
Bake in slow oven (225°) for 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Cool.
Remove netting.
Freezes well.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the lukewarm water and let set.
Mix in the order given all together and put in warm place; let rise.
Make rolls, tea rings or cinnamon rolls and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or light brown.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round pans; heat milk and butter on medium heat until butter has melted, do not cool.
Beat eggs with mixer until light and fluffy (about 5 to 7 minutes).
Slowly add sugar in fourths (still on high.)
Turn mixer to low and slowly add flour and baking soda mixture; mix well.
Add milk and butter mixture.
When combined, add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into cake pans and bake 20 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: vegetable chili
directions: Cook and stir garlic, pepper, mushrooms and onion in oil for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder and cumin.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat to low. Add beans, zucchini and corn. Simmer 15 minutes. Add 1 cup cheese. Stir until melted. Spoon into bowls and top with remaining cheese.

title: mom's crock salad
directions: Cut all vegetables into rings or rounds.
Mix last 5 ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover; let sit in fridge for 24 hours, then serve.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Blend in blender.
Do not add eggs until ready to serve.

title: bohemian boiled fish
directions: Season fish pieces with salt, pepper and hot pepper.
Sprinkle lime over fish and let stand 1/2 hour.
Put fish pieces in a medium-sized pot.
Add onion, green pepper, water and potatoes. Boil for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.
Serves 6. Serve with rice or pasta.

title: double delicious pie
directions: Cook pudding according to directions, only adding the chocolate chips and butter as the pudding cooks.
Pour into crust. When completely cool, add topping.

title: chicken fillets
directions: Bake chicken until almost done (45 minutes).
Pull meat off bone in strips.
Mix remaining ingredients together and coat strips.
Deep fat fry in oil until golden brown.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese with fork until smooth.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Shape into ball.
Wrap in Saran Wrap or foil.
Let get firm.
Roll cheese ball in 1 cup of chopped pecans.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Microwave cream cheese for 15 seconds.
Mix all together, except ground nuts.
Roll ball in ground nuts.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch ovenproof glass baking dish.
Using electric mixer, blend cake mix, butter, pecans and 1 egg for 1 minute.
Pat mixture into bottom of prepared dish.

title: jewel dressing
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve as a dressing for cooked or raw vegetables.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: cheese soup
directions: In 1 quart of water, boil onion and celery.
Add potatoes. Cook until tender.
Then add corn, peas, soup and Velveeta cheese. Cook on low heat until melted or leave in crock-pot.

title: fruit salad
directions: Save the juices from drained fruit.
Nuts can be added or any other fruits that you wish.
When fruit are prepared add Fruit Salad Dressing.

title: easy cabbage roll
directions: Chop cabbage, line bottom of greased 13 X 9 inch pan with the cabbage.
Brown meat and onion.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper. Spoon over the cabbage.
Heat soup and water to boil and pour over all.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: overnight macaroons(cookies)
directions: Mix with spoon until well blended.
Cover.

title: homemade dog biscuits
directions: Mix first four ingredients by hand until texture of coarse meal.
Slowly add water until dough forms a ball.
Roll dough to 1/2 inch-thickness and cut into bone or other shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes until bottoms are lightly browned.
Cool completely.
Store in refrigerator.

title: no-crust pepperoni cheese pie
directions: In bowl beat eggs, milk and basil until blended.
Pour egg mixture into pie plate where cheese and sliced pepperoni have been spread.
Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: waldorf rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Transfer to bowl; cover and chill.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar.
Fold in whipped topping.
Add celery, apples, walnuts and raisins to chilled rice. Fold in topping mixture.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook and drain carrots.
Layer with onions and pepper.
Heat marinade and pour over carrots.
Chill overnight.
Serve cold.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Blend soup with broth and eggs.
Pour over chicken.
Combine flour, buttermilk and oleo or butter.
Mix well.
Spoon over chicken, spreading evenly; do not stir.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until crust rises to top and is golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop the bell pepper and onion very fine. Set aside 1 cup pecans.
Drain pineapple and mix all other ingredients well. Form into
a ball and roll in remaining pecans. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: raspberry cobbler
directions: Mix flour and baking powder and milk.
Melt butter in baking dish; add batter, then pour sweetened fruit on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: lemon bar deluxe
directions: Sift together 2 cups flour and confectioners sugar.
Cut in margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat eggs, lemon juice, sugar and grated lemon rind. Sift together 1/4 cup flour and baking powder.
Stir into egg mixture.
When crust is baked, pour mixture over hot crust.
Return to oven and bake 25 minutes longer at 350°.
Cool, then sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut in bars.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in heavy pan and boil 3 minutes, covered.
Uncover and boil until hard crackle in cold water.
Add 2 tablespoons oleo.
Add 2 cups raw peanuts; cook until syrup is golden brown.
(It takes approximately 7 1/2 minutes after putting peanuts in.)
Remove from heat.
Add 2 1/2 teaspoons baking soda. Stir well.
Pour into a well-greased pan (large pan).
Cool and break into pieces.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; drain well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in soup, stuffing and butter.
Mix well. Pour in casserole dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: hommus
directions: Mix or blend wet, then add dry ingredients.
Should be of thick consistency.
Mix in parsley last.
Serve with crackers, breadsticks, pita bread, etc.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cook the water, sugar, cornstarch and butter in a double boiler until thick. Beat the egg yolks until creamy and add a small amount of hot mixture to the egg yolks and then add all of the hot mixture to prevent curdling. Cook this a few minutes and then add the lemon juice. Pour into a baked pie crust.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Pour mix into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken breasts, lettuce, onions, chow mein noodles and almonds together.
Gently heat the vinegar, oil, sesame seed, salt, pepper and Accent in a saucepan until sugar dissolves. Cool.
Pour over salad ingredients.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter together and press on bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish. Set in refrigerator to chill.

title: scallops
directions: Place scallops in buttered dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and then dab with butter.
Top with remaining ingredients and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: white chili chowder
directions: Melt the garlic butter in soup pot.
Add onions and saute until tender but not browned.
Add chilies, cumin, oregano, ground red pepper, chicken broth and hash browns.
Cook until potatoes are fork tender.
Add beans and chicken.
Stir and continue cooking over low heat for about 5 minutes.
Gradually add half & half.
Stir in cheese.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Take chicken breasts and pound with meat mallet until about 1/2-inch thick. Place chicken in resealable plastic bag. Add lemon juice. Marinate 30 minutes to 1 hour. Remove chicken. Dredge in flour. Cook in skillet in the cooking oil until done. Should be about 3 minutes per side. Will be golden brown. Serve hot. Makes 4 servings.

title: chili con carne pie
directions: Grease a shallow 2-quart casserole or baking dish.
In the baking dish, combine all the ingredients except the cheese and topping.
Place in oven at 450° for about 10 minutes while preparing the topping.
Cover top of hot casserole with cornbread mixture and return to oven for approximately 25 minutes or until done.

title: chili-chicken casserole(spicy)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed on package and drain.
In large skillet, cook and stir onion in butter until tender.
Stir in soup, pimento and chili peppers.
In a greased 4-quart casserole dish, layer 1/2 noodles and 1/2 chicken.
Top with 1/2 the soup mixture and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake uncovered about 45 minutes.

title: quick berry cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Spread half in a greased pan (9 x 13-inch).
Pour on fruit, then spread remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 350° until done, usually 30 minutes.

title: honey mustard ham glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Mix well. Brush or spoon mixture over ham during last 30 minutes of baking time. Makes 1/2 cup.

title: bustar bar ice cream cake
directions: Crust:
Combine crushed Oreos and melted margarine.
Pack into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze 1 hour.

title: blueberry buttermilk muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
In another bowl, whisk eggs, buttermilk and butter that has been melted and browned slightly.
Make a well in dry ingredients and pour in liquid ingredients, mixing quickly.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon batter into greased muffin cups and bake until golden brown.
Bake at 400° for 20-30 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer ingredients as given.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool before cutting into squares. Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in good size bowl.
Refrigerate until set.

title: italian slaw
directions: In alternate layers, arrange the cabbage and onion in large bowl.
Top with 7/8 cup of sugar (do not stir).

title: fudge frosting
directions: Combine chocolate and butter in top of a double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook until chocolate and butter melt, stirring occasionally.
Remove mixture from heat and let cool.
Add powdered sugar and milk to chocolate mixture, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Yields 2 cups.

title: frozen orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Mix with all ingredients except coconut.
Shape into small balls and roll in coconut.
Freeze and serve frozen.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: tropical dessert
directions: Prepare gelatin according to directions on package and gell with fruit cocktail.
Chill until set.
Make pudding according to the directions on package.
Cut angel food cake into small squares. In a bowl, make layers of cake, vanilla pudding, jello with fruit cocktail, whipped cream and roasted, slivered almonds.
Do these layers 2 times.
Can be prepared 24 hours ahead.

title: refrigerated cole slaw
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; let stand 1 hour.
Combine all ingredients in a large jar; refrigerate.
Take out as you need.

title: dijon barbecue sauce
directions: Mix thoroughly and use as a basting sauce for broiling or grilling meat.

title: peel-a-pound of soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Very lo-cal, nutritious soup.

title: chicken in dill sauce
directions: Place chicken cutlets in baking dish. Saute onion in butter until golden brown. Add other ingredients except cheese and pour over cutlets.
Top with cheese and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: french applesauce cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large bowl. Beat 4 minutes at medium speed of mixer. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool in pan 15 minutes; remove and cool on rack. Top with powdered sugar glaze.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown hamburger meat in a skillet until done and drain fat. Season with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Can use part of a package of taco seasoning.
Optional:
Add some chopped onion and bell pepper.
Add chunked pieces of Velveeta cheese to top of meat.
Pour cornbread mixture (all the ingredients except meat) on top of the meat and cheese.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes. Remove from oven and top with grated cheese.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add lightly beaten egg yolks. Sift dry ingredients together. Add to butter and sugar mixture alternately with sour cream. Add vanilla. Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Fold into mixture and bake in greased and floured angel food pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until just tender, drain and rinse in cold water.
Drain well.
Mix with all ingredients.
Quantity of each ingredient may be adjusted to suit personal taste.
Makes 8 servings.

title: swedish cabbage rolls
directions: Pour over cabbage rolls; bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan or large tube pan.

title: fudge cake
directions: In a saucepan, melt the butter and combine with the water. Add the cocoa and bring to a boil. Stir well and remove from heat. Add the sugar; mix well. Add the flour, stirring until smooth. Blend the eggs and sour cream into the mixture. Spread into a well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake in 375° oven for 40 minutes or until done.

title: cheese and sausage medley
directions: Place 2 cups croutons in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
In a large bowl, combine sausage, celery, green pepper, onion and pimiento.
Fold in mayonnaise and mustard.
Spread over croutons.
Top with cheese and remaining croutons.
Combine eggs and half and half.
Pour over croutons.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven, uncovered, for 1 hour or until set.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: grebble cake
directions: Prepare white bread dough per instructions. Roll to 1/8-inch ticks. Cut into 2-inch strips. Put 2 slits into middle. Put in hot oil and fry until brown. Drop into paper bag with powdered sugar and shake. Ready to eat!

title: tofu vegetable stir-fry
directions: Sprinkle Sazon seasoning over cubed tofu.
Saute vegetables in oil.
Cook for 10 minutes or until done.
Add tofu and soy sauce. Heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.
Serves 2.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Prepare vegetables in a salad bowl.
Cover with a layer of mayonnaise.
Sprinkle grated cheese and bacon.
Parmesan cheese may be put on top, if desired.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toss together before serving.

title: squash cups
directions: Chop up all of the squash in thin slices.
Dump the flour and water in different bowls.
Dip each slice of squash in the water and then dip into the flour.
Layer on a cookie sheet sprayed with butter spray.
Cook at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until crispy. Add any seasonings that you like.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all ingredients until ice is crushed.

title: miniature cheese cakes
directions: Draw a 10-inch (25 cm) circle on greased foil, which has been placed on a baking sheet.
Pile meringue mixture inside the circle. The meringue will spread out a bit while baking.
Smooth the top to ensure it is all the same height.
Bake in a preheated oven at 220° for two hours.
After baking, turn off heat and let Pavlova cool in oven without opening the oven door.
Assemble just prior to serving.
Spread whipped cream on top of Pavlova.
Place fruit on top of this in a decorative manner.
Sliced kiwis and strawberries are always good tasting, but the true Pavlova is topped with passion fruit pulp.
Serve the passion fruit pulp in a bowl, to be added on top, as it looks gooey and has an orange color with black dots.
Its flavor is unusual.

title: calamari ripiene grattinate(stuffed calamari au gratin)
directions: Mix tentacles, parsley and garlic and brown for 10 minutes. Add 2 tablespoons breadcrumbs and chopped anchovy fillets with a pinch of salt.
Fry a few minutes longer.
Take off burner and allow to cool.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Fill the calamari cavities and close with a toothpick.
Put in baking pan with about 1 to 2 tablespoons oil.
Cover and cook 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Ten minutes prior to removal, uncover to brown.

title: frozen creamed corn
directions: Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Cool and freeze.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Have chicken broth boiling.
Roll out dough, a little at a time as thin as possible.
Cut into strips and drop into boiling broth.
Repeat until all dough is used.
Cook until dumplings are done.
Add black pepper to taste.

title: bacon-jelly-cheese puff
directions: Trim crust from bread and butter each slice.
Arrange 8 slices, buttered sides down, in bottom of well buttered rectangular baking dish.
Cover with 8 slices of cheese; top with remaining slices of bread, buttered side up.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in pan of hot water in moderate oven (350°) for about 1 hour, or until puffed and browned.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Boil the broccoli.
Boil the chicken. Save broth.
Put broccoli in a square casserole.
Shred the chicken and add to the broccoli.
In a saucepan, mix cream of chicken soup and chicken broth to dilute, then add cornstarch and water mixture to thicken. Add mayonnaise.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour over chicken and broccoli mixture.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Heat all ingredients in a large stainless steel pot or in crock-pot.
Do not boil.

title: frances' candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel sweet potatoes.
Carefully slice lengthwise into slab about 1/2-inch thick.
Heat butter and margarine in large frying pan.
Place a single layer of potato slices into pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and turn over.
Fry sugar side down until brown. Sprinkle with sugar; turn potatoes and fry other side until brown.

title: seafood gumbo(use a very large pot.)
directions: Make a very dark roux with flour and oil, stirring all the time.
Add onions, garlic, bell peppers and celery.
Stir well. When wilted, add tomatoes and water.
Salt and pepper.
Let come to a boil, then turn to medium heat and add okra and crab boil.
Let simmer 45 minutes.
Add shrimp, crab meat and oysters.
Simmer slowly for 20 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Add green onions and parsley.
Serve over rice.

title: quick baba ghanouj
directions: Salt cubed eggplant and let it rest for about 10 minutes to remove bitter juice.
Place in pan; cover with water and bring to a rapid boil.
Cook for about 10 minutes until soft.
Drain. Combine eggplant with Tahini sauce.
Add seasoning.
Garnish with parsley.

title: great macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil the macaroni in water until tender; drain thoroughly. Stir in butter and egg.
Mix the dry mustard and salt with 1 tablespoon of hot water; add to milk and set aside.
Add the cheese to the macaroni, reserving enough cheese to sprinkle on top.
Place into a greased casserole dish.
Pour the milk mixture over all.
Sprinkle with the reserved cheese.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes, or until custard is set.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Trim crust from bread and flatten with rolling pin.
Blend cheese until smooth.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Spread evenly on each slice of bread.
Drain asparagus on paper towels.
Roll one spear of asparagus in each slice of bread. Dip in butter to coat even or brush butter over roll.
Place on cookie sheet side by side, seam down.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Cut in thirds and serve hot.
Makes 60.

title: top of stove cookies
directions: Boil first four ingredients for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Mix well and drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Allow to dry.
Enjoy.
Also good chilled.

title: italian dressing
directions: Put dry ingredients in large jar.
Add warm water and whip. Add oil.
Add vinegar last.
Keep in cool place.

title: busy day cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a small mixer bowl, combine all ingredients and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Beat with electric mixer until combined.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Turn into pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: wassail
directions: Mix orange juice, apple juice and lemonade together.
Place over low heat.
Add sugar and spices.
Stir in boiling water and tea.
Heat, but do not boil.
Makes 20 to 25 servings.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Mash balls gently with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Will be very crisp, so cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: nut fingers
directions: Mix all together.
Put in refrigerator until chilled.
After chilled, make into balls or fingers, then cook at 300° or more for 20 minutes.
After you cook them, roll in powdered sugar.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until browned.
Separate crescent roll dough into eight triangles.
Place dough into an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan. Press dough over bottom and sides of pan to form a crust; seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Add potatoes.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over pizza.

title: cheesy pig in the blanket
directions: Preheat oven to 350° or 375°.
Open can of crescent rolls and separate them.
There should be 8 triangles.
Cut the slices of cheese in half.
There should now be 8 rectangle slices of cheese. Place one cheese slice on one crescent.
Place one hot dog onto one crescent roll and roll up.
Follow these steps for the remaining 7 turkey hot dogs.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Grease and flour sheath pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix and jello.
Add rest and beat well.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes. When cool, frost with 1/4 box of frozen type strawberries and 1/4 stick butter.
Add powdered sugar until thick enough to spread.

title: apple pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in shallow baking dish.
Cover with sliced apples.
Pour apple juice on top; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Take cover off and bake additional 15 minutes.

title: chicken turkey dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour, depending on size of baking dish.

title: ten layer salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch dish in order given. Cover with plastic wrap, then foil.
Refrigerate until serving. May be prepared a day before serving.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in salted water only until tender; drain and stir into sauteed (fry) celery and onion.
Remove heat; add egg and milk.
Mix in crumbs and cheese.
Pour into a baking dish; dot with butter and sprinkle a little bit of crumbs and cheese on top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: eye of the round cocktail roast
directions: Put a generous	sprinkling of tenderizer on one side of the roast for half
hour,
then
on
the
other for half hour. Marinate roast
in	the
remaining ingredients in refrigerator overnight.	Turn once
before
bedtime.
Cook
either in foil, wrapped tightly, or in
roaster,
covered,	at 200° for 4 or 5 hours.
Allow to cool
before
slicing
or	take
back
to the butcher for slicing, if very thin slices are preferred.

title: holiday raspberry jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Chill until slightly thickened and fold in pecans.
Chill until firm. Beat cream cheese and sour cream until smooth and spread on Jell-O mixture.

title: quick tomato aspic
directions: Seed tomatoes.
Cut with 2 knives until fine pieces are achieved.
Slice olives.
Add to tomatoes.
Make Jell-O, less 1/4 cup water.
Add to tomato mixture and chill until set.

title: joyce's fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients about 15 minutes over medium heat. Turn off heat and leave on the stove eye.
Add vanilla and marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Add all other ingredients and pour into dish or pan.
Let cool.

title: chicken rice-a-roni salad(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Cook chicken Rice-A-Roni and cool to warm.
Prepare all vegetables and cut artichokes.
Gently mix all ingredients in big bowl.
Put into 2 quart bowl to serve.
Chill 5 to 6 hours.
Serves 10-12.

title: ice cream crunch
directions: Crumble Oreos (1 package).
Mix in slightly softened ice cream, Cool Whip and pecans.
Spread in a large 13 x 9-inch pan and freeze.
Serve in squares with chocolate syrup and a cherry on top.

title: family favorite roast(courtesy of robbie travers)
directions: Marinate roast 2 to 3 days in the remaining ingredients.
Place roast and marinade in Ziploc bag.
Turn twice a day.

title: cornish hens with wild rice
directions: Preheat oven to
Combine
rice
(minus
packaged seasonings) and water in 2 quart saucepan.
Cover; cook for 12 minutes or until water is absorbed.

title: minnesota hot dish
directions: Pour soup mixture over all.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 2 hours.
Season to your taste.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; reserve broth.
Chop chicken; set aside and boil noodles in broth.
Salt onion and bell pepper; add Ro-Tel and pimento.
Cook until bubbling; reduce heat.
Chop cheese in small pieces; add to Ro-Tel mixture.
When cheese melts, add chopped chicken.
