Drain noodles and add to Ro-Tel and chicken mixture. Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: pickled okra
directions: Boil vinegar, water and salt for 10 minutes.
Pack washed okra in pint jar.
Place dill, garlic and hot peppers in each jar. Pour hot mixture over okra in jars to cover.
Seal and allow 3 weeks to pickle.

title: curry chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts into thirds.
Marinate 30 minutes to 1 hour in yogurt mixture.
Roll in crumbs.
Fry in salad oil.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: barbecue beef ribs
directions: Put ribs in slow cooker.
Mix barbecue sauce (shake bottle well) with vinegar and water.
Mix well and pour over ribs.
If this is not enough for meat, add a little more to your sauce. Cook in slow cooker on medium or low until done.

title: eggs brunch
directions: Place the bacon, beef, 1/4 cup butter and mushrooms in a large frying pan.
Sprinkle the flour and some pepper over mixture. Gradually add the milk.
Cook until thick.
In another pan, scramble 1 dozen eggs.
Add dash of salt, 1/4 cup butter and the evaporated milk.
Layer in 10 x 10 x 2-inch casserole dish, eggs first, then cover with meat mixture.
Alternate until all is used, ending with meat mixture.
Sprinkle remaining mushrooms on top. Bake, uncovered, in Corning glass dish at 270° for 45 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Put 2 cups bran into a large bowl.
Pour boiling water over it and let stand while assembling other ingredients.
Mix
in melted shortening.
Mix remainder of the bran with sugar, eggs and buttermilk.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt. Combine all ingredients.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.
Bake as much as desired in muffin tin in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Chill 2 hours.

title: paul's baked beans
directions: Cook bacon and onion together.
Don't brown onions.
Put into crock-pot; add beans and other ingredients.
Simmer on high 1 hour.

title: my mother's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together brown sugar, cinnamon, ginger and salt.
Add pumpkin and eggs.
Stir together and add milk; stir until blended. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: granma's teacakes
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour.
Alternate flour with liquid mixture until thick dough is formed.
Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into shapes.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Add pineapple juice.
Pour into punch bowl.
Just before serving, add ice and ginger ale.

title: black bottom pie
directions: You will need 9-inch pie plate.

title: egg and cheese casserole breakfast dish
directions: Brown the sausage; set aside.
Blend eggs and milk together. Add bread cubes, cheese, dry mustard and sausage.
Mix well and cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes, covered, in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Slightly freeze loaf of bread.
Trim crusts and roll each slice of bread between 2 sheets of waxed paper until very thin. Spread cream cheese, place a piece of asparagus in center and roll up.
Place on cookie sheet, seam side down.
Brush lightly with melted butter and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
tags: containers whipped cream cheese with onions

title: turkey chowder
directions: In a five-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, saute celery and onions in margarine until vegetables are tender crisp.
Add broth, potatoes, salt, pepper, and cayenne pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Once it's simmering, cover and cook 10 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Stir in turkey.
In medium bowl gradually add milk to cornstarch.
Stir mixture into soup. Increase heat to medium, and cook 6-8 minutes longer until mixture thickens.

title: fruit bars
directions: Cream sugar and eggs; add vanilla. Add flour which has soda and salt added. Add fruit and nutmeats. Bake in large cookie sheet at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Let cool and ice.

title: crispy chicken drumsticks
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in container of an electric blender or food processor; top with cover and process until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Brush chicken with honey (lightly); dredge in oat mixture.
Place drumsticks on a rack in a roasting pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn drumsticks and bake an additional 20 minutes or until chicken is tender and golden.
Yield:
4 servings (240 calories per serving).

title: baked corn
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add all other ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: esther's baked chicken and rice
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup broth and soup.
Mix remaining ingredients and bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan for 1 hour at 325°.
When done, pour soup, thinned with broth, over casserole and let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.
(Soup and broth should be warmed.)

title: macaroni springtime salad with dill dressing
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and rinse.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.
Toss salad before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: ma's sweet dills
directions: Cut pickles in small slices or sticks.
Put in large bowl. Boil next four ingredients for 5 minutes and pour over pickles. Leave uncovered overnight.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Put a few pecan chips in crust.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and 10x sugar together and pour in crust.
Put cherry pie filling and nuts on top.

title: deep fried cauliflower
directions: Combine egg, oil and milk.
Add to flour gradually.
Add salt. Beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Divide cauliflower into flowerets.
Cook in salted water until tender.
Drain well.
Dip flowerets in batter.
Fry in 375° deep fat until lightly browned. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; add salt and place small mounds the size of a garlic head on buttered baking dish.
Bake in a very moderate oven (300°) for 30 minutes.

title: bagel cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Chill, serve on bagels, toast or other sweet breads.
The cheese mixture can be shaped in a roll in waxed paper, then rolled in the chopped pecans.

title: strawberry cheesecake trifle
directions: In a large bowl, cream together cream cheese and confectioners sugar; add sour cream, vanilla and almond extract.
Set aside.

title: best waffles
directions: Sift flour once.
Add baking powder and salt and sift again. Combine egg yolks and milk.
Add flour, beating until smooth.
Add butter.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in hot waffle iron.

title: fruit slush
directions: Combine pineapple, strawberries, bananas, orange juice concentrate, sugar and ginger ale in freezer container.
Mix well. Freeze until firm.
Thaw slightly before serving.
May substitute Sprite for ginger ale.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Into saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, water and 2 cups blueberries.
Cook, stirring over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat; add butter.
Place 2 cups blueberries in shell and pour warm filling over all.
Chill. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pork chops and heavenly rice
directions: Quickly brown pork chops at 425° in electric skillet. Add rice, soup mix and water. Bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat. Simmer for 35 to 40 minutes until rice is tender.

title: roasted vegetables
directions: Place all vegetables on a lightly greased piece of aluminum foil.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with spices.
Fold aluminum into secure packet.
Cook on grill 20 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: rocks
directions: Mix all of the ingredients. Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: *Use good quality, not flavored oil.

title: chili
directions: Add hamburger meat to sausage.
Blend onion and pepper. Pulverize ingredients and blend together and add to meat.
Rinse out catsup bottle with water and add to chili and cook until done or gone.
(Darrel could never make a small pot of chili.
Always plenty for whatever and sharing with whoever.
Never spoils, but disappears quickly.)
Excellent over Fritos and topped with Cheddar cheese!

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour 1/4 cup boiling water over oatmeal and margarine; let stand 20 minutes covered.
Add sugars, eggs, flour, soda, salt and nutmeg.
Grease and flour long dish and bake at 350°.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Cut butter into flour until crumbly.
Stir in 3/4 cup nuts. Press into bottom of pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool (place in freezer for 20 minutes).
In a small bowl, mix the cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in powdered sugar and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Chill (place in freezer for 20 minutes).

title: chicken with mushroom sauce
directions: Combine the flour, salt and pepper.
Coat the chicken breasts with flour mixture.
Heat the oil and butter in a large skillet and brown the chicken on both sides, about 10 minutes.
Lower the heat and continue to cook the chicken until it is cooked and tender, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove to a serving platter and keep warm.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer pie filling on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer pineapple on top of cherries.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over all.
Sprinkle coconut on top and bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: midnight madness
directions: If available, use 1 chocolate flavored pie crust, otherwise use regular crust to bake.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Cook beef separately until well done, seasoned to taste with salt and pepper.
Using the broth from the beef, add vegetables, cabbage, macaroni and potatoes.
Cook slowly until all ingredients are well done.
Then add tomato juice for color.
Increase ingredients according to size of family.

title: weekend casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Quick and easy.

title: lazy cabbage rolls
directions: In casserole, layer the cabbage, ground beef, mixed with rice and diced onion, and salt and pepper.
Pour over layers the tomato soup, mixed with tomato sauce and beef flavoring.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°, covered.

title: pizza bread
directions: With greased hands, spread dough (one loaf) in greased cookie sheet.
Beat together eggs and spices.
Spread 1/2 on dough, then top with 1/2 cheese and pepperoni, covering dough completely. Roll up, pinch ends and place in greased bread pan.
Repeat with other loaf.
Brush top with beaten egg.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, then at 325° for 10 minutes.
Everyone loves this!

title: mounds
directions: With hands, mix sugar, coconut, vanilla, oleo and Eagle Brand milk.
Roll into balls; let freeze.
Melt chocolate in a double boiler.
Melt paraffin and pour into chocolate.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture and put on waxed paper to cool.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Saute margarine, mustard, onion and Worcestershire sauce for about 15 minutes.
Refrigerate until spreadable, 2 to 3 hours. Remove rolls from tin; slice in half.
Place sauce on both sides. Place ham on bottom half.
Sprinkle cheese over the ham.
Place biscuits back together in tin.
With knife, separate the rolls. Wrap tin of biscuits in heavy foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: *Spread butter on both sides of bread before cubing.

title: doug's doo dah
directions: Stir orange jello, tapioca and water until thick.
Cool.
Add mandarin oranges and 1 tub cool whip.
Refrigerate.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Then add flour, vanilla, salt, syrup and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 60 minutes or until firm at 350°.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1 1/4 cups of hot water.
Add to soup and heat to boiling in pan.
Add 2 packages of cream cheese; mix and cool slightly.
Beat in mixer until smooth.
Add mayonnaise, celery, onions and shrimp.
Pour into mold and chill until set. Enjoy!

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and salt, then add the scalded milk.
Last, add the vanilla.
Pour into a pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 325° to 350° for about 45 minutes or until a table knife comes out clean.
(Don't let the pie bubble.)

title: peach honey crisp
directions: Mix peaches, honey and cornstarch well and heat on stove until mixture thickens a bit.
Cool and put in container and freeze until needed.
Peaches are preserved by the honey and will not darken.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together as listed.
Serve with round rye bread.
Scoop out middle and tear in chunks.
Fill center with dill dip.
Put pieces of bread around bread on serving tray.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding mix, stirring until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in crust and chill.

title: lime pickles
directions: First soak cucumbers and lime in 2 gallons water for 24 hours. Don't use aluminum container.
Rinse thoroughly.
Soak in fresh ice cold water for 3 hours.
Next put spices in bag and add to sugar, vinegar, salt and food coloring.
Soak cucumbers in vinegar solution 12 hours over overnight.
Cook gently about 45 minutes until cucumbers lose their white look.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 10 to 12 pints.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar and margarine.
Make into balls, refrigerate overnight.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips. Stick a toothpick into a peanut butter ball.
Dip in chocolate mixture, leaving the top plain to resemble a buckeye.
Set on waxed paper to dry.
I usually double the paraffin and chocolate chips (24 ounces).
Spread a thin layer on bottom and top of peanut butter mixture.
Its a lot quicker.
It makes 2 large pans full. Makes up like Reeses cup instead of buckeyes.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter, then add mashed bananas and salt.
Add flour and milk alternately, then add eggs.
Beat well, then add vanilla.
Grease and flour two 8-inch cake pans.
Pour evenly in the pans.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
When cool, you may put the Banana Cake Icing on it.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add the whole eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Stir in milk and flour.
Beat until smooth and thoroughly mixed.
Fill well-greased and floured cake pans 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated 375° oven 25-30 minutes.

title: the hot mustard
directions: Mix mustard
and
vinegar
until
smooth.
Add sugar to eggs and beat until smooth, using rubber spatula.
Add vinegar and mustard mix to egg and sugar mix.
Blend well.

title: chili sauce
directions: Slow boil for 2 to 3 hours or until ready to put in jars. Makes 10 to 12 pints.

title: make ahead whipped cream
directions: In a small ovenproof bowl or custard cup, sprinkle gelatin over water.
Set the bowl into 1-inch of hot water in a saucepan; let stand until gelatin dissolves.
Remove bowl from the water and let the mixture cool for about 1 minute.
Whip the cream until almost stiff, then add the dissolved gelatin, salt, vanilla and sugar; continue to whip until cream is stiff.
Cover and refrigerate.
Just before serving, beat with a spoon to blend. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: sauce for pork roast
directions: Combine salt, garlic salt and 1/2 teaspoon chili powder.
Rub on roast.
Cover all areas.
Roast at 325° for 2 hours.
In saucepan, combine jelly, catsup, vinegar and chili powder.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 2 minutes.
Set aside.
Fifteen minutes before roast is done, brush roast with sauce or spoon over.
Mix pan drippings with remaining sauce and serve with roast.

title: brandy slush
directions: Bring first 2 ingredients to a boil and cool.
Bring next 2 ingredients to a boil and cool.
Add the orange juice and lemonade to the tea mixture.
Add the sugar mixture, tea mixture and brandy together.
Freeze and stir every few hours.
When serving, add 7-Up to mixture to desired consistency.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients with a 3 liter bottle of Sprite.

title: pastor's sad cake
directions: With
mixer blend Bisquick, eggs and brown sugar.
Fold in pecans
and vanilla.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x
9 x
2-inch
pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until
it tests
done.
Cool
and cut into squares.
(Makes a chewy,
moist bar cookie;
really easy.) More of a bar cookie than a cake.

title: artichoke appetizers
directions: Chop artichoke hearts and green chilies. In a mixing bowl, combine artichokes, chilies, cheese, mayo and mustard. When ready to serve preheat oven to 350°. Split English muffins and spread mixture on each half. Bake for 30 minutes until browned. Cut each half into quarters to serve as bite-sized pieces. May be baked in a shallow round baking dish as a hot dip served with crisp bread or tortilla chips.

title: deviled clams
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and celery in butter until tender. Mix with clams and remaining ingredients.
Fill greased ramekins or scallop shells and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or microwave until hot.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion.
Add salt and pepper; drain and add oleo and 1/2 of stuffing mix.
Mix well.
Add other ingredients. Put squash mixture into greased pan and sprinkle remaining herb seasoned stuffing mix on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Save 1 cup of flour to mix with fruit and pecans.
Mix 1 cup of flour with fruit and pecans.
Mix all other ingredients together, then pour in with the floured fruit and pecans.
Pour into greased pan and cook for 3 hours at 250°.

title: mock chow mein
directions: Brown beef in large skillet, drain off fat. Stir in vegetables, rice, soup, water and soy sauce. Heat to boiling. Pour into a shallow 2 quart baking dish. Bake at 375 degrees for one hour or until rice is tender. Top with noodles and bake two minutes longer. Makes 6-8 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, soup and vegetables in ungreased casserole dish. Mix Bisquick, egg and milk and pour over top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: beth's pizza snacks
directions: Arrange muffins on paper plate.
Spread spaghetti sauce on top with cheese.
Heat in microwave for 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 2.

title: roquefort dressing(glop)
directions: Shake in a jar and chill.

title: parmesan tomato casserole
directions: Mix well and place in greased casserole dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: meal-in-one casserole
directions: Pour all ingredients including juices into a casserole dish. Mix well and season to taste.
Open 1 can of biscuits and place over top of mixture.
Bake at 325° until biscuits are done and browned.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup liquid. Add onion to carrots.
Add horseradish, salad dressing, salt, pepper and reserved liquid to carrots.
Break toast into small pieces and place on carrots.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake until golden brown, 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon angel food cake
directions: Prepare angel food cake according to package directions.
Pour 1/2 of the mix in tube pan.
Add powdered cinnamon and swirl into batter.
Pour remainder of batter on top. Bake according to package directions. Cool and serve with Cool Whip with cinnamon mixed in.

title: skillet supper
directions: Line a heavy skillet or electric skillet with strips of bacon. On top of the bacon, layer hamburger, carrots, onion and potatoes.
Pour water, salt and pepper over all.
Cover and steam until potatoes are soft, approximately 30 minutes.

title: 4 layer salad
directions: Mix Italian dressing according to directions on package.
Add mayonnaise and mix well.
In a large container, layer lettuce, cauliflower, green pepper and peas in order listed.
Pour dressing over layers; do not stir.
Let set overnight.
The next day before serving, mix very well.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: no name cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in a large loaf pan (ungreased). Spread out.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: speedy tomato-sauced pasta with spinach
directions: In a large pot, cook linguine in boiling salted water until almost tender, 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain well.
Return pasta to pot. Add all remaining ingredients to pot.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until hot and bubbly, about 5 minutes.
Serve with a generous topping of grated Parmesan cheese.

title: enchilada sauce
directions: Add 1 small can chili with no beans.
Layer over your Enchilada Casserole.

title: tempura batter
directions: Mix
batter slightly (don't overmix).
Dip desired food into batter and deep fry.

title: on the double dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Add sugar, salt, Butter Buds and 1 cup of the flour.
Beat until smooth. Stir in the rest of the flour and continue stirring until smooth. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in size (about 30 to 40 minutes).
Spoon batter into 24 muffin cups, sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Fill each cup about 1/2 full.
Let rise until dough reaches the top of the muffin tin (28 to 30 minutes). Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 24.

title: crab english muffin split
directions: Mix all ingredients; spread on English muffin halves and freeze.
Bake frozen at 400° for 10 minutes, then broil until brown.
Yields 12 to 18 pieces.

title: three bean turkey burger bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown ground turkey and onions; drain.
Add lima beans.
Cook and stir until beans are thoroughly heated.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake, uncovered, in 2-quart casserole at 350° for 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 one-cup servings.

title: golf balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into small balls.
Melt chocolate and wax together.
Dip balls into chocolate and place on waxed paper.
Let cool.
Makes approximately 5 to 6 dozen.

title: baked fish
directions: Marinate fish 1/2 to 1 hour in dressing.
Mix onion rings with Parmesan cheese (crush onion rings until very fine); add lemon juice.
Arrange fillets in baking dish.
Sprinkle onion and cheese mixture over fish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Garnish with fresh lemon.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken; debone and cut into chunks.
Mix soup, milk, onion and vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Add salt and pepper.
Add the chicken.
Place in a casserole dish and top with the biscuits. Bake at 425° until biscuits are brown, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: waldorf cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour and baking powder; set aside.
In a small bowl, beat eggs.
Combine chocolate and margarine in a saucepan and heat over low heat until melted; cool slightly.
Add eggs and cooled chocolate to flour mixture; mix until well blended.
Add milk and mix well.
Stir in vanilla. Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center of the cake comes out clean.
Let cake cool slightly.
Frost cake in pan.

title: pigs in blanket
directions: Using a Pressure Cooker:

title: shaker lemon pie
directions: Slice the lemons as thin as paper, rind and all. Place them in a bowl and put the sugar over them. Mix well and let stand for 2 hours or more. Beat the eggs together and pour over lemons. Fill unbaked pie shell with mixture and add top crust. Cut small vents in the top crust to let out steam. Place in a preheated 450° oven for 15 minutes and then turn heat down to 350° and bake for 30 minutes or until a silver knife inserted into the pie comes out clean.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in large, 6-quart kettle.
Remove to cool.
Skin and debone chicken.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Strain broth through filter to remove excess fat.
Return to kettle.
Bring to rolling boil.

title: fresh apple nut cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients; set aside.
Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in order.
Combine with dry ingredients.
Add sliced apples and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with cream cheese frosting.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in sugar and salt; bring to a boil for 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda.
Pour over corn and put in shallow pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Store in sealed container.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put rice in baking dish.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Stir.
May put chicken pieces on top (salt and peppered).
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: meat balls
directions: Bring soup and water to boil.
Mix all other ingredients together and shape into balls.
Drop into boiling soup and simmer 2 hours.

title: cheese nacho dip
directions: Fry hamburger and drain fat.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and thoroughly melt.
Eat with chips.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, add eggs one at a time.
Stir in bananas. Sift together salt, soda and flour; add to banana mixture.
Mix until blended. Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: irish shamrock cookies
directions: Cream butter and pudding mix.
Add baking mix, egg and sugar; mix well.
Roll on lightly floured board to 3/8-inch thickness. Cut with shamrock-shaped cookie cutter.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Top with frosting.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: cheesy chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil chicken and chop.
Add soup to broth.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Add soup and chicken mixture to spaghetti; season with salt, pepper and seasoned salt, if desired.
Pour into a greased casserole dish; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple waikiki
directions: Combine ingredients in order given and serve.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar and rhubarb in saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is completely melted and rhubarb begins to soften, 5 to 8 minutes.
Spread evenly in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: rambutan-mandarin-apricot cocktail
directions: Mix all ingredients well, serve over crushed ice in tall glass.
Serves 1.

title: marinated beef salad
directions: Combine salsa, oil, vinegar and red onion in medium bowl.
Add roast beef; stir to coat with salsa mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour. Just before serving, add avocado and tomato. Toss.
Place beef mixture on shredded lettuce.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour, salt, pepper and cheese.
Add milk and cook until thickened.
Alternate layers of vegetables, sauce (mushrooms or eggs) and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together shortening, 1 1/2 cups white sugar and eggs.
Add flour, cream of tartar, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Roll into walnut-size balls.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon in small bowl.
Roll balls in this mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken barley casserole
directions: Melt shortening.
Cook barley and onion in it until slightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Transfer to greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until barley is tender.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Blend pudding and pineapple.
Add Cool Whip, marshmallows and pecans.
Mix well and chill.

title: fast and easy chili
directions: Brown meat, add rest of ingredients.
Cook on low heat about 1 hour.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion.
Drain to remove fat.
In pan, pour tomatoes, kidney beans, corn and chicken broth.
Add meat. Simmer 30 minutes.
Add taco seasoning and Ranch dressing mix.
Add cabbage, if desired.

title: salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite size pieces. Add layer of crumbled bacon and layer of cut up cauliflower.

title: honey dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in a tightly covered container.
This is great on chicken salad.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover 25-30 minutes or until tender;
drain and cool.
Cut into thin wedges.
Saute bacon in a large skillet over medium- high heat 2 minutes.
Add green onions and saute 2 minutes.
Stir in flour and cook constantly 1 minute.
Gradually stir in
water and vinegar;
cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Toss with potatoes and pimiento.
Serve warm.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: canned corn
directions: Bring to boil the corn, salt, sugar and water, then add acid. Cook 20 minutes and put in jars and seal.
Rinse well before using.
Tastes good and crisp.

title: cole slaw
directions: Put cabbage and carrots into a large bowl.
Place mayonnaise, cider vinegar, salt, pepper, sugar, cayenne, Tabasco, milk, onion and green pepper into blender.
Blend on high until vegetables are pureed.
Pour into bowl with cabbage and carrots.
Mix thoroughly. Cover and place in refrigerator for about an hour to allow flavors to blend.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef into 1/4-inch thick and 1/4-inch wide strips. Brown quickly in 1/4 cup of butter in heavy skillet.
Push meat to one side and add mushrooms and onion.
Saute until tender, but not brown.
Add can of beef broth and red wine.
Heat just to boiling.
Simmer several minutes.
Blend cup of sour cream with 2 1/2 tablespoons of enriched flour; stir into broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened (sauce will be thin).
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over hot noodles or rice.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: eggs and sausage
directions: Melt and spread the butter on bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Sprinkle 1 cup of grated cheese on butter.
Break the eggs over the cheese.
Break yolks with fork.
Sprinkle all with salt and pepper.
Brown sausages and drain well.
Lay over eggs.
Pour cream over all.
Cover with 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: asparagus-artichoke casserole
directions: Make onion dip mix as directed in package with sour cream and add milk to make smooth enough to spoon on.
Layer asparagus, artichokes, dip mix and Cheddar cheese and repeat.
Top with remaining dip mix and cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add condensed milk and blend thoroughly. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: refrigerated bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix and stir first 7 ingredients.
Slice 1 onion in rings in bottom of gallon jug.
Put cucumbers in on onion and pour mixture over both.
Put in refrigerator.
Stir now and then.
Will keep 1 year.

title: stir-and-bake lo-cal drop biscuits
directions: Combine flour, margarine and 5 tablespoons of milk in a mixing bowl.
Stir vigorously until batter is blended.
Stir in additional milk until a soft batter is formed.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls onto a nonstick baking pan which has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake in a preheated oven at 450° for 10 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 biscuits, approximately 80 calories each.

title: microwave layered chicken and broccoli
directions: Stir broccoli, onion, garlic and pepper together in 8-inch dish.
Cover tightly and microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes; stir. Put chicken and water chestnuts on top of first layer.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High 3 minutes.
Mix sour cream and milk and pour over second layer.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on 70% power for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: mock filet mignon
directions: Tear bread into small pieces and place in a small shallow bowl.
Add 1/2 cup water and let soak for 10 minutes.
Squeeze water from bread; discard water.
Combine softened bread, meat, seasoned salt and pepper in a medium bowl.
Mix well.
Shape mixture into 6 patties, each 1/2-inch thick.
Wrap a bacon slice around each patty, securing with a toothpick.
Melt shortening in a large skillet over medium heat.
Cook patties until brown on each side.
Place patties in a lightly greased 2 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Combine 3/4 cup water, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir well.
Pour sauce over patties; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: lazy-day overnight lasagna
directions: Brown meat in large skillet; drain well.
Add spaghetti sauce and water.
Blend well.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine cheese, egg and seasonings.
Mix well.
In bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, spread 1 1/2 cups meat sauce, top with 1/2 noodles, 1/2 cheese mixture, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat.
Top with remaining meat sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Uncover and bake 50 to 60 minutes until noodles are tender and casserole is bubbly.
Cover; let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 12.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Add all other ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole dish. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix and put in greased casserole.
Put buttered bread crumbs and grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: the favorite "capitol bean soup"
directions: Cover beans with water and soak overnight.
Drain and recover with water.
Add the ham hock and simmer for about 4 hours, until beans are cooked tender.
Season with salt and pepper.
Just before serving, "bruise" beans with large spoon or ladle to cloud the soup.

title: swiss steak
directions: Fry a little bacon just for the grease. Cut steak in strips. Roll in flour with the spices mixed in. Place steak strips in the bacon grease and fry until brown on both sides. Slice green pepper and onion in strips. Add can of tomatoes. Cook until tender.

title: super chicken
directions: Cut dried beef in small pieces, place in colander and rinse in cold running water to remove salt.
Place beef in bottom of large casserole.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Mix together and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and onion; stir in carrot.
Fold in zucchini; set aside.
Combine stuffing and margarine; spread 1/2 mixture in 12 x 7 1/2-inch pan.
Spoon the vegetables on top; sprinkle the rest of the dressing over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberries chantilly
directions: Combine pudding mix, jello and water in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to full boil and is slightly thick and clear.
Cool until mixture begins to set.
Stir in strawberries.
Fold in Cool Whip until well blended.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Chill until firm.

title: audrey's pepper steak
directions: Slice green pepper, tomatoes, onions, garlic and mushrooms into thin slices and saute in enough olive oil to coat bottom of skillet.
Saute until green peppers and onions are almost soft, but not brown.
Meanwhile, cut meat into strips approximately 1 x 3-inch.
Put tenderizer on both sides and pound.
Add meat to green pepper mixture and cook over medium high heat to avoid browning green peppers and onions.
Add gravy and salt to pepper to taste.
Simmer covered until you are ready to serve, at least 10 minutes.
Prepare rice while this simmers.
Makes 2 servings.

title: cream cheese-pineapple ball
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl, mixing well.
Shape into a ball.
Chill until serving time.

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage.
Add catsup, seasoning and cheese.
Spoon onto party rye.
Freeze on cookie sheets, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Stack in plastic bags and freeze.
To heat:
Put under broiler for 4 minutes.
Makes 50 servings.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello; let set for 10 minutes.
Layer all ingredients, with yogurt in the middle.

title: caramel pudding
directions: Melt 1 cup of sugar in skillet until light brown.
Add boiling water and stir constantly until syrup forms.
Coat bottom and sides of ring mold or baking dish with syrup.

title: skillet "pizza"
directions: Melt fat in a 10-inch skillet. Spread half the potato slices over the bottom.
Sprinkle with salt and freshly ground pepper. Top with a layer of half the onion and half the green pepper, seasoning with salt and pepper.
Arrange half the meat atop. Repeat layers of vegetables and remaining meat for garnish. Cover and cook over low heat until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes. Break eggs into bowl.
Pour over potatoes, breaking yolks and spread eggs evenly with a fork.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan; place in oven to melt.
Remove pan from oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over melted butter; press down with fork.
Sprinkle coconut over crumbs, then add layer of chips and pecans.
Drizzle surface with milk.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut.
Makes 30 bars.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients and mix well.
Fill pans about 1/2 to 3/4 full and bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: sun pickles
directions: In a gallon glass jar, put 1 slice bread.
Add cucumbers which have been sliced longways, 8 ways, leaving ends attached.
Add dill, garlic, sliced onions and 3 to 4 tablespoons pickling salt. Fill jar with cold water; cover with cloth and set in sun for 4 to 5 days.
Store in refrigerator.
Use in 3 or 4 weeks.
Do not put lid on tight, just drop on, as the brine is still working!

title: chicken and biscuits
directions: Combine soup, chicken and cheese.
Cook over medium heat until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.
Serve over biscuits.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Place peppers and 1/2 cup vinegar in blender; puree.
Strain if desired.
Pour into large saucepan with sugar, a few drops of food coloring and remaining vinegar.
Stirring constantly, bring to a rolling boil that cannot be stirred down.
Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes.
Skim off foam and add pectin.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars.
Seal with paraffin.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms; remove stems.
Chop stems; set aside. In 4 cup glass measure, combine bacon, green pepper and onions. Cover with paper towels and cook on high, stirring once.
Drain off fat.
Add salt, cream cheese and Worcestershire sauce and mushroom stems.
Mix well.
Fill mushrooms with bacon mixture.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix with your hands the flour, sugar, baking powder and butter until crumbly. Take out 1 cup for topping, then the remaining. Add the eggs, milk and vanilla. Beat with mixer until creamy.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Sprinkle the crumbs you had set aside.
Bake at 350° until done.
You can test it with a toothpick. It should take about
35 to 45 minutes.

title: potato casserolefort collins, colorado
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh cucumber pickles
directions: Combine and heat sugar, water and vinegar until sugar melts. Cook and pour over remaining ingredients.
Stir and keep bowl in refrigerator.
The next day put in jars and refrigerate.
Will keep 8 weeks.

title: onion pie
directions: Make a crust of 30 small crushed saltine crackers and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Saute onion in butter until golden.
Put on top of crust.
Sprinkle the grated cheese and then pour the milk, egg and cheese mixture on.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until custard sets.

title: jello cheese cake
directions: Moisten crumbs with butter.
Press in bottom dish, leave some to sprinkle on top.
Whip cream cheese with Jell-O and hot water, add sugar.
Whip milk and mix with other ingredients.
Place in fridge for at least 1 hour before serving.
Can garnish with fresh or frozen fruit.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend together all ingredients; shape into a ball. Refrigerate.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Butter bottom of casserole dish.
Put 1/4 package bread crumbs in dish.
Combine all other ingredients except remainder of bread crumbs.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole.
Top with rest of bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: super simple home-made bread
directions: Measure dry ingredients into bowl.
Add eggs and milk, then beat until mixture is fairly smooth.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into Teflon lined loaf pan.
Bake at 360° for 30 to 40 minutes. Yields 1 loaf.

title: whoopee pies
directions: Mix crisco, sugar, egg, milk, vanilla, salt together until creamy.
Add flour, soda and cocoa.
Use 1/3 c. to place batter on greased cookie sheet and bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350 degrees. Place cream filling in between two chocolate cakes.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Place unpeeled potatoes in large saucepan.
Cover with water; cook until tender, but firm.
Drain.
Cut potatoes in 1-inch cubes.
Place in ungreased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add pimientos, onions, garlic and onion salt.
Place the bread cubes on top.
Pour butter over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bread is toasted.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: crab dip
directions: Stir soup mix, sour cream, lemon juice and hot pepper sauce until well blended.
Stir in crabmeat, artichoke hearts, cheese and dill until blended.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: brent's favorite spaghetti
directions: Cook onion in hot oil until golden; add meat and seasonings. Brown lightly.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine soup and cream cheese.
Use electric blender and mix well.
Add a few shakes of garlic salt and a couple drops of lemon juice.
Drain shrimp well and then add to mixture.
Mix with spoon.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put dry bread in cold water to soak.
Dice onion to make about 1/4 cup, then saute until golden brown; set aside.
Beat eggs with fork, then mix with meat.
Add all ingredients, except bread.
Mix well.
Hand squeeze the moisture out of the bread, crumble and add to the mixture.
If too wet, add a few bread crumbs.
Shape into loaf.
Place in greased baking pan.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.
Unbaked mixture can be divided and stored in freezer. Cut baking time for smaller loaves.

title: sausage balls
directions: Drop by teaspoons or roll quarter size balls. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350°.
Yields 60 sausage balls.

title: ham and vegetable chowder
directions: In 4-quart pan over medium heat, melt margarine.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in flour and cook until bubbly. Gradually stir in milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes or until slightly thickened and vegetables are tender. Makes 5 (1 1/4 cup) servings.

title: quiche
directions: Layer cheddar cheese, Mozzarella cheese, and cooked chicken in baked pie shell.
Mix together eggs, milk, flour, salt, and pepper.
Pour over layered cheese and chicken.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: butterfingers
directions: Let butter soften at room temperature before blending with sugar.
Add sifted flour slowly, mixing well.
Add to dough which will be stiff.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Shape into the size of dates and bake for 5 minutes at 400°.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
When light brown, they are done.
Let cool, then dip in powdered sugar.
Yields 25 cookies.

title: whole wheat biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside.
Sift together dry ingredients in a bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal using a pastry blender.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk, stirring until soft dough forms.
Knead 10 times.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch rounds.
Place on lightly greased pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 24.

title: state fair of texas corn dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients (except hot dogs) for batter.
Boil hot dogs; put sticks in end of each hot dog.
Dip in batter.
Cook in deep fat at 360° until brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecue pork and beef
directions: About 8 1/2 hours before serving, combine all ingredients in a 5-quart crock-pot.
Cook on high (300°). Stir with wire whisk until meat is shredded.

title: mexican quiche
directions: On floured
pastry
sheet,
roll
pastry
to 12-circle; place in	Ultra 21 (9-inch) Quiche/Pie dish.
Fold under extra pastry; flute
edges.
To
bake:
Line unpricked pastry with 2 layers heavy-duty	foil.
Bake
at
450° for 5 minutes. Remove foil; bake for
5 to 7 minutes more or until nearly done; keep warm.
For quiche filling, in skillet cook sausage, onions and garlic	until meat
is browned; drain well.
Stir in chilies; set aside.	In saucepan, combine cheese and flour;
add cream. Cook and stir over medium heat until cheese is melted; add hot pepper	sauce. Gradually
blend
hot cream mixture into eggs; add	meat
mixture. Pour into pastry.	Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until knife inserted off center comes out clean. Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken dish
directions: Boil chicken breast until tender.
Remove chicken and reserve 1/2 cup chicken broth.
Debone chicken and cut into bite-size pieces.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Place chicken pieces in baking dish.
Layer cream of celery soup and two cans of Veg-All.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Stir 1/2 cup chicken broth into cream of chicken soup.
Pour over casserole.
Stir together flour, melted margarine and milk until all lumps disappear.
Pour over the casserole and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: apple crunch
directions: Slice apples in bottom of pan.
Pour water over apples.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and flour together.
Cut in softened margarine. Sprinkle over apples. Cook for about 30 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower.
Strain.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with the mixture of the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and browned.

title: greens
directions: Wash by looking on both sides of leaf.
Be sure you wash real good.
Put in pot.
Add ham hock or vegetable oil and salt and pepper to taste.
Add water to 1/2 fill pot.
Cook until tender. A little sugar will make them very tender.

title: pineapple-cheese mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Beat by hand for 10 minutes.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Pour 1/2 cake batter into tube pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cinnamon mixture over batter and stir in like a marble cake. Repeat with remaining cake batter and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Bring rhubarb to a boil.
Add sugar; turn off heat and stir well.
Add Jell-O.
Stir well.
Put in jars.

title: italian beef
directions: Trim roast of any fat.
Place in roaster and cover the top with the chopped onion.
Combine the rest of the ingredients in blender until finely chopped.
Pour over the roast and cover. Bake 3 hours or until done.
There will be a lot of juice and the meat will be easy to slice.
Place on hard rolls and ladle juice over.
Enjoy!

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Fill greased muffin tins to top.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot. Yields 12 muffins.
May also be cooked in 8 x 8-inch square pan.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough and place on pizza pan that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Pat dough over top of pizza pan making sure no openings are left. Bake according to package directions, but only until light tan in color. Set aside to cool.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix onion, broccoli, cheese and bacon.
Toss with dressing of sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot cheese
directions: Melt cheese in microwave.
While still hot, add other ingredients; stir well.
Refrigerate.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: 3 day sweet pickles
directions: Put cucumbers whole in a brine of 12 cups water and 1 cup salt for 3 days.
After 3 days, take out of brine and rinse in cold water.
Cut cucumbers in 1/2-inch pieces.
Boil 2 cups water, 1 quart vinegar and alum the size of a walnut.
Put pickles in and boil 7 to 10 minutes.
Drain and throw away liquid.
Next, boil allspice, celery seed, mixed spice, 1 quart vinegar and sugar. Pour over pickles and let stand overnight.
Drain off liquid and boil again for 20 minutes.
Pour over pickles that have been put in pint jars and seal.
Very crisp and tasty.

title: spaghetti meat sauce deluxe
directions: In a large kettle, heat butter and olive oil and in this brown the meat.

Add the green pepper, garlic, onion, mushrooms, tomato paste, tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, Angostura Bitters, sugar, wine, salt and pepper to taste, celery salt, bay leaves and a generous dash of cayenne pepper.
Cover and cook slowly for at least 3 hours.

title: chili burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Shape into 4 patties, 3/4-inch thick.
Place patties on cooking grate and cook according to time given for hamburgers.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts. Store in refrigerator.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift flour and soda together. Sprinkle mace on this.
Add flour alternately with sour cream. Add flavoring.
Pour in a large greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 320°.

title: marinated chicken breast
directions: Let marinate for 24 hours.
Drain off.
Roll in flour and deep fry.
Don't overcook.

title: make brownies in waffle iron(fun for children)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Grease and heat waffle iron.
When hot, spoon brownie mixture onto waffle iron.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Place sugar, cornstarch and water in saucepan over low heat. Stir constantly and cook until mixture is thick, then cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add cooled sugar mixture and beat well. Spread over pie filling and bake 20 minutes or until browned at 350°.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown beef. Drain. Add sauce and seasonings. Mix well. Flatten each biscuit with a rolling pin. Press into well-greased cupcake tin (spray with Pam). Fill each one with beef and top with cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 10 cups.

title: baked brisket
directions: Salt and pepper brisket.
Slice onion and place on top of brisket.
Mix beer, brown sugar and flour.
Pour over meat.
Bake 4 to 5 hours.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Slice apples, unpeeled.
Mix remaining ingredients and use as a dip for the sliced apples.
Tastes just like old fashioned caramel apples.

title: easy hush puppies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, stirring well.
Carefully drop batter by tablespoon into deep hot 370° oil.
Fry 1 1/2 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Melt Jell-O in cup of hot water.
Cream the cheese and mayonnaise.
Add pineapple, lemon juice, Eagle Brand milk and Jell-O and mix together.
Pour in pan and chill for several hours. Cut into squares and serve.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter, add rice and stir constantly.
Put in casserole dish and add soup.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.
Can add mushrooms, almonds, peppers and onions toward the end of cooking.

title: lazy enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add enchilada sauce and soups.
Tear tortillas in small pieces.
Add tortillas and 3/4 of cheese to meat mixture.
Stir well and simmer 20 minutes.
Cover with remaining 1/4 of cheese; simmer until cheese melts.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Saute bacon drippings, flour, onions and garlic until onions are transparent. Add shrimp, okra, water and tomatoes. Simmer 5 minutes. Add rest of ingredients and simmer until done. Serve over rice.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar. Blend egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: snowball cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions and bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
While cake is baking, prepare topping.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Put all
ingredients in casserole dish.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Thaw to room temperature and remove parts bag from inside. Wash off the chicken and pat dry with paper towels.
Coat chicken with soft margarine.
Place in crock-pot.
Take dried mint in hand (approximately 1/2 to 1 teaspoon).
Crush and sprinkle over chicken.
Take dried onions and coat chicken generously.
Cover completely.
Turn on low for 8 hours.

title: creamy broccoli cheese dip
directions: Beat all ingredients in medium bowl.
Serve with vegetable dippers and assorted crackers, if desired.
Makes 3 1/2 cups. Prep time:
10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Add 1/2 stick margarine to broccoli and add Velveeta cheese; mix well.
Pour in buttered casserole.

title: stuffed chicken breast
directions: Combine stuffing mix.
1/2 cup juice, water and butter; add salt and pepper to taste.
Let stand for approximately 5 minutes. Wash and lay the chicken breast out.
Mound a large helping of stuffing mixture in the middle.
Wrap with a piece of bacon, secure with a toothpick.
Place on a slightly greased cookie sheet.
Mix 1/3 cup orange juice and honey, pour over top of each stuffed breast.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: meatless one pot meal(rice, beans and tomatoes)
directions: Heat the water to boiling. Add the rice. Salt to taste. Cook on low for 20 minutes. Add a little more water if needed. Then add the tomatoes and beans. Heat through and serve.

title: refried bean dip
directions: Mix beans, chilies, olives and add salsa to taste.
Heat in microwave until hot.
Sprinkle cheeses on top.
Heat until melted. Serve with chips.

title: fruit cocktail cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in 13 x 9-inch pan and put in oven to melt.
Mix milk, sugar and egg together.
Pour into heated pan.
Add fruit cocktail with juice and spread evenly. Heat in oven until brown on top.

title: nelle summerford's cheese biscuits
directions: Grate cheese and mix with combined dry ingredients.
Cut in butter and blend well.
Roll in small balls, place on cookie sheets, flatten with fork and top with a pecan half.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 10 1/2 dozen.

title: fruit pudding salad
directions: In large bowl, mix all drained fruits and bananas.
Fold in pie filling.
Mix pudding mix and milk until smooth.
Fold into fruits, bananas and pie filling and chill.

title: roast beef
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients and brown roast.
Cut slits in roast and fill with mixture.
Pour can of chicken broth over roast and bake at 350°, basting occasionally.
Bake, covered, until last 30 minutes or so.
Thicken the liquid (chicken broth) and it makes a delicious gravy.
This is easy and really delicious.

title: horseradish pickles
directions: Drain pickles and cut into strips.
Mix together celery seed, sugar and horseradish and pour over pickles.
Let marinate overnight.

title: cheese olive hors d'oeuvres
directions: Blend cheese with butter.
Sift together flour, salt and paprika.
Add cheese mixture and mix well.
Pinch off a small amount of the dough; flatten in the palm of your hand and wrap the dough around each olive.
Freeze.
Do not thaw before baking.
When ready to bake, place cheese balls on baking sheet and bake in a preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Form beef into patties.
Slice onion and place slices on beef. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place on foil and cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Place chicken breasts, parsley and chopped carrot in a pot. Salt lightly.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Cook until tender (approximately 45 minutes).
Remove chicken and cool.
When thoroughly cool, remove skin and bones. Shred meat in medium bowl.

title: 90 minute dinner rolls
directions: Mix 3/4 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat milk, water and margarine to 120°.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
Add 1/4 cup flour and beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on floured board and knead 2 to 3 minutes. Divide dough into 12 pieces.
Shape into balls and place in greased round pan.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Place rolls in cold oven and turn oven to 375°.
Bake 20 minutes or until done.
Serve warm.

title: vegetarian split pea soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a
Dutch oven. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour or until split peas are cooked through.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Makes 10 (1-cup) servings.

title: uncooked oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook on stove sugar, cocoa, milk and butter for 1 minute until all ingredients are dissolved.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by tablespoons onto cookie sheet or wax paper.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Put ribs in pan.
Mix rest of ingredients and thin out with a little water.
Pour over ribs.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: salsa a la miles
directions: Dice all of the ingredients into very small pieces.
Mix with lemon juice (fresh is best) and lime juice (about 3 large lemons and 1 large lime).
Add salt and pepper.
Chill and serve.
You can keep this in a Mason jar in the fridge for a long time.
The longer it sits, the hotter it gets.

title: butterflied leg of lamb(with barbecue sauce)
directions: Place lamb on a greased rack in a greased or foil-lined pan. Combine all Sauce ingredients in a saucepan and simmer 5 minutes. Roast lamb
in
a
350° oven until done, allowing 25 minutes per pound, plus
minutes
extra.
Baste lamb often while baking. Water may be added to pan to prevent scorching. Turn roast and use most
all
sauce.
Remove roast to platter, allowing to set at least 20 minutes before slicing.

title: candied nuts
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Coat nuts with this mixture.
Next, mix the remaining ingredients and the nut mixture; mix all ingredients well.
Spread covered nuts on a cookie sheet and bake for 15 minutes.
Turn over with spatula and bake another 15 minutes.
Bake at 325° to 350° depending on your individual oven.

title: chicken breasts in lemon sauce
directions: Cut each chicken breast horizontally to make 2 thin slices. Coat with flour.
Heat margarine in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Cook chicken and garlic in margarine 4 to 6 minutes, turn once, until chicken is brown.
Add wine or apple juice and lemon juice; sprinkle with pepper.
Heat until hot. Sprinkle with capers.
Garnish with strawberries and parsley.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Grease casserole.
Combine corn with egg, salt, sugar, cracker crumbs and milk.
Place in casserole.
Dot with butter and pepper. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rice custard
directions: Cook rice (wash well).
Add other ingredients and mix well. Place in glass dish and place in pan of water.
Bake at 350°.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; put in greased 3-quart casserole. Top with cheese and paprika, if desired.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Serves 8.

title: crab casserole
directions: In a large skillet, mix Chef's Blend and garlic; cook 2 to 5 minutes until lightly browned.
Add both cans of cream of mushroom soup and 1 can of water or broth and cook until bubbly.
Add carrots, okra and celery; mix and stir well, continuing cooking. Add lemon juice, Tabasco and crabmeat.
Add broth, enough to cover mixture and cook until carrots and okra are crunchy.
In a casserole dish layer 1 cup cooked rice.
Spread mix over rice and sprinkle Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake until mix is piping hot.

title: spinach pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into square baking dish or a pie plate.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour or until golden brown and firm.

title: granny's cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker crust according to package directions. Press in 8 x 8-inch dish.
Chill while beating filling.
Mix together cheesecake mix and whipped topping mix.
Add milk.
Beat at high speed until very thick.
Slice layer of bananas on graham cracker crust.
Spread filling over bananas.
Add layer of pineapple on filling.
Cover with Cool Whip.
For large dish, double measurements.

title: traditional reuben
directions: In medium skillet melt small amount of margarine.
Layer corned beef and cheese on bread and toast in skillet until browned.
Add generous helping of kraut, Russian dressing and onions, if desired. Enjoy!

title: chocolate yogurt melts
directions: Combine cake mix, yogurt, egg and margarine in bowl.
Beat until blended.
Stir in nuts and chips. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet with teaspoon 2-inches apart. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes, or until all liquid is absorbed.

title: crusty beef, cheese and noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add spaghetti sauce and salt.
Heat thoroughly.
Layer in very large casserole dish half the noodles, half the sauce and half the cheese.
Repeat layering.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Recipe can be halved.

title: spiced ham sauce
directions: Simmer all ingredients (except ham) for 1/2 hour.
Add ham and cook slowly until thick, approximately 1/2 hour.

title: party punch
directions: Combine juices and 7-Up in punch bowl.
Stir well.
You may want to add a little sugar.
Add sherbet and serve.

title: lemon bread(makes 3 loaves)
directions: *Nuts should be very fine, because the bread does not cut well if the nuts are too large pieces.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening together; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat after each one.
Add flour. Beat in lemon extract and 7-Up.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Top with crushed pineapple, if desired.

title: rhubarb relish
directions: Cook vinegar and rhubarb 20 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients and cook slowly about 1 hour.
Bottle and seal. Makes about 4 quarts.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: In food processor fitted with steel blade, break 3 or 4 slices of bread into bowl at a time and process to coarse crumbs. As processed, remove to a large bowl. Cut onion into eighths.
Wash celery and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Process vegetables until finely chopped. Heat butter in skillet and add vegetables and seasonings; cook over low heat about 10 minutes.
Add to bread crumbs and mix well.
With plastic blade, combine egg and stock. Mix into bread crumbs.
Use as a stuffing for turkey (or a roasting chicken if the recipe is halved and 1 small egg is used).

title: taco bake
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion, green pepper, salt and pepper. Add taco seasoning mix and water.
Stir and simmer.
Spread hamburger mixture over a layer of corn chips.
Cover with cheese slices and bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix the Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice together well.
Add the nuts, coconut, crushed pineapple and juice and Cool Whip.
Mix all together well.
Pour into a cracker crumb pie shell.
Sprinkle coconut on top; let set.
Makes 2 pies.

title: three fruit pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together and cook in a saucepan until thickened like pie filling.
Add the pecans and bananas to mixture.
Pour into 3 baked and cooled pie crusts.
Top with whipped topping, whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Beat cake mix, butter, oil and eggs together for 4 minutes. Mix juice in the mixture, then fold in the oranges.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple tapioca
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Let stand 5 minutes. Heat to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Simmer until apples are tender (approximately 12 minutes).
Serve warm with a sprinkle of nutmeg and a scoop of vanilla or French vanilla ice cream.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Scald milk in double boiler; add sugar, flour, cocoa and salt and blend well, stirring until thick and smooth (20 minutes). Beat egg yolks and pour a bit of hot mixture into this and return to double boiler for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and cool.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Mix water, sugar and food coloring in a skillet and stir until it boils.
Add nuts and boil until all sugar mixture is taken into nuts.
Pour nuts on a lightly buttered pan and bake 15 minutes at 250°.
You may use almonds instead of peanuts.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together the ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cool and frost.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cover raisins with water and bring to a boil. Cream lard and sugar. Add eggs. Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Add raisins, water and oatmeal. Nutmeats may be added. Drop by teaspoon on well-greased cookie sheet.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Remove ice cream from freezer and allow to soften slightly. Crush cookies until fine crumbs.
Using a glass baking dish, spread
a thin layer of cookie crumbs in bottom.
Spread softened ice cream on top of crumbs.
Do this until ice cream and cookie crumbs are gone.
Spread a generous layer of Cool Whip to "ice" your ice cream cake and garnish with cookie crumbs.
Place cake back into freezer until ice cream is again firm.
Enjoy!

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake in cake pan at 375° for 1 hour.
May not take whole hour, depending on oven.
Test for doneness with toothpick.

title: double chocolate torte
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions for fudgy brownies.
Grease a 9 inch round baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 38 - 42 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Invert onto serving dish.
Cool completely.
Melt the chocolate chips, add to softened margarine in a medium sized mixing bowl.
Stir until smooth. Spread over the brownie.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Just before serving top with whip cream.

title: meatballs in mushroom gravy
directions: Strain can of chicken rice soup.
Reserve juice for gravy but add thick parts to meat mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls and brown.
Place in baking dish.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup to drippings and juice from chicken rice soup with enough water to make 1 can.
Blend well and pour over mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes covered and another 15 minutes uncovered.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: auntie's cranberry salad
directions: Make the Jell-O; add sugar and set aside to cool.
Prepare all other ingredients and mix together.
Put into bowl or containers which you want to serve from.
Stir occasionally as it begins to jell, so it will be thoroughly mixed.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in microwavable dish.
Layer chili on top of cream cheese.
Layer green chilies over chili.
Heat in microwave until hot.
Put grated cheese on top.
Heat again in microwave until cheese is melted.

title: homemade zucchini bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in sugar, zucchini, oil and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients and spices.
Stir in nuts. Pour into bread pans which have been greased only on the bottoms. Bake at 325° for 60 to 80 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
May be used as bread or frosted and served as cake.

title: cheese and pepper sandwich
directions: Grind together onion, cheese, pepper and bacon. Spread on top of English muffin halves. Broil in oven until topping becomes bubbly.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, egg and onion.
Shape into 24 meatballs.
Brown meatballs, drain drippings.
In the same pan stir in soup and water.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes stirring often.
Serve with rice.

title: chess cake squares
directions: Mix cake mix, one egg and melted butter.
Pat out in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 3 eggs; pour over cake mixture.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 40 minutes. Cut into squares after cooling.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake as directed in two 9-inch pans.
Let cool 3 hours. Slice each layer in two, making 4 layers.

title: better than "any" cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and beat with electric mixer until smooth. Add next 3 ingredients. Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes. Use toothpicks for doneness. Let cool; remove from pan. Keep covered with foil or Saran Wrap for freshness.

title: quick sandwiches
directions: Mix soup with browned, drained hamburger.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Optional ingredients:
1 tablespoon ketchup, 1/2 teaspoon mustard and chopped onion.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix crumbs, cheese and chopped almonds together.
Blend butter and next 5 ingredients and spread over chicken breasts.
Dip pieces in crumb mixture to coat.
Put chicken in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 55 to 65 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa together.
Grate cheese.
Melt butter or oleo and cheese together.
Pour into sugar and cocoa mixture.
Add flavoring and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cut into squares when cool.
This can be divided, put nuts in half and leave half plain.
Enjoy!

title: earthquake cake
directions: In greased 9 x 13 pan, sprinkle nuts, coconut and chocolate chips. Blend margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese and set aside. Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed and pour over nuts, coconut and chips. Drop cream cheese mixture by spoonfuls over cake mixture as evenly as possible. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Can be spread with icing if you wish.

title: mom's cheesecake
directions: Whip the cream cheese until smooth.
Mix in the Eagle Brand condensed milk until smooth.
Add the sour cream and mix well. Finally, add the lemon juice and vanilla.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 8 minutes.

title: herb peel away bread
directions: Set aside 2 cups of bread flour. Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt, yeast, cheese and herbs. Heat water and 4 tablespoons butter until hot to the touch. Stir into dry mixture. Stir in egg and only enough reserved flour to make a soft dough. Knead until smooth and elastic. Then cover and let dough rest about 10 minutes. Roll into 12-inch square on lightly floured surface. Brush with 2 tablespoons melted butter. Cut into 25 squares. Overlap squares in greased, fluted tube pan. Let rise until doubled. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican munch
directions: Mix taco seasoning mix	with melted margarine.	Mix all other ingredients together in large
bowl and coat with margarine mixture.
Spread on cookie	sheet in single layer.	Toast in 200° oven, stirring frequently, until done.

title: vinegar rolls
directions: Combine vinegar, water, 1 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook over medium heat 20 minutes.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening; stir in milk with a fork until a soft dough forms. Roll out into a rectangle about 1/4-inch thick.
Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over dough.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Roll up, starting at long side.
Cut crosswise into slices about 1 1/4-inch thick.
Place cut side up close together in deep baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over rolls.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Serve hot with cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Store, covered, in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers, grate carrots and chop onions (including tops).
Combine all ingredients.
Great as a separate salad or used over tossed salad!

title: pineapple sauce for ham
directions: Mix well. Bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes. Add 2 1/4 tablespoons cornstarch in 1/2 cup water. Stir and cook until clear. Serve with ham.

title: potato salad - mustard style
directions: Have cooked potatoes cooled, cubed and mixed with chopped celery and hard-boiled eggs before making the dressing.

title: elsa's chile rellenos
directions: Cut cheese in 1-inch strips.
Clean peppers in running water, be careful not to break peppers.
Put peppers on paper towels and pat dry.
Put strips of cheese inside peppers and set aside.
Beat egg whites until fluffy and stiff; add yolks, keep beating.
Add flour and mix well.
Have frying pan ready with oil on medium heat.
Dip peppers in egg mixture until covered.
Fry until golden brown on all sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Serves 6.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and add water to juice; bring to boil.
While doing this, add sugar to cherries.
Pour juice into jello to dissolve.
Add cherries and nuts and refrigerate.

title: shoepeg corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter and cracker crumbs, and put into a 9 x 13 greased baking dish. Sprinkle combined cracker crumbs and butter over top and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger meat in large saucepan.
Add Worcestershire sauce, tomato puree or sauce, onion soup mix and seasonings. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add carrots and simmer 30 minutes. Add potatoes and simmer 30 minutes.
Add cans of vegetables all at once and simmer until heated, 15 minutes or so.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together first 9 ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese over chicken mixture and top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: two tens are twenty
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Cream 10 tablespoons of sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour, 1 tablespoon at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in 1 teaspoon baking powder and 1 teaspoon vanilla, if desired.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Combine the corn, beans, celery, onion, cheese, sour cream, soup and white pepper.
Stir well. Spoon into lightly greased 8-inch square dish. Combine butter, almonds and stuffing mix in a bowl. Toss gently. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: In large pan, bring potatoes, onion, chicken broth and water to a boil; simmer for 30 minutes. Add salt, pepper and bacon grease. Add remaining ingredients. Whisk to remove any lumps. Heat thoroughly but do not boil. Top with shredded cheese and crumbled bacon. Sprinkle with thyme and marjoram, if desired.

title: breakfast brunch
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Layer crescent rolls; pinch separations together. Next layer hash browns and mushrooms, if desired.
Crumble bacon, sausage or ham over hash browns. Scramble eggs, salt and pepper and pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Check after 1/2 hour for doneness.

title: shrimp over rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in pan.
Add soup and wine.
Add a little milk if too thick.
Fold in shrimp.
Heat slowly and serve over cooked rice.
For color, you can add peas or leave them out. Serves 4.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: dutch cream pie
directions: Mix the sugar, flour and salt in an unbaked pie shell.
Mix thoroughly with hands until well blended.
Pour the cream over the dry ingredients; do not mix.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° until bubbly and light brown on top.
The pie will be thin but will thicken when cool.

title: goblin punch
directions: Combine water and sugar in a saucepan; cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Cool; add juices and lemon rind.
Cover and chill.
Add cider just before serving.

title: frozen pudding sandwich
directions: Gradually add milk to peanut butter, blending until smooth. Add pudding mix slowly with rotary beater or at lowest speed with electric mixer for about 2 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Spread filling about 1/2-inch thick on 12 to 15 crackers.
Top with remaining crackers, pressing lightly.
Smooth edges with spatula.
Freeze until firm, about 3 hours.
Makes 12 to 15 sandwiches.

title: golden glow gelatin salad
directions: Grate or grind carrots; drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Heat to boiling juice, water and salt.
Dissolve jello in hot liquid. When jello is about to set, combine with carrots, pineapple and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Place in wet mold and chill until firm.
Makes 9 servings in a square pan or fewer in individual molds.

title: dixlucous meat loaf
directions: Except for ketchup, press into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Drain off excess fat.
Spread ketchup on top.
Bake 30 minutes until done.

title: compton's crab imperial
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, parsley and mustard (English fine dry mustard).
In a saucepan, heat milk until scalding, being careful not to burn.
Blend milk into the roux and gently stir in crabmeat, salting to taste.
(The success for this main dish is fresh lump crabmeat.)
Mix carefully; overmixing can make the tender meat flake and lose its rich texture.
Now, spoon the mixture into individual casseroles.
Sprinkle with melted butter; and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 425°.
Should be well heated and lightly browned.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Mix bran flakes, soda, salt and flour in a very large bowl. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Store covered in the refrigerator and use as needed, up to 6 weeks.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Boil onions and carrots until tender.
Melt oleo.
Mix with cornflakes.
Mix cheese with carrots and onions.
Put in greased casserole.
Sprinkle cornflake mixture on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat, then onion.
Put in tomato sauce with sugar, catsup, green pepper, garlic salt, pepper and salt.
Simmer slowly 1/2 hour.
Add water and cook another 1/2 hour.
Put in carrots and celery and cook 1 hour.
Add kidney beans.

title: green chili cheese quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
In blender, whirl eggs, cottage cheese, baking powder, salt, Tabasco and flour.
Pour into a large bowl.
Add cheese, chilies and butter.
Mix well.
Pour into baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into appetizer size squares.
Serve warm or cold.
Keeps 3 to 4 days in refrigerator.
Makes 60 to 70 appetizers.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Brown chicken in shortening and add celery, onions and pepper. Add broth.
Cover and cook until onions and celery are tender. Add Chinese vegetables and mushrooms.
Heat to boiling.
Mix soy sauce and cornstarch together.
Add to hot mixture.
Serve over rice.

title: schneider meat balls
directions: Mix together the soup and water. Combine the next 5 ingredients and add 1/4 of the soup mixture. Mix well. Shape into small balls (keeping hands wet to prevent sticking). Brown in 1 tablespoon oil in a skillet. Pour off drippings. Add remaining soup mixture (for more gravy, add 1 more can cream of mushroom soup).
