Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve over potatoes, rice or egg noodles.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken breasts about 1 hour.
Strip in big pieces and line bottom of casserole.
Drain and slice mushrooms and place on top of chicken.
Mix mushroom soup with sour cream.
Pour over chicken and mushrooms.
Melt 1/4 pound butter in skillet and add bread crumbs.
Place over casserole and bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: maria's mexican wedding cake
directions: Blend flour, sugar and soda.
Add pineapple and juice, eggs and vanilla.
Beat vigorously.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to the soft ball stage of a candy thermometer.
Add half of hot mixture to egg whites and beat until cool.
Let remaining syrup cook to the hard ball stage of candy thermometer.
Add to egg white mixture and beat until smooth.
Add vanilla and nuts. Pour into buttered pan and spread 1 inch thick. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute butter, garlic and lemon juice.
Add white wine and bring to a boil.
Add shrimp and cover.
Shrimp cooks fast, so watch closely.
Shrimp are done when the outside is pink and the inside is white.
Add capers just to heat.
Serve shrimp with some of the sauce and capers and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Saute onions and green pepper.
Brown hamburger.
Drain off excess fat.
Season with Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt.
Combine sauce, hamburger, onion and pepper in Dutch oven.
Add extra seasoning if needed. Grate cheese and add.
Stir until melted.
Add to taste.
Top with cheese.
Put in oven on 350°.
Bake about 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: fried catfish
directions: Pat fillets dry with paper towel.
Mix mustard and horseradish.
Spoon about 1 teaspoon on each piece of fish. Spread evenly over entire piece of fish.
Mix cornmeal and flour together.
Dip fish fillets gently in dry mixture.
Fry in deep, very hot cooking oil.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: grandchildren's favorite casserole(my grandchildren, especially dylan, love this dish!)
directions: Find a large roaster that will fit on your grill with the grill lid closed.
Lay a clean gunny sack in the bottom of roaster.
Peel back corn, leaving shucks still on, but removing the corn silks, then pull shucks back in place.
Layer corn in the bottom of roaster pan on top of gunny sack.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in buttered casserole dish until brown on top at 325°.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients; let stand at room temperature for 1 hour. Pour over 2 heads of fresh cut up broccoli and 1 head cut cauliflower.
Can use carrots and mushrooms.

title: fruit pie dough
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: steelhead scrambled eggs
directions: 1. Chop onions into small pieces. Shred leftover Steelhead.
2. Place steelhead and onion in mixing bowl with eggs.
Cook ingredients to desired texture.
3. Place sliced mushrooms on top of eggs after serving or
add during mixing.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Beat shortening with sugar; add eggs.
Sift and mix all dry ingredients except soda, together, then add 1/2 cup water to the soda and add to the rest of the ingredients.
Next put in the applesauce.
Mix all ingredients well in the mixer.
With the rest of the flour put aside, roll the nuts and raisins through it really well.
This keeps the nuts and raisins from sinking to the bottom of the cake.

title: butter pecan turtle cookies
directions: Mix together flour, 1 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup butter. Then pat firmly into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer pecans over the shortbread crust.
Make caramel layer by cooking 2/3 cup butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar until it boils for 1 minute.
Pour over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Wait 2 to 3 minutes then sprinkle chocolate chips or wafers.
Let melt for a minute or two, then swirl as they melt.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Beat in the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into deep dish pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Set aside.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In ungreased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch, stir together flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with a fork until smooth.
Add nuts.
Spread mixture into pan.

title: turkey noodle bake
directions: Slice mushrooms; cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain noodles reserving 2 1/2 cups of the cooking water. Blend flour in small bowl with a little of the measured water. Put remaining cooking water in saucepan.
Stir in blended flour, crumbled bouillon cube, salt, pepper and paprika, bring to a boil, stirring.
Reduce heat, add mushrooms and simmer 10 minutes. Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch souffle dish.
Remove saucepan from heat and stir in cream.
Arrange half the turkey over noodles and cover with half the sauce.
Repeat layers ending with sauce.
Scatter cheese over top, sprinkle bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix margarine and
grated cheese; add other ingredients one at a time, stirring well.
Pat
out by teaspoons on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for
about
15 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: pastry for 2-crust pie
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in Crisco.
Add cold water and mix with hands until soft dough.
Separate into 2 parts.
Roll out each part between 2 pieces of floured waxed paper.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix and bake for about 1 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar together and set aside.
Combine all other ingredients. Toss with sugar/vinegar mix 1/2 hour before serving.

title: crabmeat appetizer
directions: Mix crab, butter and cheese.
Spread on muffin quarters. Brown under broiler.
Makes 32.

title: praline pan biscuits
directions: Heat margarine and brown sugar in 1-quart saucepan until melted.
Pour into a 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Mix baking mix and milk until dough forms.
Beat 30 seconds.
If needed, add up to 1/4 cup more baking mix to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto surface dusted with baking mix.
Gently roll into baking mix to coat.
Knead 10 times.
Divide dough into 12 equal parts.
Gently shape each part into ball. Place balls on brown sugar mixture in pan.
Bake at 425° for about 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Invert pan on heat-proof serving plate.
Leave pan over biscuits a few minutes.
Cool slightly before serving.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: quick candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips in the microwave.
Pour over the next 4 ingredients mixed in a large bowl.
Place on waxed paper by spoonfuls and enjoy.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Spread in a casserole dish.
Crumble buns over pineapple.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Spread over pineapple mixture.
Allow to set 30 minutes.
Cook 30 minutes in a 300° to 350° oven.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix well. Form in balls.
Roll in powdered sugar. Bake 10 minutes at 350° on ungreased sheet.

title: wonderful bars
directions: Layer all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch baking pan in order give.
Do not stir.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, milk, sugar, oleo and vanilla.
Top with oleo, flour, brown sugar and nuts.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: biscuit pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cream of chicken, mixed vegetables and chicken in bowl.
Spread in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Put buttermilk biscuits on top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until edges of biscuits brown.

title: sherry cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with sauce.
Place a layer of noodles over the sauce.
Add half of the cheeses and cover with sauce.
Form another layer of noodles and cover with sauce. Add remaining cheese, except 1 cup of Mozzarella.
Cover with sauce.
Add remaining noodles and cover that layer with sauce.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish and cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: easy marinated mushrooms
directions: In
large
saucepan,
combine
the Italian dressing and mushrooms.	Bring
to
a
boil.
Cook,
uncovered,	for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add lemon peel and lemon juice. Cover
and chill for 4 hours or more.
Drain.
Stir parsley in the mushrooms.	Serve as an appetizer with toothpicks.

title: stuffed zucchini boats
directions: Wash zucchini.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds. Fill with shredded Mozzarella cheese, salt and pepper to taste. Broil until cheese is bubbly and slightly browned.
Serve hot.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Blend cake mix with cooked pudding.
Pour into prepared 9 by 13 pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Can be served warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: easy granola(can be doubled - freezes well)
directions: Set oven at 300°.
Boil honey and oils; add spices and vanilla.
Pour over oatmeal and mixed nuts in bowl.
Mix with hands until everything is evenly covered.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef.
Drain and add garlic, basil, oregano, thyme, salt, mushrooms, tomato paste, red peppers, chili powder, onion and bell pepper.
Simmer uncovered 30 minutes.
Cook noodles in salted water.
Set aside.
Mix cottage cheese, pepper, parsley, Parmesan cheese, beaten eggs and salt.
Place half cooked noodles in large shallow baking dish.
Spread half cheese mixture, half Mozzarella cheese and half meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes and let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together, adding cheese last.
Put into a greased casserole dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, baking powder, baking soda and salt, then add the pumpkin and chopped nuts.
In a separate bowl, mix corn oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into pumpkin mixture.
Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Pour half the batter into each pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger-vegetable soup
directions: Cook and stir hamburger in Dutch oven until light brown; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients; break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer just until vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings, about 1 1/2 cups each.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Beat in mincemeat.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: no bake fruit pie
directions: Open cans of fruit and drain for 30 minutes to remove juice. Mix, after drained, the fruit and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Pour ingredients into graham cracker crusts.
Chill and serve.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix all together except last 3 ingredients.
Steam cabbage a few minutes so they will roll easy.
Scoop large spoonful of meat mixture on cabbage leaf and roll.
Put a few tablespoons of sauce in roasting pan, then place cabbage rolls in pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top of rolls.
Cover with tomato and tomato paste mixture. Cover with lid.
Set oven at 300° to 350° for about 3 to 4 hours if Minute rice is used or 2 hours if cooked rice is used.

title: caramel clusters
directions: Put caramels and milk in a medium size saucepan over low heat. Cook, stirring occasionally, 15 to 20 minutes until caramels melt and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal and stir until coated.
Drop level tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool and set before serving.
Preparation time: 45 minutes.

title: deluxe peas and celery
directions: Cook peas, drain and set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan, add remaining ingredients (except peas) and cook until celery is crisp tender.
Add peas, heat thoroughly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: Mix together.
Pour in greased bread pan.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: janie's 4th of july chicken
directions: Melt the cube of butter and roll the chicken in it.
Then roll each piece of chicken in the mixture which includes the stuffing mix, parsley, Parmesan cheese and garlic powder.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add zucchini and dry ingredients.
Mix well; pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix together well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: hankie pankies
directions: Brown meat (ground chuck and sausage).
Drain off fat.
Add cheese and melt.
Add oregano and mix well.
Pat a tablespoon of mixture on party rye and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: danish cherry bars
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and flavoring.
Add dry ingredients.
Save 1/3 of batter.
Spread on a greased baking sheet.
Dough will be thick.
Cover with a large pan of cherry pie filling.
Add remaining dough by spoonfuls and spread lightly over cherry filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Drizzle with icing made of powdered sugar and milk.

title: chicken ravioli
directions: Steam fryer until very tender; remove fryer from broth and let cool.
Remove bones and chop meat into medium size pieces.
Saute in 1 stick melted oleo, chopped bell pepper and onion.
When about done, add poultry seasoning and oregano and garlic powder.
When done, add soup and pimento.
Stir in cooked noodles.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown and drain hamburger a skillet at a time.
Add to all other ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream margarine. Add sugar. Gradually add eggs and beat well. Add soda to applesauce and to the mixture. Add other ingredients and bake in a greased tube pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients well in a bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in milk.
Round up on lightly floured cloth-covered board.
Knead lightly for 30 seconds.
Roll dough out to about 1/2-inch thick. Cut close together with floured biscuit cutter.
Fit leftover pieces together.
Pat out and cut out remainder.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: old black joe cake
directions: Mix all dry
ingredients.
Add
eggs,
oil,
coffee and milk. Bake 25 to 30
minutes
Grease and flour pan, any shape or size.
Let coffee stand and cool before adding.

title: old-fashioned rice pudding
directions: Bring water to boil.
Stir in rice; cover and simmer until all water is absorbed.
Add milk and boil gently, stirring occasionally until mixture thickens slightly, about 5 minutes. Combine eggs, sugar and vanilla in bowl.
Gradually stir in rice mixture.
Add raisins, if desired, then pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cinnamon over the top.
Place casserole in pan containing about 1-inch of hot water.
Set both in oven preheated to 350°.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve warm or cold.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in water and juice until real soft.
Add sugar, then jello and thoroughly dissolve.
Cool.
Add fruits and nuts.
Makes 2 or more quarts.

title: pigeons
directions: Steam cabbage.
Pull off leaves and set aside.
Combine all ingredients except tomato sauce.
Shape into balls.
Wrap one ball in each cabbage leaf.
Secure with toothpick.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover with tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swiss steak dinner(serves 75 to 80)
directions: Swiss steaks are cooked in oil with quart of oil, browning along way to make stock for gravy.
Boil and mash potatoes.
Cook carrots and warm peas.
Prepare lettuce and onions as tossed salad.

title: french mint tea
directions: Juice lemons.
Add rinds to 6 cups water and sugar.
Boil 5 minutes and remove rinds.
Add vanilla, almond extract and lemon juice.
Set aside.

title: giant barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Form into balls the size of a tangerine.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour this sauce over meatballs and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes about 16 meatballs.
You can shorten cooking time by using a cooking bag, if desired.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Cook above ingredients until clear. Pour in 1 small pkg. peach jello; let cool. (To speed up cooling, put pot in large bowl of ice water.) Bake pie crust. Let crust cool. Pour a little jello (cool) mixture in bottom of cooled pie crust to seal the crust. Chill until set (few mins.). Put sliced fruit in crust and pour mixture over fruit. Shake gently to settle jello. Chill. Serve with whipping cream. This can also be made with strawberries and strawberry jello.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and 2 1/4 cups graham cracker crumbs.
Press into 12 x 9-inch cake pan or casserole dish to form a crust.
Bake for 5 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: sheath chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Melt together oleo, cocoa and water and boil.
Pour over flour and sugar and mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Bake at 375° in regular pan.

title: wet ones
directions: Cut one roll of Bounty towels in half.
Remove center cardboard; place upright in airtight container and pour solution over it.
Cover tightly and it's ready to use in one hour.
The wipes can be pulled up from the center just like the store-bought ones, and torn off at any length.
I use an empty 5 pound cottage cheese container (perfect size).

title: clare's whiskey sours
directions: Mix the sugar and lemon juice well. Add bourbon and seltzer or club soda.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fill a medium pan half full with water. Sprinkle with a little salt.
Add the vegetable oil.
Bring water to a boil.
Empty the box of uncooked macaroni into the pan.
Stir well once so macaroni does not stick.
Cook for 15 minutes, then pour all water.

title: sunshine sandwiches
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 2 teaspoons juice for Sunshine Sauce. Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper, if desired.
Brown in oil 7 minutes; cover while browning.
Spread rolls with Sunshine Sauce.
Top each sandwich with chicken, cheese, pineapple, lettuce and red onion, if desired.
Serves 2.

title: texas hash
directions: In heavy skillet (and use moderate heat), toss the ground pork back and forth until fat starts to fry out.
Push pork to one side and fry onion for five minutes, then mix with beef, stirring until beef loses its color.
Add rest of ingredients and turn into greased casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Pour off grease.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Serve with grated cheese.
Serves 6.

title: marinated garden salad
directions: Put all prepared vegetables into a large, sealable bowl (large Tupperware salad bowl).

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; let stand 10 minutes.
While it is standing, add margarine and let it melt in hot oatmeal.
When time is up, add other ingredients and pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: cabbage lasagna
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Add onion, garlic and mushrooms and saute.
Add spaghetti sauce.
In a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, place a layer of sliced cabbage, then meat and sauce and a layer of cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Cover with foil. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, removing foil last 1/2 hour.
Let set for 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: shaped sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter (or oleo), oil and both sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in and blend.
Roll dough into balls, using a teaspoonful for each ball.
Roll balls in granulated sugar.
Press down onto lightly greased cookie sheet with a glass (bottom) dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs until light yellow.
Add the next 3 ingredients together.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to first ingredients.
Blend well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in well-greased tube pan for 1 1/2 hours or in 9 x 13-inch oblong pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook stuffing mix.
Cook and drain the spinach.
Squeeze out excess liquid.
Mix all ingredients and chill.
Form into small balls and bake 15 minutes at 350° on a greased cookie sheet.
This freezes well.

title: scripture cake
directions: Make it a family project to look up the ingredients.
All are found in the Bible (King James version).
Cream the first 2 ingredients.
Add third ingredient one at a time.
Add fourth ingredient and beat well.
Mix ingredients 5, 6 and 7 and add alternately with ingredient number 8.
Stir in ingredients 9, 10 and 11.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt, milk and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell; sprinkle nutmeg over top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 50 minutes, or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: cuban black bean soup
directions: Brown
sausage	in
Dutch
oven
type saucepan, mashing sausage with
back	of
spoon
until
meat	is no longer pink. Spoon out fat and discard.	Add onion and garlic cooking until they
are soft but not browned.
Add all other ingredients but orzo, salt and pepper and bring to a boil.	Add orzo when soup is boiling and cook for 20 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: buttery peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in 3-quart pan.
When syrup boils, add butter.
Cook until 230°.
Stir frequently after that. Add nuts at 280° (soft crack).
Stir constantly until 305° (hard crack).
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda.
Pour on 2 cookie sheets, buttered.
As candy cools, stretch it thin, using forks.
Turn over as soon as stiff enough.
Break into pieces.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: no bake chocolate coconut pie
directions: Spread ice cream into crust evenly.
Spread with whipped topping and sprinkle with coconut.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer about 10 minutes before serving and dip pie pan in hot water to soften crust for easy cutting.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Wash chicken, salt and pepper.
Place in frying pan or pan large enough to hold all ingredients.
Pour remaining ingredients over chicken and cook 45 minutes at medium heat.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook until tender and ingredients have cooked down to a thick sauce.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring these ingredients to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Stir in 3 cups quick cooking oats and 1 cup walnuts or coconut or 1/2 cup of each.
Blend quickly; drop on wax paper.
Cool and enjoy. Makes 2 dozen.

title: spinach crab soup
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add spinach and onions.
Saute, stirring, until vegetables are soft.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Slowly add cream and milk, stirring constantly.
Stir in pimentos, wine, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer gently for 20 minutes.
Stir in cheese and crab meat.
Cover and simmer gently for 5 minutes. Stir once or twice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: basic cornbread dressing
directions: Simmer celery in boiling water for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender; drain, reserving 1 cup of liquid.
Cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soften bread crumbs in milk.
Cook onion in half of the butter for 5 minutes.
Add to bread crumbs.
Add beef, spices and egg. Mix well and form into 1-inch meatballs.
Saute in remaining butter in a skillet for about 10 minutes.
Blend flour and water to thicken consomme.
Add consomme and bake slowly for about 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs, cocoa, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts, if desired. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: crab cakes
directions: Take 1 pound crab meat for each four crab cakes.
Put crab meat into a mixing bowl.
Add the salt, pepper, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, egg yolk, cream sauce or mayonnaise and the parsley.
Mix well; make four crab cakes.
Press hard together. Dip into flour, then into beaten eggs, then into breadcrumbs.
Fry them in hot grease.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: The cream cheese should be soft.
Combine all ingredients and roll in a ball.
Cover with chopped nuts; chill.

title: basil marinated tomatoes
directions: In a saucepan:
Cook rice, enough for 6 to 8 servings, until it is dry and sticks to the bottom of the pan.
In a skillet, you can use either small diced chunks of pork steak, pork chops, ham, bacon, steak or leftovers, such as roast beef, etc.
Brown meat in a generous amount of shortening (or drippings) and just before it is done, add chopped onions (greens and all).
To this, stir in 1 egg and scramble.
Add the rice.
Sprinkle with soy sauce and continue to fry for awhile, stirring frequently.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Use a powdered sugar icing using strawberry juice.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Wash shrimp thoroughly; place in a large, shallow pan.
Add celery and garlic.
Squeeze juice from 2 lemons over top.
Dot shrimp with butter; sprinkle with remaining ingredients, except lemon wedges.
Place shrimp under broiler until butter melts and shrimp start to turn pink (about 5 minutes), stirring several times.
When all shrimp are slightly pink, reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until done, stirring often. Do not overcook, or shrimp will become mushy.
Taste for doneness.
Garnish with lemon wedges.
Yields 2 generous servings.

title: chicken casserole(usa)
directions: Cook chicken and cool.
Break into pieces and put into baking pan.
Pour on heated soup.
Make Stove Top as directed and put on top of chicken and soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: one dish chocolate cake
directions: Use an 8 or 9 inch pan. Set sidter in pan, put dry ingredients into sifter: sift into pan, after all dry ingredients are sifted remove sifter,make 3 hole( a happy face with the back of a spoon), put vanilla, vinegar, and oil in. One in each hole. Pour over it 1 cup of water and stir with a fork. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar through a paper doiley to dress it up.
This was passed down for 4 generations.

title: caramel corn
directions: In saucepan, boil brown sugar, butter and corn syrup for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, salt and baking soda; blend.
Pour over popcorn and mix well.
Add peanuts and mix again.
Place in large pan and bake 40 minutes in 250° oven.
Stir about every 10 minutes.
Place on wax paper or large cookie sheet and allow to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: *pecan pralines
directions: Mix sugar, milk, marshmallows and butter in saucepan.
Heat until melted.
Add pecans and cook until soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and beat only until it starts to lose its gloss.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix and bake until thick and brown.
Bake at 350°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt together the square of chocolate and the stick of butter. Mix the sugar, eggs, salt and vanilla together.
Add these ingredients to the chocolate mixture.
Mix, then pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serve with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle orange juice over apples.
Toss to cover well and drain.
Combine all other ingredients except lettuce.
Cover and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks until light.
Beat in sugar until mixture is thick.
Stir in milk and rum.
Chill for 3 hours.
Pour into punch bowl.
Fold in heavy cream, stiffly whipped.
Chill for one hour. Dust with nutmeg.
Serves 20.

title: no bake cabbage rolls
directions: Melt small amount of butter or margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan. Chop cabbage and put in bottom of casserole.
Brown beef and onion and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Pour over cabbage.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or longer.
Better if baked longer at lower heat.

title: chicken chili
directions: In kettle, saute onion and garlic in oil until limp.
Add ground chicken and braise.
Add water and tomato sauce.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Mix well, cover and simmer 4 hours. Makes 8 servings.

title: canadian-style pork chops
directions: Season pork chops to taste (I like lots of garlic powder on chops).
Place in baking pan.
Add onion and pour mushroom soup plus 1 can of cold water over chops.
Mix liquid well and cover chops completely.
Cover with foil and bake in preheated oven at 350°, until tender and well done (approximately 65 to 75 minutes). Turn once and uncover 10 minutes before it is finished to get brown color.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter and chocolate over medium-low heat, stirring until well blended.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in the flour and then mix in the walnuts.

title: corn-chili-cheese casserole
directions: Place ingredients in a large bowl and mix.
Turn into buttered shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, 40 minutes or until set.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows until smooth.
Add vanilla and food coloring, then add the corn flakes.
While still hot, pour mixture onto wax paper and form it into a wreath.
Let set, then decorate with cherries.

title: salmon or tuna loaf(lo-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Drain salmon or tuna and place in a mixing bowl; flake.
Add remaining ingredients except yogurt, lemon juice and tarragon.
Mix well.
Spray a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick spray. Turn fish mixture into prepared pan and smooth the top. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli and wild rice bake
directions: Cook broccoli stems in enough boiling, salted water to cover for 5 minutes.
Add flowerets; cook 4 to 5 minutes more or until tender.
Drain.
Prepare rice mix according to package directions. Combine sauce and soup mixes.
Stir in milk.
In a 2 quart casserole combine rice and milk mixture; fold in broccoli. Combine remaining ingredients; sprinkle over top.
Bake, uncovered, in 350 degree oven 35 to 40 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spinach madeleine
directions: Saute butter, onion and flour.
Add 1/2 cup liquid and 1/2 cup milk.
Mix together, then add cubed cheese, celery salt, garlic salt and Worcestershire.
Mix well.
Add drained spinach and stir. Put in casserole dish, top with crushed cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Preheat oven to about 400°.
Bake until brown and crispy.

title: banana cake
directions: Combine sugar and eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Add margarine, dry ingredients,
bananas and sour cream; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
In 1 bowl, sift flour; add cinnamon and nutmeg.
In second bowl, cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Stir in pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients to this mixture alternately with water just enough to mix.
Fold in nuts.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes. Cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: lentil soup
directions: Mix together all ingredients except soy sauce in large pan of water. Cover and bring to boil; reduce heat. When everything is cooking well; add soy sauce (this is the secret ingredient).

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in oil about 2 minutes; combine cornstarch in small amount of water until dissolved.
Add salt, 1 cup water, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over cabbage and cook approximately 5 minutes until mixture is slightly thick and liquid is clear.

title: cinnamon bars
directions: Pat 1 large roll of crescent rolls in bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Do not tear rolls apart, just unroll.)

Mix the cheese, 1 cup sugar and vanilla until smooth and spread over crescents. Pat the other roll of crescents on top of the cheese. Melt 1 stick margarine and pour on top. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rice with pigeon peas
directions: In a medium Dutch oven, put together oil, sason, sofrito, cooked ham or sausage, tomato sauce, oregano, paprika and pigeon peas.
Bring to boil.
Wash the rice one time with clear water; drain, then put with other ingredients.
Add the 4 cups of water and salt.
Let it boil until dried, then stir and cover.
Let it cook at medium temperature for 25 minutes.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Mix flour, yeast and sugar together.
Beat in egg, oil and water.
Cover bowl; refrigerate until ready to bake.
Grease muffin tins; fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add oil, zucchini, eggs and vanilla, then add nuts.
Grease loaf pans.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: easy spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large pot, mix all the ingredients.
Break up the hamburger as you put it in the pot.
Cook on top of stove on medium heat until it starts to cook, then reduce to low heat and continue cooking for 1 hour.
Yields 5 (16 ounce) containers.
Freezes real well.

title: salsa
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a bowl or container and chill in refrigerator.
Dip your favorite chips in the salsa and enjoy.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Beat on medium for 10 minutes or until sugar is dissolved and mixture is creamy, will look curdled to start.
This is easier than buttercream, really creamy and not too sweet.

title: meat loaf pie
directions: Empty tomato soup into a casserole dish.
Empty peas into dish on top of tomato soup.
Fry some ground meat with onion and season to taste.
After meat is cooked, spread evenly in dish over peas. Cream a couple of potatoes (season to taste) and spread over meat. Heat in oven about 15 minutes.
I always spread a little cheese on potatoes before heating!

title: quick tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Stir in soup and tuna.
Add salt and pepper.
Spread into shallow baking dish. Top with shredded cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 5 to 8 minutes until cheese is melted.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Cut cool cake made from packaged mix or bakery bought, crosswise in 4 equal layers.
Spread tops of 3 bottom layers with ice cream, using a different flavor for each.
(You can choose your favorites.)
Do one at a time, starting with strawberry and place immediately in freezer or refrigerator's freezing section.
Proceed with chocolate ice cream.
Stack on top of strawberry in freezer. Follow with layer spread with pistachio ice cream.
Add top layer of cake.
Work fast.

title: sauteed shredded zucchini with browned onions
directions: Heat a heavy skillet (preferably cast-iron) over medium-high heat.
Add the onions to the skillet and, stirring and tossing frequently to keep them from sticking, cook until golden brown, 7 to 9 minutes.
Scrape into small bowl.
Wipe out the skillet with a paper towel, return to the heat and add the oil.
When the oil is hot and coating the bottom of skillet, add the grated zucchini. Saute for 1 to 2 minutes, until the zucchini is heated through. Add the browned onions, salt and pepper.
Serves 8.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Put sugar and water in a saucepan.
Cut shortening into flour until it is fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir until dough leaves side of bowl.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Roll dough out into rectangle shape about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread apples evenly over dough.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up dough with apples like jelly roll.
Dampen edge of dough and seal. Slice dough into 16 slices 1/2-inch thick. Lay in pan of butter. Pour sugar water over this.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: grandma ray's hermits
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with mixer.
Stir in rest (except raisins and nuts).
Mix well, then add raisins and nuts.
Spread out on ungreased 11 x 17-inch pan with fingers.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool. (Great comfort food!)

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat lightly 1 egg.
Stir in milk and oil.
Sift together and add flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Blend in blueberries carefully, stirring just until flour is moistened.

title: ham and swiss scallop
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine, stir in flour.
Gradually add milk.
Stir until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese, stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 (2-quart) casseroles.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Uncover and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: pineapple pancakes
directions: Stir together the flour, sugar and nutmeg.
Blend together all remaining ingredients.
Add all at once to flour mixture, stirring only until flour is moistened.
Bake on greased griddle.

title: old-fashioned sweet rolls
directions: Rub together first 4 ingredients as for pie crust.
Heat milk; add egg yolks and yeast cakes dissolved in warm water.
Add dry mixture; stir well.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Form into rolls and let rise.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Top with any flavored frosting, nuts, sprinkles, sugar, etc.

title: tortilla wheels
directions: Put all ingredients, except tortillas, into food processor or blender; process until smooth.
Spread onto tortillas.
Roll up. Roll damp paper towel around each tortilla.
Put in a Ziploc bag and refrigerate for at least 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut into pinwheels and serve with salsa.

title: hearty breakfast muffins
directions: Beat oil, egg and milk in medium bowl.	Add remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Spoon into sprayed muffin tin (12). Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: calico beans
directions: Precook your ground beef and bacon and drain, then put all ingredients together in a large pot and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 1 hour or longer.
Ready to eat.
This is a meal in itself!

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onion and drain. Add remaining ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Bake 30-45 minutes or until bubbling.
